87/*
88 * This is the map file header for RBTDB images. It is populated, and then
89 * written, as the LAST thing done to the file. Writing this last (with
90 * zeros in the header area initially) will ensure that the header is only
91 * valid when the RBTDB image is also valid.
92 */
93typedef struct rbtdb_file_header rbtdb_file_header_t;
94
95/* Header length, always the same size regardless of structure size */
96#define RBTDB_HEADER_LENGTH 1024
97
98struct rbtdb_file_header {
99 char version1[32];
100 uint32_t ptrsize;
101 unsigned int bigendian:1;
102 uint64_t tree;
103 uint64_t nsec;
104 uint64_t nsec3;
105
106 char version2[32]; /* repeated; must match version1 */
107};

110/*%
111 * Note that "impmagic" is not the first four bytes of the struct, so
112 * ISC_MAGIC_VALID cannot be used.
113 */
114#define VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb) ((rbtdb) != NULL && \
115 (rbtdb)->common.impmagic == RBTDB_MAGIC)

120#define RBTDB_RDATATYPE_BASE(type) ((dns_rdatatype_t)((type) & 0xFFFF))
121#define RBTDB_RDATATYPE_EXT(type) ((dns_rdatatype_t)((type) >> 16))
122#define RBTDB_RDATATYPE_VALUE(base, ext) ((rbtdb_rdatatype_t)(((uint32_t)ext) << 16) | (((uint32_t)base) & 0xffff))
123
124#define RBTDB_RDATATYPE_SIGNSEC \
125 RBTDB_RDATATYPE_VALUE(dns_rdatatype_rrsig, dns_rdatatype_nsec)
126#define RBTDB_RDATATYPE_SIGNSEC3 \
127 RBTDB_RDATATYPE_VALUE(dns_rdatatype_rrsig, dns_rdatatype_nsec3)
128#define RBTDB_RDATATYPE_SIGNS \
129 RBTDB_RDATATYPE_VALUE(dns_rdatatype_rrsig, dns_rdatatype_ns)
130#define RBTDB_RDATATYPE_SIGCNAME \
131 RBTDB_RDATATYPE_VALUE(dns_rdatatype_rrsig, dns_rdatatype_cname)
132#define RBTDB_RDATATYPE_SIGDNAME \
133 RBTDB_RDATATYPE_VALUE(dns_rdatatype_rrsig, dns_rdatatype_dname)
134#define RBTDB_RDATATYPE_SIGDDS \
135 RBTDB_RDATATYPE_VALUE(dns_rdatatype_rrsig, dns_rdatatype_ds)
136#define RBTDB_RDATATYPE_NCACHEANY \
137 RBTDB_RDATATYPE_VALUE(0, dns_rdatatype_any)

139#define RBTDB_INITLOCK(l) isc_rwlock_init((l), 0, 0)
140#define RBTDB_DESTROYLOCK(l) isc_rwlock_destroy(l)
141#define RBTDB_LOCK(l, t) RWLOCK((l), (t))
142#define RBTDB_UNLOCK(l, t) RWUNLOCK((l), (t))
143
144/*
145 * Since node locking is sensitive to both performance and memory footprint,
146 * we need some trick here. If we have both high-performance rwlock and
147 * high performance and small-memory reference counters, we use rwlock for
148 * node lock and isc_refcount for node references. In this case, we don't have
149 * to protect the access to the counters by locks.
150 * Otherwise, we simply use ordinary mutex lock for node locking, and use
151 * simple integers as reference counters which is protected by the lock.
152 * In most cases, we can simply use wrapper macros such as NODE_LOCK and
153 * NODE_UNLOCK. In some other cases, however, we need to protect reference
154 * counters first and then protect other parts of a node as read-only data.
155 * Special additional macros, NODE_STRONGLOCK(), NODE_WEAKLOCK(), etc, are also
156 * provided for these special cases. When we can use the efficient backend
157 * routines, we should only protect the "other members" by NODE_WEAKLOCK(read).
158 * Otherwise, we should use NODE_STRONGLOCK() to protect the entire critical
159 * section including the access to the reference counter.
160 * Note that we cannot use NODE_LOCK()/NODE_UNLOCK() wherever the protected
161 * section is also protected by NODE_STRONGLOCK().
162 */
163typedef isc_rwlock_t nodelock_t;
164
165#define NODE_INITLOCK(l) isc_rwlock_init((l), 0, 0)
166#define NODE_DESTROYLOCK(l) isc_rwlock_destroy(l)
167#define NODE_LOCK(l, t) RWLOCK((l), (t))
168#define NODE_UNLOCK(l, t) RWUNLOCK((l), (t))
169#define NODE_TRYUPGRADE(l) isc_rwlock_tryupgrade(l)
170#define NODE_DOWNGRADE(l) isc_rwlock_downgrade(l)
171
172/*%
173 * Whether to rate-limit updating the LRU to avoid possible thread contention.
174 * Our performance measurement has shown the cost is marginal, so it's defined
175 * to be 0 by default either with or without threads.
176 */
177#ifndef DNS_RBTDB_LIMITLRUUPDATE
178#define DNS_RBTDB_LIMITLRUUPDATE 0
179#endif
180
181/*
182 * Allow clients with a virtual time of up to 5 minutes in the past to see
183 * records that would have otherwise have expired.
184 */
185#define RBTDB_VIRTUAL 300

194typedef struct rdatasetheader {
195 /*%
196 * Locked by the owning node's lock.
197 */
198 rbtdb_serial_t serial;
199 dns_ttl_t rdh_ttl;
200 rbtdb_rdatatype_t type;
201 uint16_t attributes;
202 dns_trust_t trust;
203 struct noqname *noqname;
204 struct noqname *closest;
205 unsigned int is_mmapped : 1;
206 unsigned int next_is_relative : 1;
207 unsigned int node_is_relative : 1;
208 unsigned int resign_lsb : 1;
209 /*%<
210 * We don't use the LIST macros, because the LIST structure has
211 * both head and tail pointers, and is doubly linked.
212 */
213
214 struct rdatasetheader *next;
215 /*%<
216 * If this is the top header for an rdataset, 'next' points
217 * to the top header for the next rdataset (i.e., the next type).
218 * Otherwise, it points up to the header whose down pointer points
219 * at this header.
220 */
221
222 struct rdatasetheader *down;
223 /*%<
224 * Points to the header for the next older version of
225 * this rdataset.
226 */
227
228 uint32_t count;
229 /*%<
230 * Monotonously increased every time this rdataset is bound so that
231 * it is used as the base of the starting point in DNS responses
232 * when the "cyclic" rrset-order is required. Since the ordering
233 * should not be so crucial, no lock is set for the counter for
234 * performance reasons.
235 */
236
237 dns_rbtnode_t *node;
238 isc_stdtime_t last_used;
239 ISC_LINK(struct rdatasetheader) link;
240
241 unsigned int heap_index;
242 /*%<
243 * Used for TTL-based cache cleaning.
244 */
245 isc_stdtime_t resign;
246 /*%<
247 * Case vector. If the bit is set then the corresponding
248 * character in the owner name needs to be AND'd with 0x20,
249 * rendering that character upper case.
250 */
251 unsigned char upper[32];
252} rdatasetheader_t;
253
254typedef ISC_LIST(rdatasetheader_t) rdatasetheaderlist_t;
255typedef ISC_LIST(dns_rbtnode_t) rbtnodelist_t;
256
257#define RDATASET_ATTR_NONEXISTENT 0x0001
258/*%< May be potentially served as stale data. */
259#define RDATASET_ATTR_STALE 0x0002
260#define RDATASET_ATTR_IGNORE 0x0004
261#define RDATASET_ATTR_RETAIN 0x0008
262#define RDATASET_ATTR_NXDOMAIN 0x0010
263#define RDATASET_ATTR_RESIGN 0x0020
264#define RDATASET_ATTR_STATCOUNT 0x0040
265#define RDATASET_ATTR_OPTOUT 0x0080
266#define RDATASET_ATTR_NEGATIVE 0x0100
267#define RDATASET_ATTR_PREFETCH 0x0200
268#define RDATASET_ATTR_CASESET 0x0400
269#define RDATASET_ATTR_ZEROTTL 0x0800
270#define RDATASET_ATTR_CASEFULLYLOWER 0x1000
271/*%< Ancient - awaiting cleanup. */
272#define RDATASET_ATTR_ANCIENT 0x2000
273
274/*
275 * XXX
276 * When the cache will pre-expire data (due to memory low or other
277 * situations) before the rdataset's TTL has expired, it MUST
278 * respect the RETAIN bit and not expire the data until its TTL is
279 * expired.
280 */
281
282#undef IGNORE /* WIN32 winbase.h defines this. */
283
284#define EXISTS(header) \
285 (((header)->attributes & RDATASET_ATTR_NONEXISTENT) == 0)
286#define NONEXISTENT(header) \
287 (((header)->attributes & RDATASET_ATTR_NONEXISTENT) != 0)
288#define IGNORE(header) \
289 (((header)->attributes & RDATASET_ATTR_IGNORE) != 0)
290#define RETAIN(header) \
291 (((header)->attributes & RDATASET_ATTR_RETAIN) != 0)
292#define NXDOMAIN(header) \
293 (((header)->attributes & RDATASET_ATTR_NXDOMAIN) != 0)
294#define STALE(header) \
295 (((header)->attributes & RDATASET_ATTR_STALE) != 0)
296#define RESIGN(header) \
297 (((header)->attributes & RDATASET_ATTR_RESIGN) != 0)
298#define OPTOUT(header) \
299 (((header)->attributes & RDATASET_ATTR_OPTOUT) != 0)
300#define NEGATIVE(header) \
301 (((header)->attributes & RDATASET_ATTR_NEGATIVE) != 0)
302#define PREFETCH(header) \
303 (((header)->attributes & RDATASET_ATTR_PREFETCH) != 0)
304#define CASESET(header) \
305 (((header)->attributes & RDATASET_ATTR_CASESET) != 0)
306#define ZEROTTL(header) \
307 (((header)->attributes & RDATASET_ATTR_ZEROTTL) != 0)
308#define CASEFULLYLOWER(header) \
309 (((header)->attributes & RDATASET_ATTR_CASEFULLYLOWER) != 0)
310#define ANCIENT(header) \
311 (((header)->attributes & RDATASET_ATTR_ANCIENT) != 0)
312
313#define ACTIVE(header, now) \
314 (((header)->rdh_ttl > (now)) || \
315 ((header)->rdh_ttl == (now) && ZEROTTL(header)))
316
317#define DEFAULT_NODE_LOCK_COUNT 7 /*%< Should be prime. */
318#define RBTDB_GLUE_TABLE_INIT_SIZE 2U
319
320/*%
321 * Number of buckets for cache DB entries (locks, LRU lists, TTL heaps).
322 * There is a tradeoff issue about configuring this value: if this is too
323 * small, it may cause heavier contention between threads; if this is too large,
324 * LRU purge algorithm won't work well (entries tend to be purged prematurely).
325 * The default value should work well for most environments, but this can
326 * also be configurable at compilation time via the
327 * DNS_RBTDB_CACHE_NODE_LOCK_COUNT variable. This value must be larger than
328 * 1 due to the assumption of overmem_purge().
329 */
330#ifdef DNS_RBTDB_CACHE_NODE_LOCK_COUNT
331#if DNS_RBTDB_CACHE_NODE_LOCK_COUNT <= 1
332#error "DNS_RBTDB_CACHE_NODE_LOCK_COUNT must be larger than 1"
333#else
334#define DEFAULT_CACHE_NODE_LOCK_COUNT DNS_RBTDB_CACHE_NODE_LOCK_COUNT
335#endif
336#else
337#define DEFAULT_CACHE_NODE_LOCK_COUNT 16
338#endif /* DNS_RBTDB_CACHE_NODE_LOCK_COUNT */
339

385typedef struct rbtdb_version {
386 /* Not locked */
387 rbtdb_serial_t serial;
388 dns_rbtdb_t * rbtdb;
389 /*
390 * Protected in the refcount routines.
391 * XXXJT: should we change the lock policy based on the refcount
392 * performance?
393 */
394 isc_refcount_t references;
395 /* Locked by database lock. */
396 bool writer;
397 bool commit_ok;
398 rbtdb_changedlist_t changed_list;
399 rdatasetheaderlist_t resigned_list;
400 ISC_LINK(struct rbtdb_version) link;
401 dns_db_secure_t secure;
402 bool havensec3;
403 /* NSEC3 parameters */
404 dns_hash_t hash;
405 uint8_t flags;
406 uint16_t iterations;
407 uint8_t salt_length;
408 unsigned char salt[DNS_NSEC3_SALTSIZE];
409
410 /*
411 * records and bytes are covered by rwlock.
412 */
413 isc_rwlock_t rwlock;
414 uint64_t records;
415 uint64_t bytes;
416
417 isc_rwlock_t glue_rwlock;
418 size_t glue_table_size;
419 size_t glue_table_nodecount;
420 rbtdb_glue_table_node_t **glue_table;
421} rbtdb_version_t;
422
423typedef ISC_LIST(rbtdb_version_t) rbtdb_versionlist_t;
424
425struct dns_rbtdb {
426 /* Unlocked. */
427 dns_db_t common;
428 /* Locks the data in this struct */
429 isc_rwlock_t lock;
430 /* Locks the tree structure (prevents nodes appearing/disappearing) */
431 isc_rwlock_t tree_lock;
432 /* Locks for individual tree nodes */
433 unsigned int node_lock_count;
434 rbtdb_nodelock_t * node_locks;
435 dns_rbtnode_t * origin_node;
436 dns_rbtnode_t * nsec3_origin_node;
437 dns_stats_t * rrsetstats; /* cache DB only */
438 isc_stats_t * cachestats; /* cache DB only */
439 isc_stats_t * gluecachestats; /* zone DB only */
440 /* Locked by lock. */
441 unsigned int active;
442 isc_refcount_t references;
443 unsigned int attributes;
444 rbtdb_serial_t current_serial;
445 rbtdb_serial_t least_serial;
446 rbtdb_serial_t next_serial;
447 rbtdb_version_t * current_version;
448 rbtdb_version_t * future_version;
449 rbtdb_versionlist_t open_versions;
450 isc_task_t * task;
451 dns_dbnode_t *soanode;
452 dns_dbnode_t *nsnode;
453
454 /*
455 * Maximum length of time to keep using a stale answer past its
456 * normal TTL expiry.
457 */
458 dns_ttl_t serve_stale_ttl;
459
460 /*
461 * This is a linked list used to implement the LRU cache. There will
462 * be node_lock_count linked lists here. Nodes in bucket 1 will be
463 * placed on the linked list rdatasets[1].
464 */
465 rdatasetheaderlist_t *rdatasets;
466
467 /*%
468 * Temporary storage for stale cache nodes and dynamically deleted
469 * nodes that await being cleaned up.
470 */
471 rbtnodelist_t *deadnodes;
472
473 /*
474 * Heaps. These are used for TTL based expiry in a cache,
475 * or for zone resigning in a zone DB. hmctx is the memory
476 * context to use for the heap (which differs from the main
477 * database memory context in the case of a cache).
478 */
479 isc_mem_t *hmctx;
480 isc_heap_t **heaps;
481
482 /*
483 * Base values for the mmap() code.
484 */
485 void * mmap_location;
486 size_t mmap_size;
487
488 /* Locked by tree_lock. */
489 dns_rbt_t * tree;
490 dns_rbt_t * nsec;
491 dns_rbt_t * nsec3;
492
493 /* Unlocked */
494 unsigned int quantum;
495};

625/*
626 * Note that these iterators, unless created with either DNS_DB_NSEC3ONLY or
627 * DNS_DB_NONSEC3, will transparently move between the last node of the
628 * "regular" RBT ("chain" field) and the root node of the NSEC3 RBT
629 * ("nsec3chain" field) of the database in question, as if the latter was a
630 * successor to the former in lexical order. The "current" field always holds
631 * the address of either "chain" or "nsec3chain", depending on which RBT is
632 * being traversed at given time.
633 */
634static void dbiterator_destroy(dns_dbiterator_t **iteratorp);
635static isc_result_t dbiterator_first(dns_dbiterator_t *iterator);
636static isc_result_t dbiterator_last(dns_dbiterator_t *iterator);
637static isc_result_t dbiterator_seek(dns_dbiterator_t *iterator,
638 const dns_name_t *name);
639static isc_result_t dbiterator_prev(dns_dbiterator_t *iterator);
640static isc_result_t dbiterator_next(dns_dbiterator_t *iterator);
641static isc_result_t dbiterator_current(dns_dbiterator_t *iterator,
642 dns_dbnode_t **nodep,
643 dns_name_t *name);
644static isc_result_t dbiterator_pause(dns_dbiterator_t *iterator);
645static isc_result_t dbiterator_origin(dns_dbiterator_t *iterator,
646 dns_name_t *name);
647
648static dns_dbiteratormethods_t dbiterator_methods = {
649 dbiterator_destroy,
650 dbiterator_first,
651 dbiterator_last,
652 dbiterator_seek,
653 dbiterator_prev,
654 dbiterator_next,
655 dbiterator_current,
656 dbiterator_pause,
657 dbiterator_origin
658};
659
660#define DELETION_BATCH_MAX 64
661
662/*
663 * If 'paused' is true, then the tree lock is not being held.
664 */
665typedef struct rbtdb_dbiterator {
666 dns_dbiterator_t common;
667 bool paused;
668 bool new_origin;
669 isc_rwlocktype_t tree_locked;
670 isc_result_t result;
671 dns_fixedname_t name;
672 dns_fixedname_t origin;
673 dns_rbtnodechain_t chain;
674 dns_rbtnodechain_t nsec3chain;
675 dns_rbtnodechain_t *current;
676 dns_rbtnode_t *node;
677 dns_rbtnode_t *deletions[DELETION_BATCH_MAX];
678 int delcnt;
679 bool nsec3only;
680 bool nonsec3;
681} rbtdb_dbiterator_t;
682
683
684#define IS_STUB(rbtdb) (((rbtdb)->common.attributes & DNS_DBATTR_STUB) != 0)
685#define IS_CACHE(rbtdb) (((rbtdb)->common.attributes & DNS_DBATTR_CACHE) != 0)
686
687static void free_rbtdb(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, bool log,
688 isc_event_t *event);
689static void overmem(dns_db_t *db, bool over);
690static void setnsec3parameters(dns_db_t *db, rbtdb_version_t *version);
691static void setownercase(rdatasetheader_t *header, const dns_name_t *name);
692
693static bool match_header_version(rbtdb_file_header_t *header);
694
695/* Pad to 32 bytes */
696static char FILE_VERSION[32] = "\0";
697
698/*%
699 * 'init_count' is used to initialize 'newheader->count' which inturn
700 * is used to determine where in the cycle rrset-order cyclic starts.
701 * We don't lock this as we don't care about simultaneous updates.
702 *
703 * Note:
704 * Both init_count and header->count can be UINT32_MAX.
705 * The count on the returned rdataset however can't be as
706 * that indicates that the database does not implement cyclic
707 * processing.
708 */
709static unsigned int init_count;
710
711/*
712 * Locking
713 *
714 * If a routine is going to lock more than one lock in this module, then
715 * the locking must be done in the following order:
716 *
717 * Tree Lock
718 *
719 * Node Lock (Only one from the set may be locked at one time by
720 * any caller)
721 *
722 * Database Lock
723 *
724 * Failure to follow this hierarchy can result in deadlock.
725 */
726
727/*
728 * Deleting Nodes
729 *
730 * For zone databases the node for the origin of the zone MUST NOT be deleted.
731 */
732
733/*
734 * Debugging routines
735 */
736#ifdef DEBUG
737static void
738hexdump(const char *desc, unsigned char *data, size_t size) {
739 char hexdump[BUFSIZ * 2 + 1];
740 isc_buffer_t b;
741 isc_region_t r;
742 isc_result_t result;
743 size_t bytes;
744
745 fprintf(stderr, "%s: ", desc);
746 do {
747 isc_buffer_init(&b, hexdump, sizeof(hexdump));
748 r.base = data;
749 r.length = bytes = (size > BUFSIZ) ? BUFSIZ : size;
750 result = isc_hex_totext(&r, 0, "", &b);
751 RUNTIME_CHECK(result == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
752 isc_buffer_putuint8(&b, 0);
753 fprintf(stderr, "%s", hexdump);
754 data += bytes;
755 size -= bytes;
756 } while (size > 0);
757 fprintf(stderr, "\n");
758}
759#endif

766static void
767attach(dns_db_t *source, dns_db_t **targetp) {
768 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)source;
769
770 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
771
772 isc_refcount_increment(&rbtdb->references);
773
774 *targetp = source;
775}

777static void
778free_rbtdb_callback(isc_task_t *task, isc_event_t *event) {
779 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = event->ev_arg;
780
781 UNUSED(task);
782
783 free_rbtdb(rbtdb, true, event);
784}
785
786static void
787update_cachestats(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, isc_result_t result) {
788 INSIST(IS_CACHE(rbtdb));
789
790 if (rbtdb->cachestats == NULL)
791 return;
792
793 switch (result) {
794 case ISC_R_SUCCESS:
795 case DNS_R_CNAME:
796 case DNS_R_DNAME:
797 case DNS_R_DELEGATION:
798 case DNS_R_NCACHENXDOMAIN:
799 case DNS_R_NCACHENXRRSET:
800 isc_stats_increment(rbtdb->cachestats,
801 dns_cachestatscounter_hits);
802 break;
803 default:
804 isc_stats_increment(rbtdb->cachestats,
805 dns_cachestatscounter_misses);
806 }
807}
808
809static void
810update_rrsetstats(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, rdatasetheader_t *header,
811 bool increment)
812{
813 dns_rdatastatstype_t statattributes = 0;
814 dns_rdatastatstype_t base = 0;
815 dns_rdatastatstype_t type;
816
817 /* At the moment we count statistics only for cache DB */
818 INSIST(IS_CACHE(rbtdb));
819
820 if (NEGATIVE(header)) {
821 if (NXDOMAIN(header))
822 statattributes = DNS_RDATASTATSTYPE_ATTR_NXDOMAIN;
823 else {
824 statattributes = DNS_RDATASTATSTYPE_ATTR_NXRRSET;
825 base = RBTDB_RDATATYPE_EXT(header->type);
826 }
827 } else
828 base = RBTDB_RDATATYPE_BASE(header->type);
829
830 if (STALE(header))
831 statattributes |= DNS_RDATASTATSTYPE_ATTR_STALE;
832
833 type = DNS_RDATASTATSTYPE_VALUE(base, statattributes);
834 if (increment)
835 dns_rdatasetstats_increment(rbtdb->rrsetstats, type);
836 else
837 dns_rdatasetstats_decrement(rbtdb->rrsetstats, type);
838}
839
840static void
841set_ttl(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, rdatasetheader_t *header, dns_ttl_t newttl) {
842 int idx;
843 isc_heap_t *heap;
844 dns_ttl_t oldttl;
845
846
847 if (!IS_CACHE(rbtdb)) {
848 header->rdh_ttl = newttl;
849 return;
850 }
851
852 oldttl = header->rdh_ttl;
853 header->rdh_ttl = newttl;
854
855 /*
856 * It's possible the rbtdb is not a cache. If this is the case,
857 * we will not have a heap, and we move on. If we do, though,
858 * we might need to adjust things.
859 */
860 if (header->heap_index == 0 || newttl == oldttl)
861 return;
862 idx = header->node->locknum;
863 if (rbtdb->heaps == NULL || rbtdb->heaps[idx] == NULL)
864 return;
865 heap = rbtdb->heaps[idx];
866
867 if (newttl < oldttl)
868 isc_heap_increased(heap, header->heap_index);
869 else
870 isc_heap_decreased(heap, header->heap_index);
871}
872
873/*%
874 * These functions allow the heap code to rank the priority of each
875 * element. It returns true if v1 happens "sooner" than v2.
876 */
877static bool
878ttl_sooner(void *v1, void *v2) {
879 rdatasetheader_t *h1 = v1;
880 rdatasetheader_t *h2 = v2;
881
882 return (h1->rdh_ttl < h2->rdh_ttl);
883}
884
885static bool
886resign_sooner(void *v1, void *v2) {
887 rdatasetheader_t *h1 = v1;
888 rdatasetheader_t *h2 = v2;
889
890 return (h1->resign < h2->resign ||
891 (h1->resign == h2->resign &&
892 h1->resign_lsb < h2->resign_lsb));
893}
894
895/*%
896 * This function sets the heap index into the header.
897 */
898static void
899set_index(void *what, unsigned int idx) {
900 rdatasetheader_t *h = what;
901
902 h->heap_index = idx;
903}
904
905/*%
906 * Work out how many nodes can be deleted in the time between two
907 * requests to the nameserver. Smooth the resulting number and use it
908 * as a estimate for the number of nodes to be deleted in the next
909 * iteration.
910 */
911static unsigned int
912adjust_quantum(unsigned int old, isc_time_t *start) {
913 unsigned int pps = dns_pps; /* packets per second */
914 unsigned int interval;
915 uint64_t usecs;
916 isc_time_t end;
917 unsigned int nodes;
918
919 if (pps < 100)
920 pps = 100;
921 isc_time_now(&end);
922
923 interval = 1000000 / pps; /* interval in usec */
924 if (interval == 0)
925 interval = 1;
926 usecs = isc_time_microdiff(&end, start);
927 if (usecs == 0) {
928 /*
929 * We were unable to measure the amount of time taken.
930 * Double the nodes deleted next time.
931 */
932 old *= 2;
933 if (old > 1000)
934 old = 1000;
935 return (old);
936 }
937 nodes = old * interval;
938 nodes /= (unsigned int)usecs;
939 if (nodes == 0)
940 nodes = 1;
941 else if (nodes > 1000)
942 nodes = 1000;
943
944 /* Smooth */
945 nodes = (nodes + old * 3) / 4;
946
947 if (nodes != old)
948 isc_log_write(dns_lctx, DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DATABASE,
949 DNS_LOGMODULE_CACHE, ISC_LOG_DEBUG(1),
950 "adjust_quantum: old=%d, new=%d", old, nodes);
951
952 return (nodes);
953}
954
955static void
956free_rbtdb(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, bool log, isc_event_t *event) {
957 unsigned int i;
958 isc_result_t result;
959 char buf[DNS_NAME_FORMATSIZE];
960 dns_rbt_t **treep;
961 isc_time_t start;
962 dns_dbonupdatelistener_t *listener, *listener_next;
963
964 if (IS_CACHE(rbtdb) && rbtdb->common.rdclass == dns_rdataclass_in)
965 overmem((dns_db_t *)rbtdb, (bool)-1);
966
967 REQUIRE(rbtdb->current_version != NULL || EMPTY(rbtdb->open_versions));
968 REQUIRE(rbtdb->future_version == NULL);
969
970 if (rbtdb->current_version != NULL) {
971
972 INSIST(isc_refcount_decrement(
973 &rbtdb->current_version->references)
974 == 1);
975
976 UNLINK(rbtdb->open_versions, rbtdb->current_version, link);
977 isc_rwlock_destroy(&rbtdb->current_version->glue_rwlock);
978 isc_refcount_destroy(&rbtdb->current_version->references);
979 isc_rwlock_destroy(&rbtdb->current_version->rwlock);
980 isc_mem_put(rbtdb->common.mctx, rbtdb->current_version,
981 sizeof(rbtdb_version_t));
982 }
983
984 /*
985 * We assume the number of remaining dead nodes is reasonably small;
986 * the overhead of unlinking all nodes here should be negligible.
987 */
988 for (i = 0; i < rbtdb->node_lock_count; i++) {
989 dns_rbtnode_t *node;
990
991 node = ISC_LIST_HEAD(rbtdb->deadnodes[i]);
992 while (node != NULL) {
993 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(rbtdb->deadnodes[i], node, deadlink);
994 node = ISC_LIST_HEAD(rbtdb->deadnodes[i]);
995 }
996 }
997
998 if (event == NULL)
999 rbtdb->quantum = (rbtdb->task != NULL) ? 100 : 0;
1000
1001 for (;;) {
1002 /*
1003 * pick the next tree to (start to) destroy
1004 */
1005 treep = &rbtdb->tree;
1006 if (*treep == NULL) {
1007 treep = &rbtdb->nsec;
1008 if (*treep == NULL) {
1009 treep = &rbtdb->nsec3;
1010 /*
1011 * we're finished after clear cutting
1012 */
1013 if (*treep == NULL)
1014 break;
1015 }
1016 }
1017
1018 isc_time_now(&start);
1019 result = dns_rbt_destroy2(treep, rbtdb->quantum);
1020 if (result == ISC_R_QUOTA) {
1021 INSIST(rbtdb->task != NULL);
1022 if (rbtdb->quantum != 0)
1023 rbtdb->quantum = adjust_quantum(rbtdb->quantum,
1024 &start);
1025 if (event == NULL)
1026 event = isc_event_allocate(rbtdb->common.mctx,
1027 NULL,
1028 DNS_EVENT_FREESTORAGE,
1029 free_rbtdb_callback,
1030 rbtdb,
1031 sizeof(isc_event_t));
1032 if (event == NULL)
1033 continue;
1034 isc_task_send(rbtdb->task, &event);
1035 return;
1036 }
1037 INSIST(result == ISC_R_SUCCESS && *treep == NULL);
1038 }
1039
1040 if (event != NULL)
1041 isc_event_free(&event);
1042 if (log) {
1043 if (dns_name_dynamic(&rbtdb->common.origin))
1044 dns_name_format(&rbtdb->common.origin, buf,
1045 sizeof(buf));
1046 else
1047 strlcpy(buf, "<UNKNOWN>", sizeof(buf));
1048 isc_log_write(dns_lctx, DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DATABASE,
1049 DNS_LOGMODULE_CACHE, ISC_LOG_DEBUG(1),
1050 "done free_rbtdb(%s)", buf);
1051 }
1052 if (dns_name_dynamic(&rbtdb->common.origin))
1053 dns_name_free(&rbtdb->common.origin, rbtdb->common.mctx);
1054 for (i = 0; i < rbtdb->node_lock_count; i++) {
1055 isc_refcount_destroy(&rbtdb->node_locks[i].references);
1056 NODE_DESTROYLOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[i].lock);
1057 }
1058
1059 /*
1060 * Clean up LRU / re-signing order lists.
1061 */
1062 if (rbtdb->rdatasets != NULL) {
1063 for (i = 0; i < rbtdb->node_lock_count; i++)
1064 INSIST(ISC_LIST_EMPTY(rbtdb->rdatasets[i]));
1065 isc_mem_put(rbtdb->common.mctx, rbtdb->rdatasets,
1066 rbtdb->node_lock_count *
1067 sizeof(rdatasetheaderlist_t));
1068 }
1069 /*
1070 * Clean up dead node buckets.
1071 */
1072 if (rbtdb->deadnodes != NULL) {
1073 for (i = 0; i < rbtdb->node_lock_count; i++)
1074 INSIST(ISC_LIST_EMPTY(rbtdb->deadnodes[i]));
1075 isc_mem_put(rbtdb->common.mctx, rbtdb->deadnodes,
1076 rbtdb->node_lock_count * sizeof(rbtnodelist_t));
1077 }
1078 /*
1079 * Clean up heap objects.
1080 */
1081 if (rbtdb->heaps != NULL) {
1082 for (i = 0; i < rbtdb->node_lock_count; i++)
1083 isc_heap_destroy(&rbtdb->heaps[i]);
1084 isc_mem_put(rbtdb->hmctx, rbtdb->heaps,
1085 rbtdb->node_lock_count * sizeof(isc_heap_t *));
1086 }
1087
1088 if (rbtdb->rrsetstats != NULL)
1089 dns_stats_detach(&rbtdb->rrsetstats);
1090 if (rbtdb->cachestats != NULL)
1091 isc_stats_detach(&rbtdb->cachestats);
1092 if (rbtdb->gluecachestats != NULL)
1093 isc_stats_detach(&rbtdb->gluecachestats);
1094
1095 isc_mem_put(rbtdb->common.mctx, rbtdb->node_locks,
1096 rbtdb->node_lock_count * sizeof(rbtdb_nodelock_t));
1097 isc_rwlock_destroy(&rbtdb->tree_lock);
1098 isc_refcount_destroy(&rbtdb->references);
1099 if (rbtdb->task != NULL)
1100 isc_task_detach(&rbtdb->task);
1101
1102 RBTDB_DESTROYLOCK(&rbtdb->lock);
1103 rbtdb->common.magic = 0;
1104 rbtdb->common.impmagic = 0;
1105 isc_mem_detach(&rbtdb->hmctx);
1106
1107 if (rbtdb->mmap_location != NULL)
1108 isc_file_munmap(rbtdb->mmap_location,
1109 (size_t) rbtdb->mmap_size);
1110
1111 for (listener = ISC_LIST_HEAD(rbtdb->common.update_listeners);
1112 listener != NULL;
1113 listener = listener_next)
1114 {
1115 listener_next = ISC_LIST_NEXT(listener, link);
1116 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(rbtdb->common.update_listeners, listener, link);
1117 isc_mem_put(rbtdb->common.mctx, listener,
1118 sizeof(dns_dbonupdatelistener_t));
1119 }
1120
1121 isc_mem_putanddetach(&rbtdb->common.mctx, rbtdb, sizeof(*rbtdb));
1122}
1123
1124static inline void
1125maybe_free_rbtdb(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb) {
1126 bool want_free = false;
1127 unsigned int i;
1128 unsigned int inactive = 0;
1129
1130 /* XXX check for open versions here */
1131
1132 if (rbtdb->soanode != NULL)
1133 dns_db_detachnode((dns_db_t *)rbtdb, &rbtdb->soanode);
1134 if (rbtdb->nsnode != NULL)
1135 dns_db_detachnode((dns_db_t *)rbtdb, &rbtdb->nsnode);
1136
1137 /*
1138 * The current version's glue table needs to be freed early
1139 * so the nodes are dereferenced before we check the active
1140 * node count below.
1141 */
1142 if (rbtdb->current_version != NULL) {
1143 free_gluetable(rbtdb->current_version);
1144 }
1145
1146 /*
1147 * Even though there are no external direct references, there still
1148 * may be nodes in use.
1149 */
1150 for (i = 0; i < rbtdb->node_lock_count; i++) {
1151 NODE_LOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[i].lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
1152 rbtdb->node_locks[i].exiting = true;
1153 NODE_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[i].lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
1154 if (isc_refcount_current(&rbtdb->node_locks[i].references) == 0)
1155 {
1156 inactive++;
1157 }
1158 }
1159
1160 if (inactive != 0) {
1161 RBTDB_LOCK(&rbtdb->lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
1162 rbtdb->active -= inactive;
1163 if (rbtdb->active == 0) {
1164 want_free = true;
1165 }
1166 RBTDB_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
1167 if (want_free) {
1168 char buf[DNS_NAME_FORMATSIZE];
1169 if (dns_name_dynamic(&rbtdb->common.origin)) {
1170 dns_name_format(&rbtdb->common.origin, buf,
1171 sizeof(buf));
1172 } else {
1173 strlcpy(buf, "<UNKNOWN>", sizeof(buf));
1174 }
1175 isc_log_write(dns_lctx, DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DATABASE,
1176 DNS_LOGMODULE_CACHE, ISC_LOG_DEBUG(1),
1177 "calling free_rbtdb(%s)", buf);
1178 free_rbtdb(rbtdb, true, NULL);
1179 }
1180 }
1181}
1182
1183static void
1184detach(dns_db_t **dbp) {
1185 REQUIRE(dbp != NULL && VALID_RBTDB((dns_rbtdb_t *)(*dbp)));
1186 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)(*dbp);
1187 *dbp = NULL;
1188
1189 if (isc_refcount_decrement(&rbtdb->references) == 1) {
1190 (void)isc_refcount_current(&rbtdb->references);
1191 maybe_free_rbtdb(rbtdb);
1192 }
1193}
1194
1195static void
1196currentversion(dns_db_t *db, dns_dbversion_t **versionp) {
1197 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
1198 rbtdb_version_t *version;
1199
1200 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
1201
1202 /* XXXOND: Is the lock needed here? */
1203 RBTDB_LOCK(&rbtdb->lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
1204 version = rbtdb->current_version;
1205 isc_refcount_increment(&version->references);
1206 RBTDB_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
1207
1208 *versionp = (dns_dbversion_t *)version;
1209}
1210
1211static inline rbtdb_version_t *
1212allocate_version(isc_mem_t *mctx, rbtdb_serial_t serial,
1213 unsigned int references, bool writer)
1214{
1215 isc_result_t result;
1216 rbtdb_version_t *version;
1217 size_t i;
1218
1219 version = isc_mem_get(mctx, sizeof(*version));
1220 if (version == NULL)
1221 return (NULL);
1222 version->serial = serial;
1223
1224 isc_refcount_init(&version->references, references);
1225
1226 result = isc_rwlock_init(&version->glue_rwlock, 0, 0);
1227 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1228 isc_refcount_destroy(&version->references);
1229 isc_mem_put(mctx, version, sizeof(*version));
1230 return (NULL);
1231 }
1232
1233 version->glue_table_size = RBTDB_GLUE_TABLE_INIT_SIZE;
1234 version->glue_table_nodecount = 0U;
1235 version->glue_table = (rbtdb_glue_table_node_t **)
1236 isc_mem_get(mctx, (version->glue_table_size *
1237 sizeof(*version->glue_table)));
1238 if (version->glue_table == NULL) {
1239 isc_rwlock_destroy(&version->glue_rwlock);
1240 isc_refcount_destroy(&version->references);
1241 isc_mem_put(mctx, version, sizeof(*version));
1242 return (NULL);
1243 }
1244
1245 version->writer = writer;
1246 version->commit_ok = false;
1247 ISC_LIST_INIT(version->changed_list);
1248 ISC_LIST_INIT(version->resigned_list);
1249 ISC_LINK_INIT(version, link);
1250
1251 for (i = 0; i < version->glue_table_size; i++)
1252 version->glue_table[i] = NULL;
1253
1254 return (version);
1255}
1256
1257static isc_result_t
1258newversion(dns_db_t *db, dns_dbversion_t **versionp) {
1259 isc_result_t result;
1260 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
1261 rbtdb_version_t *version;
1262
1263 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
1264 REQUIRE(versionp != NULL && *versionp == NULL);
1265 REQUIRE(rbtdb->future_version == NULL);
1266
1267 RBTDB_LOCK(&rbtdb->lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
1268 RUNTIME_CHECK(rbtdb->next_serial != 0); /* XXX Error? */
1269 version = allocate_version(rbtdb->common.mctx, rbtdb->next_serial, 1,
1270 true);
1271 if (version != NULL) {
1272 version->rbtdb = rbtdb;
1273 version->commit_ok = true;
1274 version->secure = rbtdb->current_version->secure;
1275 version->havensec3 = rbtdb->current_version->havensec3;
1276 if (version->havensec3) {
1277 version->flags = rbtdb->current_version->flags;
1278 version->iterations =
1279 rbtdb->current_version->iterations;
1280 version->hash = rbtdb->current_version->hash;
1281 version->salt_length =
1282 rbtdb->current_version->salt_length;
1283 memmove(version->salt, rbtdb->current_version->salt,
1284 version->salt_length);
1285 } else {
1286 version->flags = 0;
1287 version->iterations = 0;
1288 version->hash = 0;
1289 version->salt_length = 0;
1290 memset(version->salt, 0, sizeof(version->salt));
1291 }
1292 result = isc_rwlock_init(&version->rwlock, 0, 0);
1293 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1294 free_gluetable(version);
1295 isc_rwlock_destroy(&version->glue_rwlock);
1296 isc_refcount_destroy(&version->references);
1297 isc_mem_put(rbtdb->common.mctx, version,
1298 sizeof(*version));
1299 version = NULL;
1300 } else {
1301 RWLOCK(&rbtdb->current_version->rwlock,
1302 isc_rwlocktype_read);
1303 version->records = rbtdb->current_version->records;
1304 version->bytes = rbtdb->current_version->bytes;
1305 RWUNLOCK(&rbtdb->current_version->rwlock,
1306 isc_rwlocktype_read);
1307 rbtdb->next_serial++;
1308 rbtdb->future_version = version;
1309 }
1310 } else
1311 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
1312 RBTDB_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
1313
1314 if (version == NULL)
1315 return (result);
1316
1317 *versionp = version;
1318
1319 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1320}
1321
1322static void
1323attachversion(dns_db_t *db, dns_dbversion_t *source,
1324 dns_dbversion_t **targetp)
1325{
1326 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
1327 rbtdb_version_t *rbtversion = source;
1328
1329 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
1330 INSIST(rbtversion != NULL && rbtversion->rbtdb == rbtdb);
1331
1332 isc_refcount_increment(&rbtversion->references);
1333
1334 *targetp = rbtversion;
1335}
1336
1337static rbtdb_changed_t *
1338add_changed(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, rbtdb_version_t *version,
1339 dns_rbtnode_t *node)
1340{
1341 rbtdb_changed_t *changed;
1342
1343 /*
1344 * Caller must be holding the node lock if its reference must be
1345 * protected by the lock.
1346 */
1347
1348 changed = isc_mem_get(rbtdb->common.mctx, sizeof(*changed));
1349
1350 RBTDB_LOCK(&rbtdb->lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
1351
1352 REQUIRE(version->writer);
1353
1354 if (changed != NULL) {
1355 isc_refcount_increment(&node->references);
1356 changed->node = node;
1357 changed->dirty = false;
1358 ISC_LIST_INITANDAPPEND(version->changed_list, changed, link);
1359 } else
1360 version->commit_ok = false;
1361
1362 RBTDB_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
1363
1364 return (changed);
1365}
1366
1367static inline void
1368free_noqname(isc_mem_t *mctx, struct noqname **noqname) {
1369
1370 if (dns_name_dynamic(&(*noqname)->name))
1371 dns_name_free(&(*noqname)->name, mctx);
1372 if ((*noqname)->neg != NULL)
1373 isc_mem_put(mctx, (*noqname)->neg,
1374 dns_rdataslab_size((*noqname)->neg, 0));
1375 if ((*noqname)->negsig != NULL)
1376 isc_mem_put(mctx, (*noqname)->negsig,
1377 dns_rdataslab_size((*noqname)->negsig, 0));
1378 isc_mem_put(mctx, *noqname, sizeof(**noqname));
1379 *noqname = NULL;
1380}
1381
1382static inline void
1383init_rdataset(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, rdatasetheader_t *h) {
1384 ISC_LINK_INIT(h, link);
1385 h->heap_index = 0;
1386 h->is_mmapped = 0;
1387 h->next_is_relative = 0;
1388 h->node_is_relative = 0;
1389
1390#if TRACE_HEADER
1391 if (IS_CACHE(rbtdb) && rbtdb->common.rdclass == dns_rdataclass_in)
1392 fprintf(stderr, "initialized header: %p\n", h);
1393#else
1394 UNUSED(rbtdb);
1395#endif
1396}
1397
1398/*
1399 * Update the copied values of 'next' and 'node' if they are relative.
1400 */
1401static void
1402update_newheader(rdatasetheader_t *newh, rdatasetheader_t *old) {
1403 char *p;
1404
1405 if (old->next_is_relative) {
1406 p = (char *) old;
1407 p += (uintptr_t)old->next;
1408 newh->next = (rdatasetheader_t *)p;
1409 }
1410 if (old->node_is_relative) {
1411 p = (char *) old;
1412 p += (uintptr_t)old->node;
1413 newh->node = (dns_rbtnode_t *)p;
1414 }
1415 if (CASESET(old)) {
1416 uint16_t attr;
1417
1418 memmove(newh->upper, old->upper, sizeof(old->upper));
1419 attr = old->attributes & (RDATASET_ATTR_CASESET |
1420 RDATASET_ATTR_CASEFULLYLOWER);
1421 newh->attributes |= attr;
1422 }
1423}
1424
1425static inline rdatasetheader_t *
1426new_rdataset(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, isc_mem_t *mctx) {
1427 rdatasetheader_t *h;
1428
1429 h = isc_mem_get(mctx, sizeof(*h));
1430 if (h == NULL)
1431 return (NULL);
1432
1433#if TRACE_HEADER
1434 if (IS_CACHE(rbtdb) && rbtdb->common.rdclass == dns_rdataclass_in)
1435 fprintf(stderr, "allocated header: %p\n", h);
1436#endif
1437 memset(h->upper, 0xeb, sizeof(h->upper));
1438 init_rdataset(rbtdb, h);
1439 h->rdh_ttl = 0;
1440 return (h);
1441}
1442
1443static inline void
1444free_rdataset(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, isc_mem_t *mctx, rdatasetheader_t *rdataset) {
1445 unsigned int size;
1446 int idx;
1447
1448 if (EXISTS(rdataset) &&
1449 (rdataset->attributes & RDATASET_ATTR_STATCOUNT) != 0) {
1450 update_rrsetstats(rbtdb, rdataset, false);
1451 }
1452
1453 idx = rdataset->node->locknum;
1454 if (ISC_LINK_LINKED(rdataset, link)) {
1455 INSIST(IS_CACHE(rbtdb));
1456 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(rbtdb->rdatasets[idx], rdataset, link);
1457 }
1458
1459 if (rdataset->heap_index != 0)
1460 isc_heap_delete(rbtdb->heaps[idx], rdataset->heap_index);
1461 rdataset->heap_index = 0;
1462
1463 if (rdataset->noqname != NULL)
1464 free_noqname(mctx, &rdataset->noqname);
1465 if (rdataset->closest != NULL)
1466 free_noqname(mctx, &rdataset->closest);
1467
1468 if (NONEXISTENT(rdataset))
1469 size = sizeof(*rdataset);
1470 else
1471 size = dns_rdataslab_size((unsigned char *)rdataset,
1472 sizeof(*rdataset));
1473
1474 if (rdataset->is_mmapped == 1)
1475 return;
1476
1477 isc_mem_put(mctx, rdataset, size);
1478}
1479
1480static inline void
1481rollback_node(dns_rbtnode_t *node, rbtdb_serial_t serial) {
1482 rdatasetheader_t *header, *dcurrent;
1483 bool make_dirty = false;
1484
1485 /*
1486 * Caller must hold the node lock.
1487 */
1488
1489 /*
1490 * We set the IGNORE attribute on rdatasets with serial number
1491 * 'serial'. When the reference count goes to zero, these rdatasets
1492 * will be cleaned up; until that time, they will be ignored.
1493 */
1494 for (header = node->data; header != NULL; header = header->next) {
1495 if (header->serial == serial) {
1496 header->attributes |= RDATASET_ATTR_IGNORE;
1497 make_dirty = true;
1498 }
1499 for (dcurrent = header->down;
1500 dcurrent != NULL;
1501 dcurrent = dcurrent->down) {
1502 if (dcurrent->serial == serial) {
1503 dcurrent->attributes |= RDATASET_ATTR_IGNORE;
1504 make_dirty = true;
1505 }
1506 }
1507 }
1508 if (make_dirty)
1509 node->dirty = 1;
1510}
1511
1512static inline void
1513mark_header_ancient(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, rdatasetheader_t *header) {
1514
1515 /*
1516 * If we are already ancient there is nothing to do.
1517 */
1518 if (ANCIENT(header))
1519 return;
1520
1521 header->attributes |= RDATASET_ATTR_ANCIENT;
1522 header->node->dirty = 1;
1523
1524 /*
1525 * If we have not been counted then there is nothing to do.
1526 */
1527 if ((header->attributes & RDATASET_ATTR_STATCOUNT) == 0)
1528 return;
1529
1530 if (EXISTS(header))
1531 update_rrsetstats(rbtdb, header, true);
1532}
1533
1534static inline void
1535clean_stale_headers(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, isc_mem_t *mctx, rdatasetheader_t *top)
1536{
1537 rdatasetheader_t *d, *down_next;
1538
1539 for (d = top->down; d != NULL; d = down_next) {
1540 down_next = d->down;
1541 free_rdataset(rbtdb, mctx, d);
1542 }
1543 top->down = NULL;
1544}
1545
1546static inline void
1547clean_cache_node(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, dns_rbtnode_t *node) {
1548 rdatasetheader_t *current, *top_prev, *top_next;
1549 isc_mem_t *mctx = rbtdb->common.mctx;
1550
1551 /*
1552 * Caller must be holding the node lock.
1553 */
1554
1555 top_prev = NULL;
1556 for (current = node->data; current != NULL; current = top_next) {
1557 top_next = current->next;
1558 clean_stale_headers(rbtdb, mctx, current);
1559 /*
1560 * If current is nonexistent or stale, we can clean it up.
1561 */
1562 if (NONEXISTENT(current) || ANCIENT(current) ||
1563 (STALE(current) && ! KEEPSTALE(rbtdb))) {
1564 if (top_prev != NULL)
1565 top_prev->next = current->next;
1566 else
1567 node->data = current->next;
1568 free_rdataset(rbtdb, mctx, current);
1569 } else
1570 top_prev = current;
1571 }
1572 node->dirty = 0;
1573}
1574
1575static inline void
1576clean_zone_node(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, dns_rbtnode_t *node,
1577 rbtdb_serial_t least_serial)
1578{
1579 rdatasetheader_t *current, *dcurrent, *down_next, *dparent;
1580 rdatasetheader_t *top_prev, *top_next;
1581 isc_mem_t *mctx = rbtdb->common.mctx;
1582 bool still_dirty = false;
1583
1584 /*
1585 * Caller must be holding the node lock.
1586 */
1587 REQUIRE(least_serial != 0);
1588
1589 top_prev = NULL;
1590 for (current = node->data; current != NULL; current = top_next) {
1591 top_next = current->next;
1592
1593 /*
1594 * First, we clean up any instances of multiple rdatasets
1595 * with the same serial number, or that have the IGNORE
1596 * attribute.
1597 */
1598 dparent = current;
1599 for (dcurrent = current->down;
1600 dcurrent != NULL;
1601 dcurrent = down_next) {
1602 down_next = dcurrent->down;
1603 INSIST(dcurrent->serial <= dparent->serial);
1604 if (dcurrent->serial == dparent->serial ||
1605 IGNORE(dcurrent)) {
1606 if (down_next != NULL)
1607 down_next->next = dparent;
1608 dparent->down = down_next;
1609 free_rdataset(rbtdb, mctx, dcurrent);
1610 } else
1611 dparent = dcurrent;
1612 }
1613
1614 /*
1615 * We've now eliminated all IGNORE datasets with the possible
1616 * exception of current, which we now check.
1617 */
1618 if (IGNORE(current)) {
1619 down_next = current->down;
1620 if (down_next == NULL) {
1621 if (top_prev != NULL)
1622 top_prev->next = current->next;
1623 else
1624 node->data = current->next;
1625 free_rdataset(rbtdb, mctx, current);
1626 /*
1627 * current no longer exists, so we can
1628 * just continue with the loop.
1629 */
1630 continue;
1631 } else {
1632 /*
1633 * Pull up current->down, making it the new
1634 * current.
1635 */
1636 if (top_prev != NULL)
1637 top_prev->next = down_next;
1638 else
1639 node->data = down_next;
1640 down_next->next = top_next;
1641 free_rdataset(rbtdb, mctx, current);
1642 current = down_next;
1643 }
1644 }
1645
1646 /*
1647 * We now try to find the first down node less than the
1648 * least serial.
1649 */
1650 dparent = current;
1651 for (dcurrent = current->down;
1652 dcurrent != NULL;
1653 dcurrent = down_next) {
1654 down_next = dcurrent->down;
1655 if (dcurrent->serial < least_serial)
1656 break;
1657 dparent = dcurrent;
1658 }
1659
1660 /*
1661 * If there is a such an rdataset, delete it and any older
1662 * versions.
1663 */
1664 if (dcurrent != NULL) {
1665 do {
1666 down_next = dcurrent->down;
1667 INSIST(dcurrent->serial <= least_serial);
1668 free_rdataset(rbtdb, mctx, dcurrent);
1669 dcurrent = down_next;
1670 } while (dcurrent != NULL);
1671 dparent->down = NULL;
1672 }
1673
1674 /*
1675 * Note. The serial number of 'current' might be less than
1676 * least_serial too, but we cannot delete it because it is
1677 * the most recent version, unless it is a NONEXISTENT
1678 * rdataset.
1679 */
1680 if (current->down != NULL) {
1681 still_dirty = true;
1682 top_prev = current;
1683 } else {
1684 /*
1685 * If this is a NONEXISTENT rdataset, we can delete it.
1686 */
1687 if (NONEXISTENT(current)) {
1688 if (top_prev != NULL)
1689 top_prev->next = current->next;
1690 else
1691 node->data = current->next;
1692 free_rdataset(rbtdb, mctx, current);
1693 } else
1694 top_prev = current;
1695 }
1696 }
1697 if (!still_dirty)
1698 node->dirty = 0;
1699}
1700
1701static void
1702delete_node(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, dns_rbtnode_t *node) {
1703 dns_rbtnode_t *nsecnode;
1704 dns_fixedname_t fname;
1705 dns_name_t *name;
1706 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_UNEXPECTED;
1707
1708 INSIST(!ISC_LINK_LINKED(node, deadlink));
1709
1710 if (isc_log_wouldlog(dns_lctx, ISC_LOG_DEBUG(1))) {
1711 char printname[DNS_NAME_FORMATSIZE];
1712 isc_log_write(dns_lctx,
1713 DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DATABASE,
1714 DNS_LOGMODULE_CACHE,
1715 ISC_LOG_DEBUG(1),
1716 "delete_node(): %p %s (bucket %d)",
1717 node,
1718 dns_rbt_formatnodename(node,
1719 printname, sizeof(printname)),
1720 node->locknum);
1721 }
1722
1723 switch (node->nsec) {
1724 case DNS_RBT_NSEC_NORMAL:
1725 /*
1726 * Though this may be wasteful, it has to be done before
1727 * node is deleted.
1728 */
1729 name = dns_fixedname_initname(&fname);
1730 dns_rbt_fullnamefromnode(node, name);
1731
1732 result = dns_rbt_deletenode(rbtdb->tree, node, false);
1733 break;
1734 case DNS_RBT_NSEC_HAS_NSEC:
1735 name = dns_fixedname_initname(&fname);
1736 dns_rbt_fullnamefromnode(node, name);
1737 /*
1738 * Delete the corresponding node from the auxiliary NSEC
1739 * tree before deleting from the main tree.
1740 */
1741 nsecnode = NULL;
1742 result = dns_rbt_findnode(rbtdb->nsec, name, NULL, &nsecnode,
1743 NULL, DNS_RBTFIND_EMPTYDATA,
1744 NULL, NULL);
1745 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1746 isc_log_write(dns_lctx, DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DATABASE,
1747 DNS_LOGMODULE_CACHE, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
1748 "delete_node: "
1749 "dns_rbt_findnode(nsec): %s",
1750 isc_result_totext(result));
1751 } else {
1752 result = dns_rbt_deletenode(rbtdb->nsec, nsecnode,
1753 false);
1754 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1755 isc_log_write(dns_lctx,
1756 DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DATABASE,
1757 DNS_LOGMODULE_CACHE,
1758 ISC_LOG_WARNING,
1759 "delete_node(): "
1760 "dns_rbt_deletenode(nsecnode): %s",
1761 isc_result_totext(result));
1762 }
1763 }
1764 result = dns_rbt_deletenode(rbtdb->tree, node, false);
1765 break;
1766 case DNS_RBT_NSEC_NSEC:
1767 result = dns_rbt_deletenode(rbtdb->nsec, node, false);
1768 break;
1769 case DNS_RBT_NSEC_NSEC3:
1770 result = dns_rbt_deletenode(rbtdb->nsec3, node, false);
1771 break;
1772 }
1773 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1774 isc_log_write(dns_lctx,
1775 DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DATABASE,
1776 DNS_LOGMODULE_CACHE,
1777 ISC_LOG_WARNING,
1778 "delete_node(): "
1779 "dns_rbt_deletenode: %s",
1780 isc_result_totext(result));
1781 }
1782}
1783
1784/*
1785 * Caller must be holding the node lock.
1786 */
1787static inline void
1788new_reference(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, dns_rbtnode_t *node) {
1789 INSIST(!ISC_LINK_LINKED(node, deadlink));
1790 if (isc_refcount_increment(&node->references) == 0) {
1791 /* this is the first reference to the node */
1792 isc_refcount_increment0(&rbtdb->node_locks[node->locknum].references);
1793 }
1794}
1795
1796/*%
1797 * Clean up dead nodes. These are nodes which have no references, and
1798 * have no data. They are dead but we could not or chose not to delete
1799 * them when we deleted all the data at that node because we did not want
1800 * to wait for the tree write lock.
1801 *
1802 * The caller must hold a tree write lock and bucketnum'th node (write) lock.
1803 */
1804static void
1805cleanup_dead_nodes(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, int bucketnum) {
1806 dns_rbtnode_t *node;
1807 int count = 10; /* XXXJT: should be adjustable */
1808
1809 node = ISC_LIST_HEAD(rbtdb->deadnodes[bucketnum]);
1810 while (node != NULL && count > 0) {
1811 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(rbtdb->deadnodes[bucketnum], node, deadlink);
1812
1813 /*
1814 * Since we're holding a tree write lock, it should be
1815 * impossible for this node to be referenced by others.
1816 */
1817 INSIST(isc_refcount_current(&node->references) == 0 &&
1818 node->data == NULL);
1819
1820 if (node->parent != NULL &&
1821 node->parent->down == node && node->left == NULL &&
1822 node->right == NULL && rbtdb->task != NULL)
1823 {
1824 isc_event_t *ev;
1825 dns_db_t *db;
1826
1827 ev = isc_event_allocate(rbtdb->common.mctx, NULL,
1828 DNS_EVENT_RBTPRUNE,
1829 prune_tree, node,
1830 sizeof(isc_event_t));
1831 if (ev != NULL) {
1832 new_reference(rbtdb, node);
1833 db = NULL;
1834 attach((dns_db_t *)rbtdb, &db);
1835 ev->ev_sender = db;
1836 isc_task_send(rbtdb->task, &ev);
1837 } else {
1838 ISC_LIST_APPEND(rbtdb->deadnodes[bucketnum],
1839 node, deadlink);
1840 }
1841 } else {
1842 delete_node(rbtdb, node);
1843 }
1844 node = ISC_LIST_HEAD(rbtdb->deadnodes[bucketnum]);
1845 count--;
1846 }
1847}
1848
1849/*
1850 * This function is assumed to be called when a node is newly referenced
1851 * and can be in the deadnode list. In that case the node must be retrieved
1852 * from the list because it is going to be used. In addition, if the caller
1853 * happens to hold a write lock on the tree, it's a good chance to purge dead
1854 * nodes.
1855 * Note: while a new reference is gained in multiple places, there are only very
1856 * few cases where the node can be in the deadnode list (only empty nodes can
1857 * have been added to the list).
1858 */
1859static inline void
1860reactivate_node(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, dns_rbtnode_t *node,
1861 isc_rwlocktype_t treelocktype)
1862{
1863 isc_rwlocktype_t locktype = isc_rwlocktype_read;
1864 nodelock_t *nodelock = &rbtdb->node_locks[node->locknum].lock;
1865 bool maybe_cleanup = false;
1866
1867 POST(locktype);
1868
1869 NODE_LOCK(nodelock, locktype);
1870
1871 /*
1872 * Check if we can possibly cleanup the dead node. If so, upgrade
1873 * the node lock below to perform the cleanup.
1874 */
1875 if (!ISC_LIST_EMPTY(rbtdb->deadnodes[node->locknum]) &&
1876 treelocktype == isc_rwlocktype_write) {
1877 maybe_cleanup = true;
1878 }
1879
1880 if (ISC_LINK_LINKED(node, deadlink) || maybe_cleanup) {
1881 /*
1882 * Upgrade the lock and test if we still need to unlink.
1883 */
1884 NODE_UNLOCK(nodelock, locktype);
1885 locktype = isc_rwlocktype_write;
1886 POST(locktype);
1887 NODE_LOCK(nodelock, locktype);
1888 if (ISC_LINK_LINKED(node, deadlink))
1889 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(rbtdb->deadnodes[node->locknum],
1890 node, deadlink);
1891 if (maybe_cleanup)
1892 cleanup_dead_nodes(rbtdb, node->locknum);
1893 }
1894
1895 new_reference(rbtdb, node);
1896
1897 NODE_UNLOCK(nodelock, locktype);
1898}
1899
1900/*
1901 * Caller must be holding the node lock; either the "strong", read or write
1902 * lock. Note that the lock must be held even when node references are
1903 * atomically modified; in that case the decrement operation itself does not
1904 * have to be protected, but we must avoid a race condition where multiple
1905 * threads are decreasing the reference to zero simultaneously and at least
1906 * one of them is going to free the node.
1907 *
1908 * This function returns true if and only if the node reference decreases
1909 * to zero.
1910 *
1911 * NOTE: Decrementing the reference count of a node to zero does not mean it
1912 * will be immediately freed.
1913 */
1914static bool
1915decrement_reference(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, dns_rbtnode_t *node,
1916 rbtdb_serial_t least_serial,
1917 isc_rwlocktype_t nlock, isc_rwlocktype_t tlock,
1918 bool pruning)
1919{
1920 isc_result_t result;
1921 bool write_locked;
1922 rbtdb_nodelock_t *nodelock;
1923 int bucket = node->locknum;
1924 bool no_reference = true;
1925 uint_fast32_t refs;
1926
1927 nodelock = &rbtdb->node_locks[bucket];
1928
1929#define KEEP_NODE(n, r) \
1930 ((n)->data != NULL || (n)->down != NULL || \
1931 (n) == (r)->origin_node || (n) == (r)->nsec3_origin_node)
1932
1933 /* Handle easy and typical case first. */
1934 if (!node->dirty && KEEP_NODE(node, rbtdb)) {
1935 if (isc_refcount_decrement(&node->references) == 1) {
1936 refs = isc_refcount_decrement(&nodelock->references);
1937 INSIST(refs > 0);
1938 return (true);
1939 } else {
1940 return (false);
1941 }
1942 }
1943
1944 /* Upgrade the lock? */
1945 if (nlock == isc_rwlocktype_read) {
1946 NODE_UNLOCK(&nodelock->lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
1947 NODE_LOCK(&nodelock->lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
1948 }
1949
1950 if (isc_refcount_decrement(&node->references) > 1) {
1951 /* Restore the lock? */
1952 if (nlock == isc_rwlocktype_read)
1953 NODE_DOWNGRADE(&nodelock->lock);
1954 return (false);
1955 }
1956
1957 if (node->dirty) {
1958 if (IS_CACHE(rbtdb))
1959 clean_cache_node(rbtdb, node);
1960 else {
1961 if (least_serial == 0) {
1962 /*
1963 * Caller doesn't know the least serial.
1964 * Get it.
1965 */
1966 RBTDB_LOCK(&rbtdb->lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
1967 least_serial = rbtdb->least_serial;
1968 RBTDB_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->lock,
1969 isc_rwlocktype_read);
1970 }
1971 clean_zone_node(rbtdb, node, least_serial);
1972 }
1973 }
1974
1975 /*
1976 * Attempt to switch to a write lock on the tree. If this fails,
1977 * we will add this node to a linked list of nodes in this locking
1978 * bucket which we will free later.
1979 */
1980 if (tlock != isc_rwlocktype_write) {
1981 /*
1982 * Locking hierarchy notwithstanding, we don't need to free
1983 * the node lock before acquiring the tree write lock because
1984 * we only do a trylock.
1985 */
1986 if (tlock == isc_rwlocktype_read)
1987 result = isc_rwlock_tryupgrade(&rbtdb->tree_lock);
1988 else
1989 result = isc_rwlock_trylock(&rbtdb->tree_lock,
1990 isc_rwlocktype_write);
1991 RUNTIME_CHECK(result == ISC_R_SUCCESS ||
1992 result == ISC_R_LOCKBUSY);
1993
1994 write_locked = (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1995 } else
1996 write_locked = true;
1997
1998 refs = isc_refcount_decrement(&nodelock->references);
1999 INSIST(refs > 0);
2000
2001 if (KEEP_NODE(node, rbtdb))
2002 goto restore_locks;
2003
2004#undef KEEP_NODE
2005
2006 if (write_locked) {
2007 /*
2008 * We can now delete the node.
2009 */
2010
2011 /*
2012 * If this node is the only one in the level it's in, deleting
2013 * this node may recursively make its parent the only node in
2014 * the parent level; if so, and if no one is currently using
2015 * the parent node, this is almost the only opportunity to
2016 * clean it up. But the recursive cleanup is not that trivial
2017 * since the child and parent may be in different lock buckets,
2018 * which would cause a lock order reversal problem. To avoid
2019 * the trouble, we'll dispatch a separate event for batch
2020 * cleaning. We need to check whether we're deleting the node
2021 * as a result of pruning to avoid infinite dispatching.
2022 * Note: pruning happens only when a task has been set for the
2023 * rbtdb. If the user of the rbtdb chooses not to set a task,
2024 * it's their responsibility to purge stale leaves (e.g. by
2025 * periodic walk-through).
2026 */
2027 if (!pruning && node->parent != NULL &&
2028 node->parent->down == node && node->left == NULL &&
2029 node->right == NULL && rbtdb->task != NULL) {
2030 isc_event_t *ev;
2031 dns_db_t *db;
2032
2033 ev = isc_event_allocate(rbtdb->common.mctx, NULL,
2034 DNS_EVENT_RBTPRUNE,
2035 prune_tree, node,
2036 sizeof(isc_event_t));
2037 if (ev != NULL) {
2038 new_reference(rbtdb, node);
2039 db = NULL;
2040 attach((dns_db_t *)rbtdb, &db);
2041 ev->ev_sender = db;
2042 isc_task_send(rbtdb->task, &ev);
2043 no_reference = false;
2044 } else {
2045 /*
2046 * XXX: this is a weird situation. We could
2047 * ignore this error case, but then the stale
2048 * node will unlikely be purged except via a
2049 * rare condition such as manual cleanup. So
2050 * we queue it in the deadnodes list, hoping
2051 * the memory shortage is temporary and the node
2052 * will be deleted later.
2053 */
2054 isc_log_write(dns_lctx,
2055 DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DATABASE,
2056 DNS_LOGMODULE_CACHE,
2057 ISC_LOG_INFO,
2058 "decrement_reference: failed to "
2059 "allocate pruning event");
2060 INSIST(node->data == NULL);
2061 INSIST(!ISC_LINK_LINKED(node, deadlink));
2062 ISC_LIST_APPEND(rbtdb->deadnodes[bucket], node,
2063 deadlink);
2064 }
2065 } else {
2066 delete_node(rbtdb, node);
2067 }
2068 } else {
2069 INSIST(node->data == NULL);
2070 INSIST(!ISC_LINK_LINKED(node, deadlink));
2071 ISC_LIST_APPEND(rbtdb->deadnodes[bucket], node, deadlink);
2072 }
2073
2074 restore_locks:
2075 /* Restore the lock? */
2076 if (nlock == isc_rwlocktype_read)
2077 NODE_DOWNGRADE(&nodelock->lock);
2078
2079 /*
2080 * Relock a read lock, or unlock the write lock if no lock was held.
2081 */
2082 if (tlock == isc_rwlocktype_none)
2083 if (write_locked)
2084 RWUNLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
2085
2086 if (tlock == isc_rwlocktype_read)
2087 if (write_locked)
2088 isc_rwlock_downgrade(&rbtdb->tree_lock);
2089
2090 return (no_reference);
2091}
2092
2093/*
2094 * Prune the tree by recursively cleaning-up single leaves. In the worst
2095 * case, the number of iteration is the number of tree levels, which is at
2096 * most the maximum number of domain name labels, i.e, 127. In practice, this
2097 * should be much smaller (only a few times), and even the worst case would be
2098 * acceptable for a single event.
2099 */
2100static void
2101prune_tree(isc_task_t *task, isc_event_t *event) {
2102 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = event->ev_sender;
2103 dns_rbtnode_t *node = event->ev_arg;
2104 dns_rbtnode_t *parent;
2105 unsigned int locknum;
2106
2107 UNUSED(task);
2108
2109 isc_event_free(&event);
2110
2111 RWLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
2112 locknum = node->locknum;
2113 NODE_LOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[locknum].lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
2114 do {
2115 parent = node->parent;
2116 decrement_reference(rbtdb, node, 0, isc_rwlocktype_write,
2117 isc_rwlocktype_write, true);
2118
2119 if (parent != NULL && parent->down == NULL) {
2120 /*
2121 * node was the only down child of the parent and has
2122 * just been removed. We'll then need to examine the
2123 * parent. Keep the lock if possible; otherwise,
2124 * release the old lock and acquire one for the parent.
2125 */
2126 if (parent->locknum != locknum) {
2127 NODE_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[locknum].lock,
2128 isc_rwlocktype_write);
2129 locknum = parent->locknum;
2130 NODE_LOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[locknum].lock,
2131 isc_rwlocktype_write);
2132 }
2133
2134 /*
2135 * We need to gain a reference to the node before
2136 * decrementing it in the next iteration. In addition,
2137 * if the node is in the dead-nodes list, extract it
2138 * from the list beforehand as we do in
2139 * reactivate_node().
2140 */
2141 if (ISC_LINK_LINKED(parent, deadlink))
2142 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(rbtdb->deadnodes[locknum],
2143 parent, deadlink);
2144 new_reference(rbtdb, parent);
2145 } else
2146 parent = NULL;
2147
2148 node = parent;
2149 } while (node != NULL);
2150 NODE_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[locknum].lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
2151 RWUNLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
2152
2153 detach((dns_db_t **)(void *)&rbtdb);
2154}
2155
2156static inline void
2157make_least_version(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, rbtdb_version_t *version,
2158 rbtdb_changedlist_t *cleanup_list)
2159{
2160 /*
2161 * Caller must be holding the database lock.
2162 */
2163
2164 rbtdb->least_serial = version->serial;
2165 *cleanup_list = version->changed_list;
2166 ISC_LIST_INIT(version->changed_list);
2167}
2168
2169static inline void
2170cleanup_nondirty(rbtdb_version_t *version, rbtdb_changedlist_t *cleanup_list) {
2171 rbtdb_changed_t *changed, *next_changed;
2172
2173 /*
2174 * If the changed record is dirty, then
2175 * an update created multiple versions of
2176 * a given rdataset. We keep this list
2177 * until we're the least open version, at
2178 * which point it's safe to get rid of any
2179 * older versions.
2180 *
2181 * If the changed record isn't dirty, then
2182 * we don't need it anymore since we're
2183 * committing and not rolling back.
2184 *
2185 * The caller must be holding the database lock.
2186 */
2187 for (changed = HEAD(version->changed_list);
2188 changed != NULL;
2189 changed = next_changed) {
2190 next_changed = NEXT(changed, link);
2191 if (!changed->dirty) {
2192 UNLINK(version->changed_list,
2193 changed, link);
2194 APPEND(*cleanup_list,
2195 changed, link);
2196 }
2197 }
2198}
2199
2200static void
2201iszonesecure(dns_db_t *db, rbtdb_version_t *version, dns_dbnode_t *origin) {
2202 dns_rdataset_t keyset;
2203 dns_rdataset_t nsecset, signsecset;
2204 bool haszonekey = false;
2205 bool hasnsec = false;
2206 isc_result_t result;
2207
2208 dns_rdataset_init(&keyset);
2209 result = dns_db_findrdataset(db, origin, version, dns_rdatatype_dnskey,
2210 0, 0, &keyset, NULL);
2211 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2212 result = dns_rdataset_first(&keyset);
2213 while (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2214 dns_rdata_t keyrdata = DNS_RDATA_INIT;
2215 dns_rdataset_current(&keyset, &keyrdata);
2216 if (dns_zonekey_iszonekey(&keyrdata)) {
2217 haszonekey = true;
2218 break;
2219 }
2220 result = dns_rdataset_next(&keyset);
2221 }
2222 dns_rdataset_disassociate(&keyset);
2223 }
2224 if (!haszonekey) {
2225 version->secure = dns_db_insecure;
2226 version->havensec3 = false;
2227 return;
2228 }
2229
2230 dns_rdataset_init(&nsecset);
2231 dns_rdataset_init(&signsecset);
2232 result = dns_db_findrdataset(db, origin, version, dns_rdatatype_nsec,
2233 0, 0, &nsecset, &signsecset);
2234 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2235 if (dns_rdataset_isassociated(&signsecset)) {
2236 hasnsec = true;
2237 dns_rdataset_disassociate(&signsecset);
2238 }
2239 dns_rdataset_disassociate(&nsecset);
2240 }
2241
2242 setnsec3parameters(db, version);
2243
2244 /*
2245 * Do we have a valid NSEC/NSEC3 chain?
2246 */
2247 if (version->havensec3 || hasnsec)
2248 version->secure = dns_db_secure;
2249 else
2250 version->secure = dns_db_insecure;
2251}
2252
2253/*%<
2254 * Walk the origin node looking for NSEC3PARAM records.
2255 * Cache the nsec3 parameters.
2256 */
2257static void
2258setnsec3parameters(dns_db_t *db, rbtdb_version_t *version) {
2259 dns_rbtnode_t *node;
2260 dns_rdata_nsec3param_t nsec3param;
2261 dns_rdata_t rdata = DNS_RDATA_INIT;
2262 isc_region_t region;
2263 isc_result_t result;
2264 rdatasetheader_t *header, *header_next;
2265 unsigned char *raw; /* RDATASLAB */
2266 unsigned int count, length;
2267 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
2268
2269 RWLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
2270 version->havensec3 = false;
2271 node = rbtdb->origin_node;
2272 NODE_LOCK(&(rbtdb->node_locks[node->locknum].lock),
2273 isc_rwlocktype_read);
2274 for (header = node->data;
2275 header != NULL;
2276 header = header_next) {
2277 header_next = header->next;
2278 do {
2279 if (header->serial <= version->serial &&
2280 !IGNORE(header)) {
2281 if (NONEXISTENT(header))
2282 header = NULL;
2283 break;
2284 } else
2285 header = header->down;
2286 } while (header != NULL);
2287
2288 if (header != NULL &&
2289 (header->type == dns_rdatatype_nsec3param)) {
2290 /*
2291 * Find A NSEC3PARAM with a supported algorithm.
2292 */
2293 raw = (unsigned char *)header + sizeof(*header);
2294 count = raw[0] * 256 + raw[1]; /* count */
2295#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
2296 raw += count * 4 + 2;
2297#else
2298 raw += 2;
2299#endif
2300 while (count-- > 0U) {
2301 length = raw[0] * 256 + raw[1];
2302#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
2303 raw += 4;
2304#else
2305 raw += 2;
2306#endif
2307 region.base = raw;
2308 region.length = length;
2309 raw += length;
2310 dns_rdata_fromregion(&rdata,
2311 rbtdb->common.rdclass,
2312 dns_rdatatype_nsec3param,
2313 &region);
2314 result = dns_rdata_tostruct(&rdata,
2315 &nsec3param,
2316 NULL);
2317 INSIST(result == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
2318 dns_rdata_reset(&rdata);
2319
2320 if (nsec3param.hash != DNS_NSEC3_UNKNOWNALG &&
2321 !dns_nsec3_supportedhash(nsec3param.hash))
2322 continue;
2323
2324 if (nsec3param.flags != 0)
2325 continue;
2326
2327 memmove(version->salt, nsec3param.salt,
2328 nsec3param.salt_length);
2329 version->hash = nsec3param.hash;
2330 version->salt_length = nsec3param.salt_length;
2331 version->iterations = nsec3param.iterations;
2332 version->flags = nsec3param.flags;
2333 version->havensec3 = true;
2334 /*
2335 * Look for a better algorithm than the
2336 * unknown test algorithm.
2337 */
2338 if (nsec3param.hash != DNS_NSEC3_UNKNOWNALG)
2339 goto unlock;
2340 }
2341 }
2342 }
2343 unlock:
2344 NODE_UNLOCK(&(rbtdb->node_locks[node->locknum].lock),
2345 isc_rwlocktype_read);
2346 RWUNLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
2347}
2348
2349static void
2350cleanup_dead_nodes_callback(isc_task_t *task, isc_event_t *event) {
2351 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = event->ev_arg;
2352 bool again = false;
2353 unsigned int locknum;
2354
2355 RWLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
2356 for (locknum = 0; locknum < rbtdb->node_lock_count; locknum++) {
2357 NODE_LOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[locknum].lock,
2358 isc_rwlocktype_write);
2359 cleanup_dead_nodes(rbtdb, locknum);
2360 if (ISC_LIST_HEAD(rbtdb->deadnodes[locknum]) != NULL)
2361 again = true;
2362 NODE_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[locknum].lock,
2363 isc_rwlocktype_write);
2364 }
2365 RWUNLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
2366 if (again)
2367 isc_task_send(task, &event);
2368 else {
2369 isc_event_free(&event);
2370 if (isc_refcount_decrement(&rbtdb->references) == 1) {
2371 (void)isc_refcount_current(&rbtdb->references);
2372 maybe_free_rbtdb(rbtdb);
2373 }
2374 }
2375}
2376
2377static void
2378closeversion(dns_db_t *db, dns_dbversion_t **versionp, bool commit) {
2379 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
2380 rbtdb_version_t *version, *cleanup_version, *least_greater;
2381 bool rollback = false;
2382 rbtdb_changedlist_t cleanup_list;
2383 rdatasetheaderlist_t resigned_list;
2384 rbtdb_changed_t *changed, *next_changed;
2385 rbtdb_serial_t serial, least_serial;
2386 dns_rbtnode_t *rbtnode;
2387 rdatasetheader_t *header;
2388
2389 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
2390 version = (rbtdb_version_t *)*versionp;
2391 INSIST(version->rbtdb == rbtdb);
2392
2393 cleanup_version = NULL;
2394 ISC_LIST_INIT(cleanup_list);
2395 ISC_LIST_INIT(resigned_list);
2396
2397 if (isc_refcount_decrement(&version->references) > 1) {
2398 /* typical and easy case first */
2399 if (commit) {
2400 RBTDB_LOCK(&rbtdb->lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
2401 INSIST(!version->writer);
2402 RBTDB_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
2403 }
2404 goto end;
2405 }
2406
2407 /*
2408 * Update the zone's secure status in version before making
2409 * it the current version.
2410 */
2411 if (version->writer && commit && !IS_CACHE(rbtdb))
2412 iszonesecure(db, version, rbtdb->origin_node);
2413
2414 RBTDB_LOCK(&rbtdb->lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
2415 serial = version->serial;
2416 if (version->writer) {
2417 if (commit) {
2418 unsigned cur_ref;
2419 rbtdb_version_t *cur_version;
2420
2421 INSIST(version->commit_ok);
2422 INSIST(version == rbtdb->future_version);
2423 /*
2424 * The current version is going to be replaced.
2425 * Release the (likely last) reference to it from the
2426 * DB itself and unlink it from the open list.
2427 */
2428 cur_version = rbtdb->current_version;
2429 cur_ref = isc_refcount_decrement(&cur_version->references);
2430 if (cur_ref == 1) {
2431 (void)isc_refcount_current(&cur_version->references);
2432 if (cur_version->serial == rbtdb->least_serial)
2433 INSIST(EMPTY(cur_version->changed_list));
2434 UNLINK(rbtdb->open_versions,
2435 cur_version, link);
2436 }
2437 if (EMPTY(rbtdb->open_versions)) {
2438 /*
2439 * We're going to become the least open
2440 * version.
2441 */
2442 make_least_version(rbtdb, version,
2443 &cleanup_list);
2444 } else {
2445 /*
2446 * Some other open version is the
2447 * least version. We can't cleanup
2448 * records that were changed in this
2449 * version because the older versions
2450 * may still be in use by an open
2451 * version.
2452 *
2453 * We can, however, discard the
2454 * changed records for things that
2455 * we've added that didn't exist in
2456 * prior versions.
2457 */
2458 cleanup_nondirty(version, &cleanup_list);
2459 }
2460 /*
2461 * If the (soon to be former) current version
2462 * isn't being used by anyone, we can clean
2463 * it up.
2464 */
2465 if (cur_ref == 1) {
2466 cleanup_version = cur_version;
2467 APPENDLIST(version->changed_list,
2468 cleanup_version->changed_list,
2469 link);
2470 }
2471 /*
2472 * Become the current version.
2473 */
2474 version->writer = false;
2475 rbtdb->current_version = version;
2476 rbtdb->current_serial = version->serial;
2477 rbtdb->future_version = NULL;
2478
2479 /*
2480 * Keep the current version in the open list, and
2481 * gain a reference for the DB itself (see the DB
2482 * creation function below). This must be the only
2483 * case where we need to increment the counter from
2484 * zero and need to use isc_refcount_increment0().
2485 */
2486 INSIST(isc_refcount_increment0(&version->references) == 0);
2487 PREPEND(rbtdb->open_versions,
2488 rbtdb->current_version, link);
2489 resigned_list = version->resigned_list;
2490 ISC_LIST_INIT(version->resigned_list);
2491 } else {
2492 /*
2493 * We're rolling back this transaction.
2494 */
2495 cleanup_list = version->changed_list;
2496 ISC_LIST_INIT(version->changed_list);
2497 resigned_list = version->resigned_list;
2498 ISC_LIST_INIT(version->resigned_list);
2499 rollback = true;
2500 cleanup_version = version;
2501 rbtdb->future_version = NULL;
2502 }
2503 } else {
2504 if (version != rbtdb->current_version) {
2505 /*
2506 * There are no external or internal references
2507 * to this version and it can be cleaned up.
2508 */
2509 cleanup_version = version;
2510
2511 /*
2512 * Find the version with the least serial
2513 * number greater than ours.
2514 */
2515 least_greater = PREV(version, link);
2516 if (least_greater == NULL)
2517 least_greater = rbtdb->current_version;
2518
2519 INSIST(version->serial < least_greater->serial);
2520 /*
2521 * Is this the least open version?
2522 */
2523 if (version->serial == rbtdb->least_serial) {
2524 /*
2525 * Yes. Install the new least open
2526 * version.
2527 */
2528 make_least_version(rbtdb,
2529 least_greater,
2530 &cleanup_list);
2531 } else {
2532 /*
2533 * Add any unexecuted cleanups to
2534 * those of the least greater version.
2535 */
2536 APPENDLIST(least_greater->changed_list,
2537 version->changed_list,
2538 link);
2539 }
2540 } else if (version->serial == rbtdb->least_serial)
2541 INSIST(EMPTY(version->changed_list));
2542 UNLINK(rbtdb->open_versions, version, link);
2543 }
2544 least_serial = rbtdb->least_serial;
2545 RBTDB_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
2546
2547 if (cleanup_version != NULL) {
2548 INSIST(EMPTY(cleanup_version->changed_list));
2549 free_gluetable(cleanup_version);
2550 isc_rwlock_destroy(&cleanup_version->glue_rwlock);
2551 isc_rwlock_destroy(&cleanup_version->rwlock);
2552 isc_mem_put(rbtdb->common.mctx, cleanup_version,
2553 sizeof(*cleanup_version));
2554 }
2555
2556 /*
2557 * Commit/rollback re-signed headers.
2558 */
2559 for (header = HEAD(resigned_list);
2560 header != NULL;
2561 header = HEAD(resigned_list)) {
2562 nodelock_t *lock;
2563
2564 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(resigned_list, header, link);
2565
2566 lock = &rbtdb->node_locks[header->node->locknum].lock;
2567 NODE_LOCK(lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
2568 if (rollback && !IGNORE(header)) {
2569 isc_result_t result;
2570 result = resign_insert(rbtdb, header->node->locknum,
2571 header);
2572 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
2573 isc_log_write(dns_lctx,
2574 DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DATABASE,
2575 DNS_LOGMODULE_ZONE, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
2576 "Unable to reinsert header to "
2577 "re-signing heap: %s",
2578 dns_result_totext(result));
2579 }
2580 decrement_reference(rbtdb, header->node, least_serial,
2581 isc_rwlocktype_write, isc_rwlocktype_none,
2582 false);
2583 NODE_UNLOCK(lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
2584 }
2585
2586 if (!EMPTY(cleanup_list)) {
2587 isc_event_t *event = NULL;
2588 isc_rwlocktype_t tlock = isc_rwlocktype_none;
2589
2590 if (rbtdb->task != NULL)
2591 event = isc_event_allocate(rbtdb->common.mctx, NULL,
2592 DNS_EVENT_RBTDEADNODES,
2593 cleanup_dead_nodes_callback,
2594 rbtdb, sizeof(isc_event_t));
2595 if (event == NULL) {
2596 /*
2597 * We acquire a tree write lock here in order to make
2598 * sure that stale nodes will be removed in
2599 * decrement_reference(). If we didn't have the lock,
2600 * those nodes could miss the chance to be removed
2601 * until the server stops. The write lock is
2602 * expensive, but this event should be rare enough
2603 * to justify the cost.
2604 */
2605 RWLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
2606 tlock = isc_rwlocktype_write;
2607 }
2608
2609 for (changed = HEAD(cleanup_list);
2610 changed != NULL;
2611 changed = next_changed) {
2612 nodelock_t *lock;
2613
2614 next_changed = NEXT(changed, link);
2615 rbtnode = changed->node;
2616 lock = &rbtdb->node_locks[rbtnode->locknum].lock;
2617
2618 NODE_LOCK(lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
2619 /*
2620 * This is a good opportunity to purge any dead nodes,
2621 * so use it.
2622 */
2623 if (event == NULL)
2624 cleanup_dead_nodes(rbtdb, rbtnode->locknum);
2625
2626 if (rollback)
2627 rollback_node(rbtnode, serial);
2628 decrement_reference(rbtdb, rbtnode, least_serial,
2629 isc_rwlocktype_write, tlock,
2630 false);
2631
2632 NODE_UNLOCK(lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
2633
2634 isc_mem_put(rbtdb->common.mctx, changed,
2635 sizeof(*changed));
2636 }
2637 if (event != NULL) {
2638 isc_refcount_increment(&rbtdb->references);
2639 isc_task_send(rbtdb->task, &event);
2640 } else
2641 RWUNLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
2642 }
2643
2644 end:
2645 *versionp = NULL;
2646}
2647
2648/*
2649 * Add the necessary magic for the wildcard name 'name'
2650 * to be found in 'rbtdb'.
2651 *
2652 * In order for wildcard matching to work correctly in
2653 * zone_find(), we must ensure that a node for the wildcarding
2654 * level exists in the database, and has its 'find_callback'
2655 * and 'wild' bits set.
2656 *
2657 * E.g. if the wildcard name is "*.sub.example." then we
2658 * must ensure that "sub.example." exists and is marked as
2659 * a wildcard level.
2660 */
2661static isc_result_t
2662add_wildcard_magic(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, const dns_name_t *name) {
2663 isc_result_t result;
2664 dns_name_t foundname;
2665 dns_offsets_t offsets;
2666 unsigned int n;
2667 dns_rbtnode_t *node = NULL;
2668
2669 dns_name_init(&foundname, offsets);
2670 n = dns_name_countlabels(name);
2671 INSIST(n >= 2);
2672 n--;
2673 dns_name_getlabelsequence(name, 1, n, &foundname);
2674 result = dns_rbt_addnode(rbtdb->tree, &foundname, &node);
2675 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS && result != ISC_R_EXISTS)
2676 return (result);
2677 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
2678 node->nsec = DNS_RBT_NSEC_NORMAL;
2679 node->find_callback = 1;
2680 node->wild = 1;
2681 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
2682}
2683
2684static isc_result_t
2685add_empty_wildcards(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, const dns_name_t *name) {
2686 isc_result_t result;
2687 dns_name_t foundname;
2688 dns_offsets_t offsets;
2689 unsigned int n, l, i;
2690
2691 dns_name_init(&foundname, offsets);
2692 n = dns_name_countlabels(name);
2693 l = dns_name_countlabels(&rbtdb->common.origin);
2694 i = l + 1;
2695 while (i < n) {
2696 dns_rbtnode_t *node = NULL; /* dummy */
2697 dns_name_getlabelsequence(name, n - i, i, &foundname);
2698 if (dns_name_iswildcard(&foundname)) {
2699 result = add_wildcard_magic(rbtdb, &foundname);
2700 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
2701 return (result);
2702 result = dns_rbt_addnode(rbtdb->tree, &foundname,
2703 &node);
2704 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS && result != ISC_R_EXISTS)
2705 return (result);
2706 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
2707 node->nsec = DNS_RBT_NSEC_NORMAL;
2708 }
2709 i++;
2710 }
2711 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
2712}
2713
2714static isc_result_t
2715findnodeintree(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, dns_rbt_t *tree, const dns_name_t *name,
2716 bool create, dns_dbnode_t **nodep)
2717{
2718 dns_rbtnode_t *node = NULL;
2719 dns_name_t nodename;
2720 isc_result_t result;
2721 isc_rwlocktype_t locktype = isc_rwlocktype_read;
2722
2723 INSIST(tree == rbtdb->tree || tree == rbtdb->nsec3);
2724
2725 dns_name_init(&nodename, NULL);
2726 RWLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, locktype);
2727 result = dns_rbt_findnode(tree, name, NULL, &node, NULL,
2728 DNS_RBTFIND_EMPTYDATA, NULL, NULL);
2729 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2730 RWUNLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, locktype);
2731 if (!create) {
2732 if (result == DNS_R_PARTIALMATCH)
2733 result = ISC_R_NOTFOUND;
2734 return (result);
2735 }
2736 /*
2737 * It would be nice to try to upgrade the lock instead of
2738 * unlocking then relocking.
2739 */
2740 locktype = isc_rwlocktype_write;
2741 RWLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, locktype);
2742 node = NULL;
2743 result = dns_rbt_addnode(tree, name, &node);
2744 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2745 dns_rbt_namefromnode(node, &nodename);
2746 node->locknum = node->hashval % rbtdb->node_lock_count;
2747 if (tree == rbtdb->tree) {
2748 add_empty_wildcards(rbtdb, name);
2749
2750 if (dns_name_iswildcard(name)) {
2751 result = add_wildcard_magic(rbtdb,
2752 name);
2753 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2754 RWUNLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock,
2755 locktype);
2756 return (result);
2757 }
2758 }
2759 }
2760 if (tree == rbtdb->nsec3)
2761 node->nsec = DNS_RBT_NSEC_NSEC3;
2762 } else if (result != ISC_R_EXISTS) {
2763 RWUNLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, locktype);
2764 return (result);
2765 }
2766 }
2767
2768 if (tree == rbtdb->nsec3)
2769 INSIST(node->nsec == DNS_RBT_NSEC_NSEC3);
2770
2771 reactivate_node(rbtdb, node, locktype);
2772
2773 RWUNLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, locktype);
2774
2775 *nodep = (dns_dbnode_t *)node;
2776
2777 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
2778}
2779
2780static isc_result_t
2781findnode(dns_db_t *db, const dns_name_t *name, bool create,
2782 dns_dbnode_t **nodep)
2783{
2784 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
2785
2786 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
2787
2788 return (findnodeintree(rbtdb, rbtdb->tree, name, create, nodep));
2789}
2790
2791static isc_result_t
2792findnsec3node(dns_db_t *db, const dns_name_t *name, bool create,
2793 dns_dbnode_t **nodep)
2794{
2795 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
2796
2797 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
2798
2799 return (findnodeintree(rbtdb, rbtdb->nsec3, name, create, nodep));
2800}
2801
2802static isc_result_t
2803zone_zonecut_callback(dns_rbtnode_t *node, dns_name_t *name, void *arg) {
2804 rbtdb_search_t *search = arg;
2805 rdatasetheader_t *header, *header_next;
2806 rdatasetheader_t *dname_header, *sigdname_header, *ns_header;
2807 rdatasetheader_t *found;
2808 isc_result_t result;
2809 dns_rbtnode_t *onode;
2810
2811 /*
2812 * We only want to remember the topmost zone cut, since it's the one
2813 * that counts, so we'll just continue if we've already found a
2814 * zonecut.
2815 */
2816 if (search->zonecut != NULL)
2817 return (DNS_R_CONTINUE);
2818
2819 found = NULL;
2820 result = DNS_R_CONTINUE;
2821 onode = search->rbtdb->origin_node;
2822
2823 NODE_LOCK(&(search->rbtdb->node_locks[node->locknum].lock),
2824 isc_rwlocktype_read);
2825
2826 /*
2827 * Look for an NS or DNAME rdataset active in our version.
2828 */
2829 ns_header = NULL;
2830 dname_header = NULL;
2831 sigdname_header = NULL;
2832 for (header = node->data; header != NULL; header = header_next) {
2833 header_next = header->next;
2834 if (header->type == dns_rdatatype_ns ||
2835 header->type == dns_rdatatype_dname ||
2836 header->type == RBTDB_RDATATYPE_SIGDNAME) {
2837 do {
2838 if (header->serial <= search->serial &&
2839 !IGNORE(header)) {
2840 /*
2841 * Is this a "this rdataset doesn't
2842 * exist" record?
2843 */
2844 if (NONEXISTENT(header))
2845 header = NULL;
2846 break;
2847 } else
2848 header = header->down;
2849 } while (header != NULL);
2850 if (header != NULL) {
2851 if (header->type == dns_rdatatype_dname)
2852 dname_header = header;
2853 else if (header->type ==
2854 RBTDB_RDATATYPE_SIGDNAME)
2855 sigdname_header = header;
2856 else if (node != onode ||
2857 IS_STUB(search->rbtdb)) {
2858 /*
2859 * We've found an NS rdataset that
2860 * isn't at the origin node. We check
2861 * that they're not at the origin node,
2862 * because otherwise we'd erroneously
2863 * treat the zone top as if it were
2864 * a delegation.
2865 */
2866 ns_header = header;
2867 }
2868 }
2869 }
2870 }
2871
2872 /*
2873 * Did we find anything?
2874 */
2875 if (!IS_CACHE(search->rbtdb) && !IS_STUB(search->rbtdb) &&
2876 ns_header != NULL) {
2877 /*
2878 * Note that NS has precedence over DNAME if both exist
2879 * in a zone. Otherwise DNAME take precedence over NS.
2880 */
2881 found = ns_header;
2882 search->zonecut_sigrdataset = NULL;
2883 } else if (dname_header != NULL) {
2884 found = dname_header;
2885 search->zonecut_sigrdataset = sigdname_header;
2886 } else if (ns_header != NULL) {
2887 found = ns_header;
2888 search->zonecut_sigrdataset = NULL;
2889 }
2890
2891 if (found != NULL) {
2892 /*
2893 * We increment the reference count on node to ensure that
2894 * search->zonecut_rdataset will still be valid later.
2895 */
