2896 new_reference(search->rbtdb, node);
2897 search->zonecut = node;
2898 search->zonecut_rdataset = found;
2899 search->need_cleanup = true;
2900 /*
2901 * Since we've found a zonecut, anything beneath it is
2902 * glue and is not subject to wildcard matching, so we
2903 * may clear search->wild.
2904 */
2905 search->wild = false;
2906 if ((search->options & DNS_DBFIND_GLUEOK) == 0) {
2907 /*
2908 * If the caller does not want to find glue, then
2909 * this is the best answer and the search should
2910 * stop now.
2911 */
2912 result = DNS_R_PARTIALMATCH;
2913 } else {
2914 dns_name_t *zcname;
2915
2916 /*
2917 * The search will continue beneath the zone cut.
2918 * This may or may not be the best match. In case it
2919 * is, we need to remember the node name.
2920 */
2921 zcname = dns_fixedname_name(&search->zonecut_name);
2922 RUNTIME_CHECK(dns_name_copy(name, zcname, NULL) ==
2923 ISC_R_SUCCESS);
2924 search->copy_name = true;
2925 }
2926 } else {
2927 /*
2928 * There is no zonecut at this node which is active in this
2929 * version.
2930 *
2931 * If this is a "wild" node and the caller hasn't disabled
2932 * wildcard matching, remember that we've seen a wild node
2933 * in case we need to go searching for wildcard matches
2934 * later on.
2935 */
2936 if (node->wild && (search->options & DNS_DBFIND_NOWILD) == 0)
2937 search->wild = true;
2938 }
2939
2940 NODE_UNLOCK(&(search->rbtdb->node_locks[node->locknum].lock),
2941 isc_rwlocktype_read);
2942
2943 return (result);
2944}
2945
2946static inline void
2947bind_rdataset(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, dns_rbtnode_t *node,
2948 rdatasetheader_t *header, isc_stdtime_t now,
2949 dns_rdataset_t *rdataset)
2950{
2951 unsigned char *raw; /* RDATASLAB */
2952
2953 /*
2954 * Caller must be holding the node reader lock.
2955 * XXXJT: technically, we need a writer lock, since we'll increment
2956 * the header count below. However, since the actual counter value
2957 * doesn't matter, we prioritize performance here. (We may want to
2958 * use atomic increment when available).
2959 */
2960
2961 if (rdataset == NULL)
2962 return;
2963
2964 new_reference(rbtdb, node);
2965
2966 INSIST(rdataset->methods == NULL); /* We must be disassociated. */
2967
2968 rdataset->methods = &rdataset_methods;
2969 rdataset->rdclass = rbtdb->common.rdclass;
2970 rdataset->type = RBTDB_RDATATYPE_BASE(header->type);
2971 rdataset->covers = RBTDB_RDATATYPE_EXT(header->type);
2972 rdataset->ttl = header->rdh_ttl - now;
2973 rdataset->trust = header->trust;
2974 if (NEGATIVE(header))
2975 rdataset->attributes |= DNS_RDATASETATTR_NEGATIVE;
2976 if (NXDOMAIN(header))
2977 rdataset->attributes |= DNS_RDATASETATTR_NXDOMAIN;
2978 if (OPTOUT(header))
2979 rdataset->attributes |= DNS_RDATASETATTR_OPTOUT;
2980 if (PREFETCH(header))
2981 rdataset->attributes |= DNS_RDATASETATTR_PREFETCH;
2982 if (STALE(header)) {
2983 rdataset->attributes |= DNS_RDATASETATTR_STALE;
2984 rdataset->stale_ttl =
2985 (rbtdb->serve_stale_ttl + header->rdh_ttl) - now;
2986 rdataset->ttl = 0;
2987 }
2988 rdataset->private1 = rbtdb;
2989 rdataset->private2 = node;
2990 raw = (unsigned char *)header + sizeof(*header);
2991 rdataset->private3 = raw;
2992 rdataset->count = header->count++;
2993 if (rdataset->count == UINT32_MAX)
2994 rdataset->count = 0;
2995
2996 /*
2997 * Reset iterator state.
2998 */
2999 rdataset->privateuint4 = 0;
3000 rdataset->private5 = NULL;
3001
3002 /*
3003 * Add noqname proof.
3004 */
3005 rdataset->private6 = header->noqname;
3006 if (rdataset->private6 != NULL)
3007 rdataset->attributes |= DNS_RDATASETATTR_NOQNAME;
3008 rdataset->private7 = header->closest;
3009 if (rdataset->private7 != NULL)
3010 rdataset->attributes |= DNS_RDATASETATTR_CLOSEST;
3011
3012 /*
3013 * Copy out re-signing information.
3014 */
3015 if (RESIGN(header)) {
3016 rdataset->attributes |= DNS_RDATASETATTR_RESIGN;
3017 rdataset->resign = (header->resign << 1) | header->resign_lsb;
3018 } else
3019 rdataset->resign = 0;
3020}
3021
3022static inline isc_result_t
3023setup_delegation(rbtdb_search_t *search, dns_dbnode_t **nodep,
3024 dns_name_t *foundname, dns_rdataset_t *rdataset,
3025 dns_rdataset_t *sigrdataset)
3026{
3027 isc_result_t result;
3028 dns_name_t *zcname;
3029 rbtdb_rdatatype_t type;
3030 dns_rbtnode_t *node;
3031
3032 /*
3033 * The caller MUST NOT be holding any node locks.
3034 */
3035
3036 node = search->zonecut;
3037 type = search->zonecut_rdataset->type;
3038
3039 /*
3040 * If we have to set foundname, we do it before anything else.
3041 * If we were to set foundname after we had set nodep or bound the
3042 * rdataset, then we'd have to undo that work if dns_name_copy()
3043 * failed. By setting foundname first, there's nothing to undo if
3044 * we have trouble.
3045 */
3046 if (foundname != NULL && search->copy_name) {
3047 zcname = dns_fixedname_name(&search->zonecut_name);
3048 result = dns_name_copy(zcname, foundname, NULL);
3049 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3050 return (result);
3051 }
3052 if (nodep != NULL) {
3053 /*
3054 * Note that we don't have to increment the node's reference
3055 * count here because we're going to use the reference we
3056 * already have in the search block.
3057 */
3058 *nodep = node;
3059 search->need_cleanup = false;
3060 }
3061 if (rdataset != NULL) {
3062 NODE_LOCK(&(search->rbtdb->node_locks[node->locknum].lock),
3063 isc_rwlocktype_read);
3064 bind_rdataset(search->rbtdb, node, search->zonecut_rdataset,
3065 search->now, rdataset);
3066 if (sigrdataset != NULL && search->zonecut_sigrdataset != NULL)
3067 bind_rdataset(search->rbtdb, node,
3068 search->zonecut_sigrdataset,
3069 search->now, sigrdataset);
3070 NODE_UNLOCK(&(search->rbtdb->node_locks[node->locknum].lock),
3071 isc_rwlocktype_read);
3072 }
3073
3074 if (type == dns_rdatatype_dname)
3075 return (DNS_R_DNAME);
3076 return (DNS_R_DELEGATION);
3077}
3078
3079static inline bool
3080valid_glue(rbtdb_search_t *search, dns_name_t *name, rbtdb_rdatatype_t type,
3081 dns_rbtnode_t *node)
3082{
3083 unsigned char *raw; /* RDATASLAB */
3084 unsigned int count, size;
3085 dns_name_t ns_name;
3086 bool valid = false;
3087 dns_offsets_t offsets;
3088 isc_region_t region;
3089 rdatasetheader_t *header;
3090
3091 /*
3092 * No additional locking is required.
3093 */
3094
3095 /*
3096 * Valid glue types are A, AAAA, A6. NS is also a valid glue type
3097 * if it occurs at a zone cut, but is not valid below it.
3098 */
3099 if (type == dns_rdatatype_ns) {
3100 if (node != search->zonecut) {
3101 return (false);
3102 }
3103 } else if (type != dns_rdatatype_a &&
3104 type != dns_rdatatype_aaaa &&
3105 type != dns_rdatatype_a6) {
3106 return (false);
3107 }
3108
3109 header = search->zonecut_rdataset;
3110 raw = (unsigned char *)header + sizeof(*header);
3111 count = raw[0] * 256 + raw[1];
3112#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
3113 raw += 2 + (4 * count);
3114#else
3115 raw += 2;
3116#endif
3117
3118 while (count > 0) {
3119 count--;
3120 size = raw[0] * 256 + raw[1];
3121#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
3122 raw += 4;
3123#else
3124 raw += 2;
3125#endif
3126 region.base = raw;
3127 region.length = size;
3128 raw += size;
3129 /*
3130 * XXX Until we have rdata structures, we have no choice but
3131 * to directly access the rdata format.
3132 */
3133 dns_name_init(&ns_name, offsets);
3134 dns_name_fromregion(&ns_name, &region);
3135 if (dns_name_compare(&ns_name, name) == 0) {
3136 valid = true;
3137 break;
3138 }
3139 }
3140
3141 return (valid);
3142}
3143
3144static inline bool
3145activeempty(rbtdb_search_t *search, dns_rbtnodechain_t *chain,
3146 const dns_name_t *name)
3147{
3148 dns_fixedname_t fnext;
3149 dns_fixedname_t forigin;
3150 dns_name_t *next;
3151 dns_name_t *origin;
3152 dns_name_t prefix;
3153 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb;
3154 dns_rbtnode_t *node;
3155 isc_result_t result;
3156 bool answer = false;
3157 rdatasetheader_t *header;
3158
3159 rbtdb = search->rbtdb;
3160
3161 dns_name_init(&prefix, NULL);
3162 next = dns_fixedname_initname(&fnext);
3163 origin = dns_fixedname_initname(&forigin);
3164
3165 result = dns_rbtnodechain_next(chain, NULL, NULL);
3166 while (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS || result == DNS_R_NEWORIGIN) {
3167 node = NULL;
3168 result = dns_rbtnodechain_current(chain, &prefix,
3169 origin, &node);
3170 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3171 break;
3172 NODE_LOCK(&(rbtdb->node_locks[node->locknum].lock),
3173 isc_rwlocktype_read);
3174 for (header = node->data;
3175 header != NULL;
3176 header = header->next) {
3177 if (header->serial <= search->serial &&
3178 !IGNORE(header) && EXISTS(header))
3179 break;
3180 }
3181 NODE_UNLOCK(&(rbtdb->node_locks[node->locknum].lock),
3182 isc_rwlocktype_read);
3183 if (header != NULL)
3184 break;
3185 result = dns_rbtnodechain_next(chain, NULL, NULL);
3186 }
3187 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3188 result = dns_name_concatenate(&prefix, origin, next, NULL);
3189 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS && dns_name_issubdomain(next, name))
3190 answer = true;
3191 return (answer);
3192}
3193
3194static inline bool
3195activeemtpynode(rbtdb_search_t *search, const dns_name_t *qname,
3196 dns_name_t *wname)
3197{
3198 dns_fixedname_t fnext;
3199 dns_fixedname_t forigin;
3200 dns_fixedname_t fprev;
3201 dns_name_t *next;
3202 dns_name_t *origin;
3203 dns_name_t *prev;
3204 dns_name_t name;
3205 dns_name_t rname;
3206 dns_name_t tname;
3207 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb;
3208 dns_rbtnode_t *node;
3209 dns_rbtnodechain_t chain;
3210 bool check_next = true;
3211 bool check_prev = true;
3212 bool answer = false;
3213 isc_result_t result;
3214 rdatasetheader_t *header;
3215 unsigned int n;
3216
3217 rbtdb = search->rbtdb;
3218
3219 dns_name_init(&name, NULL);
3220 dns_name_init(&tname, NULL);
3221 dns_name_init(&rname, NULL);
3222 next = dns_fixedname_initname(&fnext);
3223 prev = dns_fixedname_initname(&fprev);
3224 origin = dns_fixedname_initname(&forigin);
3225
3226 /*
3227 * Find if qname is at or below a empty node.
3228 * Use our own copy of the chain.
3229 */
3230
3231 chain = search->chain;
3232 do {
3233 node = NULL;
3234 result = dns_rbtnodechain_current(&chain, &name,
3235 origin, &node);
3236 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3237 break;
3238 NODE_LOCK(&(rbtdb->node_locks[node->locknum].lock),
3239 isc_rwlocktype_read);
3240 for (header = node->data;
3241 header != NULL;
3242 header = header->next) {
3243 if (header->serial <= search->serial &&
3244 !IGNORE(header) && EXISTS(header))
3245 break;
3246 }
3247 NODE_UNLOCK(&(rbtdb->node_locks[node->locknum].lock),
3248 isc_rwlocktype_read);
3249 if (header != NULL)
3250 break;
3251 result = dns_rbtnodechain_prev(&chain, NULL, NULL);
3252 } while (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS || result == DNS_R_NEWORIGIN);
3253 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3254 result = dns_name_concatenate(&name, origin, prev, NULL);
3255 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3256 check_prev = false;
3257
3258 result = dns_rbtnodechain_next(&chain, NULL, NULL);
3259 while (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS || result == DNS_R_NEWORIGIN) {
3260 node = NULL;
3261 result = dns_rbtnodechain_current(&chain, &name,
3262 origin, &node);
3263 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3264 break;
3265 NODE_LOCK(&(rbtdb->node_locks[node->locknum].lock),
3266 isc_rwlocktype_read);
3267 for (header = node->data;
3268 header != NULL;
3269 header = header->next) {
3270 if (header->serial <= search->serial &&
3271 !IGNORE(header) && EXISTS(header))
3272 break;
3273 }
3274 NODE_UNLOCK(&(rbtdb->node_locks[node->locknum].lock),
3275 isc_rwlocktype_read);
3276 if (header != NULL)
3277 break;
3278 result = dns_rbtnodechain_next(&chain, NULL, NULL);
3279 }
3280 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3281 result = dns_name_concatenate(&name, origin, next, NULL);
3282 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3283 check_next = false;
3284
3285 dns_name_clone(qname, &rname);
3286
3287 /*
3288 * Remove the wildcard label to find the terminal name.
3289 */
3290 n = dns_name_countlabels(wname);
3291 dns_name_getlabelsequence(wname, 1, n - 1, &tname);
3292
3293 do {
3294 if ((check_prev && dns_name_issubdomain(prev, &rname)) ||
3295 (check_next && dns_name_issubdomain(next, &rname))) {
3296 answer = true;
3297 break;
3298 }
3299 /*
3300 * Remove the left hand label.
3301 */
3302 n = dns_name_countlabels(&rname);
3303 dns_name_getlabelsequence(&rname, 1, n - 1, &rname);
3304 } while (!dns_name_equal(&rname, &tname));
3305 return (answer);
3306}
3307
3308static inline isc_result_t
3309find_wildcard(rbtdb_search_t *search, dns_rbtnode_t **nodep,
3310 const dns_name_t *qname)
3311{
3312 unsigned int i, j;
3313 dns_rbtnode_t *node, *level_node, *wnode;
3314 rdatasetheader_t *header;
3315 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_NOTFOUND;
3316 dns_name_t name;
3317 dns_name_t *wname;
3318 dns_fixedname_t fwname;
3319 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb;
3320 bool done, wild, active;
3321 dns_rbtnodechain_t wchain;
3322
3323 /*
3324 * Caller must be holding the tree lock and MUST NOT be holding
3325 * any node locks.
3326 */
3327
3328 /*
3329 * Examine each ancestor level. If the level's wild bit
3330 * is set, then construct the corresponding wildcard name and
3331 * search for it. If the wildcard node exists, and is active in
3332 * this version, we're done. If not, then we next check to see
3333 * if the ancestor is active in this version. If so, then there
3334 * can be no possible wildcard match and again we're done. If not,
3335 * continue the search.
3336 */
3337
3338 rbtdb = search->rbtdb;
3339 i = search->chain.level_matches;
3340 done = false;
3341 node = *nodep;
3342 do {
3343 NODE_LOCK(&(rbtdb->node_locks[node->locknum].lock),
3344 isc_rwlocktype_read);
3345
3346 /*
3347 * First we try to figure out if this node is active in
3348 * the search's version. We do this now, even though we
3349 * may not need the information, because it simplifies the
3350 * locking and code flow.
3351 */
3352 for (header = node->data;
3353 header != NULL;
3354 header = header->next) {
3355 if (header->serial <= search->serial &&
3356 !IGNORE(header) && EXISTS(header))
3357 break;
3358 }
3359 if (header != NULL)
3360 active = true;
3361 else
3362 active = false;
3363
3364 if (node->wild)
3365 wild = true;
3366 else
3367 wild = false;
3368
3369 NODE_UNLOCK(&(rbtdb->node_locks[node->locknum].lock),
3370 isc_rwlocktype_read);
3371
3372 if (wild) {
3373 /*
3374 * Construct the wildcard name for this level.
3375 */
3376 dns_name_init(&name, NULL);
3377 dns_rbt_namefromnode(node, &name);
3378 wname = dns_fixedname_initname(&fwname);
3379 result = dns_name_concatenate(dns_wildcardname, &name,
3380 wname, NULL);
3381 j = i;
3382 while (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS && j != 0) {
3383 j--;
3384 level_node = search->chain.levels[j];
3385 dns_name_init(&name, NULL);
3386 dns_rbt_namefromnode(level_node, &name);
3387 result = dns_name_concatenate(wname,
3388 &name,
3389 wname,
3390 NULL);
3391 }
3392 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3393 break;
3394
3395 wnode = NULL;
3396 dns_rbtnodechain_init(&wchain, NULL);
3397 result = dns_rbt_findnode(rbtdb->tree, wname,
3398 NULL, &wnode, &wchain,
3399 DNS_RBTFIND_EMPTYDATA,
3400 NULL, NULL);
3401 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
3402 nodelock_t *lock;
3403
3404 /*
3405 * We have found the wildcard node. If it
3406 * is active in the search's version, we're
3407 * done.
3408 */
3409 lock = &rbtdb->node_locks[wnode->locknum].lock;
3410 NODE_LOCK(lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
3411 for (header = wnode->data;
3412 header != NULL;
3413 header = header->next) {
3414 if (header->serial <= search->serial &&
3415 !IGNORE(header) && EXISTS(header))
3416 break;
3417 }
3418 NODE_UNLOCK(lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
3419 if (header != NULL ||
3420 activeempty(search, &wchain, wname)) {
3421 if (activeemtpynode(search, qname,
3422 wname)) {
3423 return (ISC_R_NOTFOUND);
3424 }
3425 /*
3426 * The wildcard node is active!
3427 *
3428 * Note: result is still ISC_R_SUCCESS
3429 * so we don't have to set it.
3430 */
3431 *nodep = wnode;
3432 break;
3433 }
3434 } else if (result != ISC_R_NOTFOUND &&
3435 result != DNS_R_PARTIALMATCH) {
3436 /*
3437 * An error has occurred. Bail out.
3438 */
3439 break;
3440 }
3441 }
3442
3443 if (active) {
3444 /*
3445 * The level node is active. Any wildcarding
3446 * present at higher levels has no
3447 * effect and we're done.
3448 */
3449 result = ISC_R_NOTFOUND;
3450 break;
3451 }
3452
3453 if (i > 0) {
3454 i--;
3455 node = search->chain.levels[i];
3456 } else
3457 done = true;
3458 } while (!done);
3459
3460 return (result);
3461}
3462
3463static bool
3464matchparams(rdatasetheader_t *header, rbtdb_search_t *search)
3465{
3466 dns_rdata_t rdata = DNS_RDATA_INIT;
3467 dns_rdata_nsec3_t nsec3;
3468 unsigned char *raw; /* RDATASLAB */
3469 unsigned int rdlen, count;
3470 isc_region_t region;
3471 isc_result_t result;
3472
3473 REQUIRE(header->type == dns_rdatatype_nsec3);
3474
3475 raw = (unsigned char *)header + sizeof(*header);
3476 count = raw[0] * 256 + raw[1]; /* count */
3477#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
3478 raw += count * 4 + 2;
3479#else
3480 raw += 2;
3481#endif
3482 while (count-- > 0) {
3483 rdlen = raw[0] * 256 + raw[1];
3484#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
3485 raw += 4;
3486#else
3487 raw += 2;
3488#endif
3489 region.base = raw;
3490 region.length = rdlen;
3491 dns_rdata_fromregion(&rdata, search->rbtdb->common.rdclass,
3492 dns_rdatatype_nsec3, &region);
3493 raw += rdlen;
3494 result = dns_rdata_tostruct(&rdata, &nsec3, NULL);
3495 INSIST(result == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
3496 if (nsec3.hash == search->rbtversion->hash &&
3497 nsec3.iterations == search->rbtversion->iterations &&
3498 nsec3.salt_length == search->rbtversion->salt_length &&
3499 memcmp(nsec3.salt, search->rbtversion->salt,
3500 nsec3.salt_length) == 0)
3501 return (true);
3502 dns_rdata_reset(&rdata);
3503 }
3504 return (false);
3505}
3506
3507/*
3508 * Find node of the NSEC/NSEC3 record that is 'name'.
3509 */
3510static inline isc_result_t
3511previous_closest_nsec(dns_rdatatype_t type, rbtdb_search_t *search,
3512 dns_name_t *name, dns_name_t *origin,
3513 dns_rbtnode_t **nodep, dns_rbtnodechain_t *nsecchain,
3514 bool *firstp)
3515{
3516 dns_fixedname_t ftarget;
3517 dns_name_t *target;
3518 dns_rbtnode_t *nsecnode;
3519 isc_result_t result;
3520
3521 REQUIRE(nodep != NULL && *nodep == NULL);
3522
3523 if (type == dns_rdatatype_nsec3) {
3524 result = dns_rbtnodechain_prev(&search->chain, NULL, NULL);
3525 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS && result != DNS_R_NEWORIGIN)
3526 return (result);
3527 result = dns_rbtnodechain_current(&search->chain, name, origin,
3528 nodep);
3529 return (result);
3530 }
3531
3532 target = dns_fixedname_initname(&ftarget);
3533
3534 for (;;) {
3535 if (*firstp) {
3536 /*
3537 * Construct the name of the second node to check.
3538 * It is the first node sought in the NSEC tree.
3539 */
3540 *firstp = false;
3541 dns_rbtnodechain_init(nsecchain, NULL);
3542 result = dns_name_concatenate(name, origin,
3543 target, NULL);
3544 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3545 return (result);
3546 nsecnode = NULL;
3547 result = dns_rbt_findnode(search->rbtdb->nsec,
3548 target, NULL,
3549 &nsecnode, nsecchain,
3550 DNS_RBTFIND_NOOPTIONS,
3551 NULL, NULL);
3552 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
3553 /*
3554 * Since this was the first loop, finding the
3555 * name in the NSEC tree implies that the first
3556 * node checked in the main tree had an
3557 * unacceptable NSEC record.
3558 * Try the previous node in the NSEC tree.
3559 */
3560 result = dns_rbtnodechain_prev(nsecchain,
3561 name, origin);
3562 if (result == DNS_R_NEWORIGIN)
3563 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
3564 } else if (result == ISC_R_NOTFOUND ||
3565 result == DNS_R_PARTIALMATCH) {
3566 result = dns_rbtnodechain_current(nsecchain,
3567 name, origin, NULL);
3568 if (result == ISC_R_NOTFOUND)
3569 result = ISC_R_NOMORE;
3570 }
3571 } else {
3572 /*
3573 * This is a second or later trip through the auxiliary
3574 * tree for the name of a third or earlier NSEC node in
3575 * the main tree. Previous trips through the NSEC tree
3576 * must have found nodes in the main tree with NSEC
3577 * records. Perhaps they lacked signature records.
3578 */
3579 result = dns_rbtnodechain_prev(nsecchain, name, origin);
3580 if (result == DNS_R_NEWORIGIN)
3581 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
3582 }
3583 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3584 return (result);
3585
3586 /*
3587 * Construct the name to seek in the main tree.
3588 */
3589 result = dns_name_concatenate(name, origin, target, NULL);
3590 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3591 return (result);
3592
3593 *nodep = NULL;
3594 result = dns_rbt_findnode(search->rbtdb->tree, target, NULL,
3595 nodep, &search->chain,
3596 DNS_RBTFIND_NOOPTIONS, NULL, NULL);
3597 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3598 return (result);
3599
3600 /*
3601 * There should always be a node in the main tree with the
3602 * same name as the node in the auxiliary NSEC tree, except for
3603 * nodes in the auxiliary tree that are awaiting deletion.
3604 */
3605 if (result != DNS_R_PARTIALMATCH && result != ISC_R_NOTFOUND) {
3606 isc_log_write(dns_lctx, DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DATABASE,
3607 DNS_LOGMODULE_CACHE, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
3608 "previous_closest_nsec(): %s",
3609 isc_result_totext(result));
3610 return (DNS_R_BADDB);
3611 }
3612 }
3613}
3614
3615/*
3616 * Find the NSEC/NSEC3 which is or before the current point on the
3617 * search chain. For NSEC3 records only NSEC3 records that match the
3618 * current NSEC3PARAM record are considered.
3619 */
3620static inline isc_result_t
3621find_closest_nsec(rbtdb_search_t *search, dns_dbnode_t **nodep,
3622 dns_name_t *foundname, dns_rdataset_t *rdataset,
3623 dns_rdataset_t *sigrdataset, dns_rbt_t *tree,
3624 dns_db_secure_t secure)
3625{
3626 dns_rbtnode_t *node, *prevnode;
3627 rdatasetheader_t *header, *header_next, *found, *foundsig;
3628 dns_rbtnodechain_t nsecchain;
3629 bool empty_node;
3630 isc_result_t result;
3631 dns_fixedname_t fname, forigin;
3632 dns_name_t *name, *origin;
3633 dns_rdatatype_t type;
3634 rbtdb_rdatatype_t sigtype;
3635 bool wraps;
3636 bool first = true;
3637 bool need_sig = (secure == dns_db_secure);
3638
3639 if (tree == search->rbtdb->nsec3) {
3640 type = dns_rdatatype_nsec3;
3641 sigtype = RBTDB_RDATATYPE_SIGNSEC3;
3642 wraps = true;
3643 } else {
3644 type = dns_rdatatype_nsec;
3645 sigtype = RBTDB_RDATATYPE_SIGNSEC;
3646 wraps = false;
3647 }
3648
3649 /*
3650 * Use the auxiliary tree only starting with the second node in the
3651 * hope that the original node will be right much of the time.
3652 */
3653 name = dns_fixedname_initname(&fname);
3654 origin = dns_fixedname_initname(&forigin);
3655 again:
3656 node = NULL;
3657 prevnode = NULL;
3658 result = dns_rbtnodechain_current(&search->chain, name, origin, &node);
3659 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3660 return (result);
3661 do {
3662 NODE_LOCK(&(search->rbtdb->node_locks[node->locknum].lock),
3663 isc_rwlocktype_read);
3664 found = NULL;
3665 foundsig = NULL;
3666 empty_node = true;
3667 for (header = node->data;
3668 header != NULL;
3669 header = header_next) {
3670 header_next = header->next;
3671 /*
3672 * Look for an active, extant NSEC or RRSIG NSEC.
3673 */
3674 do {
3675 if (header->serial <= search->serial &&
3676 !IGNORE(header)) {
3677 /*
3678 * Is this a "this rdataset doesn't
3679 * exist" record?
3680 */
3681 if (NONEXISTENT(header))
3682 header = NULL;
3683 break;
3684 } else
3685 header = header->down;
3686 } while (header != NULL);
3687 if (header != NULL) {
3688 /*
3689 * We now know that there is at least one
3690 * active rdataset at this node.
3691 */
3692 empty_node = false;
3693 if (header->type == type) {
3694 found = header;
3695 if (foundsig != NULL)
3696 break;
3697 } else if (header->type == sigtype) {
3698 foundsig = header;
3699 if (found != NULL)
3700 break;
3701 }
3702 }
3703 }
3704 if (!empty_node) {
3705 if (found != NULL && search->rbtversion->havensec3 &&
3706 found->type == dns_rdatatype_nsec3 &&
3707 !matchparams(found, search)) {
3708 empty_node = true;
3709 found = NULL;
3710 foundsig = NULL;
3711 result = previous_closest_nsec(type, search,
3712 name, origin,
3713 &prevnode, NULL,
3714 NULL);
3715 } else if (found != NULL &&
3716 (foundsig != NULL || !need_sig)) {
3717 /*
3718 * We've found the right NSEC/NSEC3 record.
3719 *
3720 * Note: for this to really be the right
3721 * NSEC record, it's essential that the NSEC
3722 * records of any nodes obscured by a zone
3723 * cut have been removed; we assume this is
3724 * the case.
3725 */
3726 result = dns_name_concatenate(name, origin,
3727 foundname, NULL);
3728 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
3729 if (nodep != NULL) {
3730 new_reference(search->rbtdb,
3731 node);
3732 *nodep = node;
3733 }
3734 bind_rdataset(search->rbtdb, node,
3735 found, search->now,
3736 rdataset);
3737 if (foundsig != NULL)
3738 bind_rdataset(search->rbtdb,
3739 node,
3740 foundsig,
3741 search->now,
3742 sigrdataset);
3743 }
3744 } else if (found == NULL && foundsig == NULL) {
3745 /*
3746 * This node is active, but has no NSEC or
3747 * RRSIG NSEC. That means it's glue or
3748 * other obscured zone data that isn't
3749 * relevant for our search. Treat the
3750 * node as if it were empty and keep looking.
3751 */
3752 empty_node = true;
3753 result = previous_closest_nsec(type, search,
3754 name, origin,
3755 &prevnode,
3756 &nsecchain,
3757 &first);
3758 } else {
3759 /*
3760 * We found an active node, but either the
3761 * NSEC or the RRSIG NSEC is missing. This
3762 * shouldn't happen.
3763 */
3764 result = DNS_R_BADDB;
3765 }
3766 } else {
3767 /*
3768 * This node isn't active. We've got to keep
3769 * looking.
3770 */
3771 result = previous_closest_nsec(type, search,
3772 name, origin, &prevnode,
3773 &nsecchain, &first);
3774 }
3775 NODE_UNLOCK(&(search->rbtdb->node_locks[node->locknum].lock),
3776 isc_rwlocktype_read);
3777 node = prevnode;
3778 prevnode = NULL;
3779 } while (empty_node && result == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
3780
3781 if (!first)
3782 dns_rbtnodechain_invalidate(&nsecchain);
3783
3784 if (result == ISC_R_NOMORE && wraps) {
3785 result = dns_rbtnodechain_last(&search->chain, tree,
3786 NULL, NULL);
3787 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS || result == DNS_R_NEWORIGIN) {
3788 wraps = false;
3789 goto again;
3790 }
3791 }
3792
3793 /*
3794 * If the result is ISC_R_NOMORE, then we got to the beginning of
3795 * the database and didn't find a NSEC record. This shouldn't
3796 * happen.
3797 */
3798 if (result == ISC_R_NOMORE)
3799 result = DNS_R_BADDB;
3800
3801 return (result);
3802}
3803
3804static isc_result_t
3805zone_find(dns_db_t *db, const dns_name_t *name, dns_dbversion_t *version,
3806 dns_rdatatype_t type, unsigned int options, isc_stdtime_t now,
3807 dns_dbnode_t **nodep, dns_name_t *foundname,
3808 dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, dns_rdataset_t *sigrdataset)
3809{
3810 dns_rbtnode_t *node = NULL;
3811 isc_result_t result;
3812 rbtdb_search_t search;
3813 bool cname_ok = true;
3814 bool close_version = false;
3815 bool maybe_zonecut = false;
3816 bool at_zonecut = false;
3817 bool wild;
3818 bool empty_node;
3819 rdatasetheader_t *header, *header_next, *found, *nsecheader;
3820 rdatasetheader_t *foundsig, *cnamesig, *nsecsig;
3821 rbtdb_rdatatype_t sigtype;
3822 bool active;
3823 dns_rbtnodechain_t chain;
3824 nodelock_t *lock;
3825 dns_rbt_t *tree;
3826
3827 search.rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
3828
3829 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(search.rbtdb));
3830 INSIST(version == NULL ||
3831 ((rbtdb_version_t *)version)->rbtdb == (dns_rbtdb_t *)db);
3832
3833 /*
3834 * We don't care about 'now'.
3835 */
3836 UNUSED(now);
3837
3838 /*
3839 * If the caller didn't supply a version, attach to the current
3840 * version.
3841 */
3842 if (version == NULL) {
3843 currentversion(db, &version);
3844 close_version = true;
3845 }
3846
3847 search.rbtversion = version;
3848 search.serial = search.rbtversion->serial;
3849 search.options = options;
3850 search.copy_name = false;
3851 search.need_cleanup = false;
3852 search.wild = false;
3853 search.zonecut = NULL;
3854 dns_fixedname_init(&search.zonecut_name);
3855 dns_rbtnodechain_init(&search.chain, search.rbtdb->common.mctx);
3856 search.now = 0;
3857
3858 /*
3859 * 'wild' will be true iff. we've matched a wildcard.
3860 */
3861 wild = false;
3862
3863 RWLOCK(&search.rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
3864
3865 /*
3866 * Search down from the root of the tree. If, while going down, we
3867 * encounter a callback node, zone_zonecut_callback() will search the
3868 * rdatasets at the zone cut for active DNAME or NS rdatasets.
3869 */
3870 tree = (options & DNS_DBFIND_FORCENSEC3) != 0 ? search.rbtdb->nsec3 :
3871 search.rbtdb->tree;
3872 result = dns_rbt_findnode(tree, name, foundname, &node,
3873 &search.chain, DNS_RBTFIND_EMPTYDATA,
3874 zone_zonecut_callback, &search);
3875
3876 if (result == DNS_R_PARTIALMATCH) {
3877 partial_match:
3878 if (search.zonecut != NULL) {
3879 result = setup_delegation(&search, nodep, foundname,
3880 rdataset, sigrdataset);
3881 goto tree_exit;
3882 }
3883
3884 if (search.wild) {
3885 /*
3886 * At least one of the levels in the search chain
3887 * potentially has a wildcard. For each such level,
3888 * we must see if there's a matching wildcard active
3889 * in the current version.
3890 */
3891 result = find_wildcard(&search, &node, name);
3892 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
3893 result = dns_name_copy(name, foundname, NULL);
3894 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3895 goto tree_exit;
3896 wild = true;
3897 goto found;
3898 }
3899 else if (result != ISC_R_NOTFOUND)
3900 goto tree_exit;
3901 }
3902
3903 chain = search.chain;
3904 active = activeempty(&search, &chain, name);
3905
3906 /*
3907 * If we're here, then the name does not exist, is not
3908 * beneath a zonecut, and there's no matching wildcard.
3909 */
3910 if ((search.rbtversion->secure == dns_db_secure &&
3911 !search.rbtversion->havensec3) ||
3912 (search.options & DNS_DBFIND_FORCENSEC) != 0 ||
3913 (search.options & DNS_DBFIND_FORCENSEC3) != 0)
3914 {
3915 result = find_closest_nsec(&search, nodep, foundname,
3916 rdataset, sigrdataset, tree,
3917 search.rbtversion->secure);
3918 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3919 result = active ? DNS_R_EMPTYNAME :
3920 DNS_R_NXDOMAIN;
3921 } else
3922 result = active ? DNS_R_EMPTYNAME : DNS_R_NXDOMAIN;
3923 goto tree_exit;
3924 } else if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3925 goto tree_exit;
3926
3927 found:
3928 /*
3929 * We have found a node whose name is the desired name, or we
3930 * have matched a wildcard.
3931 */
3932
3933 if (search.zonecut != NULL) {
3934 /*
3935 * If we're beneath a zone cut, we don't want to look for
3936 * CNAMEs because they're not legitimate zone glue.
3937 */
3938 cname_ok = false;
3939 } else {
3940 /*
3941 * The node may be a zone cut itself. If it might be one,
3942 * make sure we check for it later.
3943 *
3944 * DS records live above the zone cut in ordinary zone so
3945 * we want to ignore any referral.
3946 *
3947 * Stub zones don't have anything "above" the delgation so
3948 * we always return a referral.
3949 */
3950 if (node->find_callback &&
3951 ((node != search.rbtdb->origin_node &&
3952 !dns_rdatatype_atparent(type)) ||
3953 IS_STUB(search.rbtdb)))
3954 maybe_zonecut = true;
3955 }
3956
3957 /*
3958 * Certain DNSSEC types are not subject to CNAME matching
3959 * (RFC4035, section 2.5 and RFC3007).
3960 *
3961 * We don't check for RRSIG, because we don't store RRSIG records
3962 * directly.
3963 */
3964 if (type == dns_rdatatype_key || type == dns_rdatatype_nsec)
3965 cname_ok = false;
3966
3967 /*
3968 * We now go looking for rdata...
3969 */
3970
3971 lock = &search.rbtdb->node_locks[node->locknum].lock;
3972 NODE_LOCK(lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
3973
3974 found = NULL;
3975 foundsig = NULL;
3976 sigtype = RBTDB_RDATATYPE_VALUE(dns_rdatatype_rrsig, type);
3977 nsecheader = NULL;
3978 nsecsig = NULL;
3979 cnamesig = NULL;
3980 empty_node = true;
3981 for (header = node->data; header != NULL; header = header_next) {
3982 header_next = header->next;
3983 /*
3984 * Look for an active, extant rdataset.
3985 */
3986 do {
3987 if (header->serial <= search.serial &&
3988 !IGNORE(header)) {
3989 /*
3990 * Is this a "this rdataset doesn't
3991 * exist" record?
3992 */
3993 if (NONEXISTENT(header))
3994 header = NULL;
3995 break;
3996 } else
3997 header = header->down;
3998 } while (header != NULL);
3999 if (header != NULL) {
4000 /*
4001 * We now know that there is at least one active
4002 * rdataset at this node.
4003 */
4004 empty_node = false;
4005
4006 /*
4007 * Do special zone cut handling, if requested.
4008 */
4009 if (maybe_zonecut &&
4010 header->type == dns_rdatatype_ns) {
4011 /*
4012 * We increment the reference count on node to
4013 * ensure that search->zonecut_rdataset will
4014 * still be valid later.
4015 */
4016 new_reference(search.rbtdb, node);
4017 search.zonecut = node;
4018 search.zonecut_rdataset = header;
4019 search.zonecut_sigrdataset = NULL;
4020 search.need_cleanup = true;
4021 maybe_zonecut = false;
4022 at_zonecut = true;
4023 /*
4024 * It is not clear if KEY should still be
4025 * allowed at the parent side of the zone
4026 * cut or not. It is needed for RFC3007
4027 * validated updates.
4028 */
4029 if ((search.options & DNS_DBFIND_GLUEOK) == 0
4030 && type != dns_rdatatype_nsec
4031 && type != dns_rdatatype_key) {
4032 /*
4033 * Glue is not OK, but any answer we
4034 * could return would be glue. Return
4035 * the delegation.
4036 */
4037 found = NULL;
4038 break;
4039 }
4040 if (found != NULL && foundsig != NULL)
4041 break;
4042 }
4043
4044
4045 /*
4046 * If the NSEC3 record doesn't match the chain
4047 * we are using behave as if it isn't here.
4048 */
4049 if (header->type == dns_rdatatype_nsec3 &&
4050 !matchparams(header, &search)) {
4051 NODE_UNLOCK(lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
4052 goto partial_match;
4053 }
4054 /*
4055 * If we found a type we were looking for,
4056 * remember it.
4057 */
4058 if (header->type == type ||
4059 type == dns_rdatatype_any ||
4060 (header->type == dns_rdatatype_cname &&
4061 cname_ok)) {
4062 /*
4063 * We've found the answer!
4064 */
4065 found = header;
4066 if (header->type == dns_rdatatype_cname &&
4067 cname_ok) {
4068 /*
4069 * We may be finding a CNAME instead
4070 * of the desired type.
4071 *
4072 * If we've already got the CNAME RRSIG,
4073 * use it, otherwise change sigtype
4074 * so that we find it.
4075 */
4076 if (cnamesig != NULL)
4077 foundsig = cnamesig;
4078 else
4079 sigtype =
4080 RBTDB_RDATATYPE_SIGCNAME;
4081 }
4082 /*
4083 * If we've got all we need, end the search.
4084 */
4085 if (!maybe_zonecut && foundsig != NULL)
4086 break;
4087 } else if (header->type == sigtype) {
4088 /*
4089 * We've found the RRSIG rdataset for our
4090 * target type. Remember it.
4091 */
4092 foundsig = header;
4093 /*
4094 * If we've got all we need, end the search.
4095 */
4096 if (!maybe_zonecut && found != NULL)
4097 break;
4098 } else if (header->type == dns_rdatatype_nsec &&
4099 !search.rbtversion->havensec3) {
4100 /*
4101 * Remember a NSEC rdataset even if we're
4102 * not specifically looking for it, because
4103 * we might need it later.
4104 */
4105 nsecheader = header;
4106 } else if (header->type == RBTDB_RDATATYPE_SIGNSEC &&
4107 !search.rbtversion->havensec3) {
4108 /*
4109 * If we need the NSEC rdataset, we'll also
4110 * need its signature.
4111 */
4112 nsecsig = header;
4113 } else if (cname_ok &&
4114 header->type == RBTDB_RDATATYPE_SIGCNAME) {
4115 /*
4116 * If we get a CNAME match, we'll also need
4117 * its signature.
4118 */
4119 cnamesig = header;
4120 }
4121 }
4122 }
4123
4124 if (empty_node) {
4125 /*
4126 * We have an exact match for the name, but there are no
4127 * active rdatasets in the desired version. That means that
4128 * this node doesn't exist in the desired version, and that
4129 * we really have a partial match.
4130 */
4131 if (!wild) {
4132 NODE_UNLOCK(lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
4133 goto partial_match;
4134 }
4135 }
4136
4137 /*
4138 * If we didn't find what we were looking for...
4139 */
4140 if (found == NULL) {
4141 if (search.zonecut != NULL) {
4142 /*
4143 * We were trying to find glue at a node beneath a
4144 * zone cut, but didn't.
4145 *
4146 * Return the delegation.
4147 */
4148 NODE_UNLOCK(lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
4149 result = setup_delegation(&search, nodep, foundname,
4150 rdataset, sigrdataset);
4151 goto tree_exit;
4152 }
4153 /*
4154 * The desired type doesn't exist.
4155 */
4156 result = DNS_R_NXRRSET;
4157 if (search.rbtversion->secure == dns_db_secure &&
4158 !search.rbtversion->havensec3 &&
4159 (nsecheader == NULL || nsecsig == NULL)) {
4160 /*
4161 * The zone is secure but there's no NSEC,
4162 * or the NSEC has no signature!
4163 */
4164 if (!wild) {
4165 result = DNS_R_BADDB;
4166 goto node_exit;
4167 }
4168
4169 NODE_UNLOCK(lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
4170 result = find_closest_nsec(&search, nodep, foundname,
4171 rdataset, sigrdataset,
4172 search.rbtdb->tree,
4173 search.rbtversion->secure);
4174 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
4175 result = DNS_R_EMPTYWILD;
4176 goto tree_exit;
4177 }
4178 if ((search.options & DNS_DBFIND_FORCENSEC) != 0 &&
4179 nsecheader == NULL)
4180 {
4181 /*
4182 * There's no NSEC record, and we were told
4183 * to find one.
4184 */
4185 result = DNS_R_BADDB;
4186 goto node_exit;
4187 }
4188 if (nodep != NULL) {
4189 new_reference(search.rbtdb, node);
4190 *nodep = node;
4191 }
4192 if ((search.rbtversion->secure == dns_db_secure &&
4193 !search.rbtversion->havensec3) ||
4194 (search.options & DNS_DBFIND_FORCENSEC) != 0)
4195 {
4196 bind_rdataset(search.rbtdb, node, nsecheader,
4197 0, rdataset);
4198 if (nsecsig != NULL)
4199 bind_rdataset(search.rbtdb, node,
4200 nsecsig, 0, sigrdataset);
4201 }
4202 if (wild)
4203 foundname->attributes |= DNS_NAMEATTR_WILDCARD;
4204 goto node_exit;
4205 }
4206
4207 /*
4208 * We found what we were looking for, or we found a CNAME.
4209 */
4210
4211 if (type != found->type &&
4212 type != dns_rdatatype_any &&
4213 found->type == dns_rdatatype_cname) {
4214 /*
4215 * We weren't doing an ANY query and we found a CNAME instead
4216 * of the type we were looking for, so we need to indicate
4217 * that result to the caller.
4218 */
4219 result = DNS_R_CNAME;
4220 } else if (search.zonecut != NULL) {
4221 /*
4222 * If we're beneath a zone cut, we must indicate that the
4223 * result is glue, unless we're actually at the zone cut
4224 * and the type is NSEC or KEY.
4225 */
4226 if (search.zonecut == node) {
4227 /*
4228 * It is not clear if KEY should still be
4229 * allowed at the parent side of the zone
4230 * cut or not. It is needed for RFC3007
4231 * validated updates.
4232 */
4233 if (type == dns_rdatatype_nsec ||
4234 type == dns_rdatatype_nsec3 ||
4235 type == dns_rdatatype_key)
4236 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
4237 else if (type == dns_rdatatype_any)
4238 result = DNS_R_ZONECUT;
4239 else
4240 result = DNS_R_GLUE;
4241 } else
4242 result = DNS_R_GLUE;
4243 /*
4244 * We might have found data that isn't glue, but was occluded
4245 * by a dynamic update. If the caller cares about this, they
4246 * will have told us to validate glue.
4247 *
4248 * XXX We should cache the glue validity state!
4249 */
4250 if (result == DNS_R_GLUE &&
4251 (search.options & DNS_DBFIND_VALIDATEGLUE) != 0 &&
4252 !valid_glue(&search, foundname, type, node)) {
4253 NODE_UNLOCK(lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
4254 result = setup_delegation(&search, nodep, foundname,
4255 rdataset, sigrdataset);
4256 goto tree_exit;
4257 }
4258 } else {
4259 /*
4260 * An ordinary successful query!
4261 */
4262 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
4263 }
4264
4265 if (nodep != NULL) {
4266 if (!at_zonecut)
4267 new_reference(search.rbtdb, node);
4268 else
4269 search.need_cleanup = false;
4270 *nodep = node;
4271 }
4272
4273 if (type != dns_rdatatype_any) {
4274 bind_rdataset(search.rbtdb, node, found, 0, rdataset);
4275 if (foundsig != NULL)
4276 bind_rdataset(search.rbtdb, node, foundsig, 0,
4277 sigrdataset);
4278 }
4279
4280 if (wild)
4281 foundname->attributes |= DNS_NAMEATTR_WILDCARD;
4282
4283 node_exit:
4284 NODE_UNLOCK(lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
4285
4286 tree_exit:
4287 RWUNLOCK(&search.rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
4288
4289 /*
4290 * If we found a zonecut but aren't going to use it, we have to
4291 * let go of it.
4292 */
4293 if (search.need_cleanup) {
4294 node = search.zonecut;
4295 INSIST(node != NULL);
4296 lock = &(search.rbtdb->node_locks[node->locknum].lock);
4297
4298 NODE_LOCK(lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
4299 decrement_reference(search.rbtdb, node, 0,
4300 isc_rwlocktype_read, isc_rwlocktype_none,
4301 false);
4302 NODE_UNLOCK(lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
4303 }
4304
4305 if (close_version)
4306 closeversion(db, &version, false);
4307
4308 dns_rbtnodechain_reset(&search.chain);
4309
4310 return (result);
4311}
4312
4313static isc_result_t
4314zone_findzonecut(dns_db_t *db, const dns_name_t *name, unsigned int options,
4315 isc_stdtime_t now, dns_dbnode_t **nodep,
4316 dns_name_t *foundname, dns_name_t *dcname,
4317 dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, dns_rdataset_t *sigrdataset)
4318{
4319 UNUSED(db);
4320 UNUSED(name);
4321 UNUSED(options);
4322 UNUSED(now);
4323 UNUSED(nodep);
4324 UNUSED(foundname);
4325 UNUSED(dcname);
4326 UNUSED(rdataset);
4327 UNUSED(sigrdataset);
4328
4329 FATAL_ERROR(__FILE__, __LINE__, "zone_findzonecut() called!");
4330
4331 /* NOTREACHED */
4332 return (ISC_R_NOTIMPLEMENTED);
4333}
4334
4335static bool
4336check_stale_header(dns_rbtnode_t *node, rdatasetheader_t *header,
4337 isc_rwlocktype_t *locktype, nodelock_t *lock,
4338 rbtdb_search_t *search, rdatasetheader_t **header_prev)
4339{
4340
4341 if (!ACTIVE(header, search->now)) {
4342 dns_ttl_t stale = header->rdh_ttl +
4343 search->rbtdb->serve_stale_ttl;
4344 /*
4345 * If this data is in the stale window keep it and if
4346 * DNS_DBFIND_STALEOK is not set we tell the caller to
4347 * skip this record.
4348 */
4349 if (KEEPSTALE(search->rbtdb) && stale > search->now) {
4350 header->attributes |= RDATASET_ATTR_STALE;
4351 *header_prev = header;
4352 return ((search->options & DNS_DBFIND_STALEOK) == 0);
4353 }
4354
4355 /*
4356 * This rdataset is stale. If no one else is using the
4357 * node, we can clean it up right now, otherwise we mark
4358 * it as stale, and the node as dirty, so it will get
4359 * cleaned up later.
4360 */
4361 if ((header->rdh_ttl < search->now - RBTDB_VIRTUAL) &&
4362 (*locktype == isc_rwlocktype_write ||
4363 NODE_TRYUPGRADE(lock) == ISC_R_SUCCESS))
4364 {
4365 /*
4366 * We update the node's status only when we can
4367 * get write access; otherwise, we leave others
4368 * to this work. Periodical cleaning will
4369 * eventually take the job as the last resort.
4370 * We won't downgrade the lock, since other
4371 * rdatasets are probably stale, too.
4372 */
4373 *locktype = isc_rwlocktype_write;
4374
4375 if (isc_refcount_current(&node->references) == 0) {
4376 isc_mem_t *mctx;
4377
4378 /*
4379 * header->down can be non-NULL if the
4380 * refcount has just decremented to 0
4381 * but decrement_reference() has not
4382 * performed clean_cache_node(), in
4383 * which case we need to purge the stale
4384 * headers first.
4385 */
4386 mctx = search->rbtdb->common.mctx;
4387 clean_stale_headers(search->rbtdb, mctx, header);
4388 if (*header_prev != NULL)
4389 (*header_prev)->next = header->next;
4390 else
4391 node->data = header->next;
4392 free_rdataset(search->rbtdb, mctx, header);
4393 } else {
4394 mark_header_ancient(search->rbtdb, header);
4395 *header_prev = header;
4396 }
4397 } else
4398 *header_prev = header;
4399 return (true);
4400 }
4401 return (false);
4402}
4403
4404static isc_result_t
4405cache_zonecut_callback(dns_rbtnode_t *node, dns_name_t *name, void *arg) {
4406 rbtdb_search_t *search = arg;
4407 rdatasetheader_t *header, *header_prev, *header_next;
4408 rdatasetheader_t *dname_header, *sigdname_header;
4409 isc_result_t result;
4410 nodelock_t *lock;
4411 isc_rwlocktype_t locktype;
4412
4413 /* XXX comment */
4414
4415 REQUIRE(search->zonecut == NULL);
4416
4417 /*
4418 * Keep compiler silent.
4419 */
4420 UNUSED(name);
4421
4422 lock = &(search->rbtdb->node_locks[node->locknum].lock);
4423 locktype = isc_rwlocktype_read;
4424 NODE_LOCK(lock, locktype);
4425
4426 /*
4427 * Look for a DNAME or RRSIG DNAME rdataset.
4428 */
4429 dname_header = NULL;
4430 sigdname_header = NULL;
4431 header_prev = NULL;
4432 for (header = node->data; header != NULL; header = header_next) {
4433 header_next = header->next;
4434 if (check_stale_header(node, header,
4435 &locktype, lock, search,
4436 &header_prev)) {
4437 /* Do nothing. */
4438 } else if (header->type == dns_rdatatype_dname &&
4439 EXISTS(header)) {
4440 dname_header = header;
4441 header_prev = header;
4442 } else if (header->type == RBTDB_RDATATYPE_SIGDNAME &&
4443 EXISTS(header)) {
4444 sigdname_header = header;
4445 header_prev = header;
4446 } else
4447 header_prev = header;
4448 }
4449
4450 if (dname_header != NULL &&
4451 (!DNS_TRUST_PENDING(dname_header->trust) ||
4452 (search->options & DNS_DBFIND_PENDINGOK) != 0)) {
4453 /*
4454 * We increment the reference count on node to ensure that
4455 * search->zonecut_rdataset will still be valid later.
4456 */
4457 new_reference(search->rbtdb, node);
4458 INSIST(!ISC_LINK_LINKED(node, deadlink));
4459 search->zonecut = node;
4460 search->zonecut_rdataset = dname_header;
4461 search->zonecut_sigrdataset = sigdname_header;
4462 search->need_cleanup = true;
4463 result = DNS_R_PARTIALMATCH;
4464 } else
4465 result = DNS_R_CONTINUE;
4466
4467 NODE_UNLOCK(lock, locktype);
4468
4469 return (result);
4470}
4471
4472static inline isc_result_t
4473find_deepest_zonecut(rbtdb_search_t *search, dns_rbtnode_t *node,
4474 dns_dbnode_t **nodep, dns_name_t *foundname,
4475 dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, dns_rdataset_t *sigrdataset)
4476{
4477 unsigned int i;
4478 dns_rbtnode_t *level_node;
4479 rdatasetheader_t *header, *header_prev, *header_next;
4480 rdatasetheader_t *found, *foundsig;
4481 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_NOTFOUND;
4482 dns_name_t name;
4483 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb;
4484 bool done;
4485 nodelock_t *lock;
4486 isc_rwlocktype_t locktype;
4487
4488 /*
4489 * Caller must be holding the tree lock.
4490 */
4491
4492 rbtdb = search->rbtdb;
4493 i = search->chain.level_matches;
4494 done = false;
4495 do {
4496 locktype = isc_rwlocktype_read;
4497 lock = &rbtdb->node_locks[node->locknum].lock;
4498 NODE_LOCK(lock, locktype);
4499
4500 /*
4501 * Look for NS and RRSIG NS rdatasets.
4502 */
4503 found = NULL;
4504 foundsig = NULL;
4505 header_prev = NULL;
4506 for (header = node->data; header != NULL; header = header_next) {
4507 header_next = header->next;
4508 if (check_stale_header(node, header,
4509 &locktype, lock, search,
4510 &header_prev)) {
4511 /* Do nothing. */
4512 } else if (EXISTS(header)) {
4513 /*
4514 * We've found an extant rdataset. See if
4515 * we're interested in it.
4516 */
4517 if (header->type == dns_rdatatype_ns) {
4518 found = header;
4519 if (foundsig != NULL)
4520 break;
4521 } else if (header->type ==
4522 RBTDB_RDATATYPE_SIGNS) {
4523 foundsig = header;
4524 if (found != NULL)
4525 break;
4526 }
4527 header_prev = header;
4528 } else
4529 header_prev = header;
4530 }
4531
4532 if (found != NULL) {
4533 /*
4534 * If we have to set foundname, we do it before
4535 * anything else. If we were to set foundname after
4536 * we had set nodep or bound the rdataset, then we'd
4537 * have to undo that work if dns_name_concatenate()
4538 * failed. By setting foundname first, there's
4539 * nothing to undo if we have trouble.
4540 */
4541 if (foundname != NULL) {
4542 dns_name_init(&name, NULL);
4543 dns_rbt_namefromnode(node, &name);
4544 result = dns_name_copy(&name, foundname, NULL);
4545 while (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS && i > 0) {
4546 i--;
4547 level_node = search->chain.levels[i];
4548 dns_name_init(&name, NULL);
4549 dns_rbt_namefromnode(level_node,
4550 &name);
4551 result =
4552 dns_name_concatenate(foundname,
4553 &name,
4554 foundname,
4555 NULL);
4556 }
4557 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
4558 *nodep = NULL;
4559 goto node_exit;
4560 }
4561 }
4562 result = DNS_R_DELEGATION;
4563 if (nodep != NULL) {
4564 new_reference(search->rbtdb, node);
4565 *nodep = node;
4566 }
4567 bind_rdataset(search->rbtdb, node, found, search->now,
4568 rdataset);
4569 if (foundsig != NULL)
4570 bind_rdataset(search->rbtdb, node, foundsig,
4571 search->now, sigrdataset);
4572 if (need_headerupdate(found, search->now) ||
4573 (foundsig != NULL &&
4574 need_headerupdate(foundsig, search->now))) {
4575 if (locktype != isc_rwlocktype_write) {
4576 NODE_UNLOCK(lock, locktype);
4577 NODE_LOCK(lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
4578 locktype = isc_rwlocktype_write;
4579 POST(locktype);
4580 }
4581 if (need_headerupdate(found, search->now))
4582 update_header(search->rbtdb, found,
4583 search->now);
4584 if (foundsig != NULL &&
4585 need_headerupdate(foundsig, search->now)) {
4586 update_header(search->rbtdb, foundsig,
4587 search->now);
4588 }
4589 }
4590 }
4591
4592 node_exit:
4593 NODE_UNLOCK(lock, locktype);
4594
4595 if (found == NULL && i > 0) {
4596 i--;
4597 node = search->chain.levels[i];
4598 } else
4599 done = true;
4600
4601 } while (!done);
4602
4603 return (result);
4604}
4605
4606static isc_result_t
4607find_coveringnsec(rbtdb_search_t *search, dns_dbnode_t **nodep,
4608 isc_stdtime_t now, dns_name_t *foundname,
4609 dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, dns_rdataset_t *sigrdataset)
4610{
4611 dns_rbtnode_t *node;
4612 rdatasetheader_t *header, *header_next, *header_prev;
4613 rdatasetheader_t *found, *foundsig;
4614 bool empty_node;
4615 isc_result_t result;
4616 dns_fixedname_t fname, forigin;
4617 dns_name_t *name, *origin;
4618 rbtdb_rdatatype_t matchtype, sigmatchtype;
4619 nodelock_t *lock;
4620 isc_rwlocktype_t locktype;
4621 dns_rbtnodechain_t chain;
4622
4623 chain = search->chain;
4624
4625 matchtype = RBTDB_RDATATYPE_VALUE(dns_rdatatype_nsec, 0);
4626 sigmatchtype = RBTDB_RDATATYPE_VALUE(dns_rdatatype_rrsig,
4627 dns_rdatatype_nsec);
4628
4629 do {
4630 node = NULL;
4631 name = dns_fixedname_initname(&fname);
4632 origin = dns_fixedname_initname(&forigin);
4633 result = dns_rbtnodechain_current(&chain, name, origin, &node);
4634 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
4635 return (result);
4636 locktype = isc_rwlocktype_read;
4637 lock = &(search->rbtdb->node_locks[node->locknum].lock);
4638 NODE_LOCK(lock, locktype);
4639 found = NULL;
4640 foundsig = NULL;
4641 empty_node = true;
4642 header_prev = NULL;
4643 for (header = node->data; header != NULL; header = header_next)
4644 {
4645 header_next = header->next;
4646 if (check_stale_header(node, header,
4647 &locktype, lock, search,
4648 &header_prev)) {
4649 continue;
4650 }
4651 if (NONEXISTENT(header) ||
4652 RBTDB_RDATATYPE_BASE(header->type) == 0) {
4653 header_prev = header;
4654 continue;
4655 }
4656 /*
4657 * Don't stop on provable noqname / RRSIG.
4658 */
4659 if (header->noqname == NULL &&
4660 RBTDB_RDATATYPE_BASE(header->type)
4661 != dns_rdatatype_rrsig)
4662 {
4663 empty_node = false;
4664 }
4665 if (header->type == matchtype)
4666 found = header;
4667 else if (header->type == sigmatchtype)
4668 foundsig = header;
4669 header_prev = header;
4670 }
4671 if (found != NULL) {
4672 result = dns_name_concatenate(name, origin,
4673 foundname, NULL);
4674 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
4675 goto unlock_node;
4676 bind_rdataset(search->rbtdb, node, found,
4677 now, rdataset);
4678 if (foundsig != NULL)
4679 bind_rdataset(search->rbtdb, node, foundsig,
4680 now, sigrdataset);
4681 new_reference(search->rbtdb, node);
4682 *nodep = node;
4683 result = DNS_R_COVERINGNSEC;
4684 } else if (!empty_node) {
4685 result = ISC_R_NOTFOUND;
4686 } else
4687 result = dns_rbtnodechain_prev(&chain, NULL, NULL);
4688 unlock_node:
4689 NODE_UNLOCK(lock, locktype);
4690 } while (empty_node && result == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
4691 return (result);
4692}
4693
4694static isc_result_t
4695cache_find(dns_db_t *db, const dns_name_t *name, dns_dbversion_t *version,
4696 dns_rdatatype_t type, unsigned int options, isc_stdtime_t now,
4697 dns_dbnode_t **nodep, dns_name_t *foundname,
4698 dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, dns_rdataset_t *sigrdataset)
4699{
4700 dns_rbtnode_t *node = NULL;
4701 isc_result_t result;
4702 rbtdb_search_t search;
4703 bool cname_ok = true;
4704 bool empty_node;
4705 nodelock_t *lock;
4706 isc_rwlocktype_t locktype;
4707 rdatasetheader_t *header, *header_prev, *header_next;
4708 rdatasetheader_t *found, *nsheader;
4709 rdatasetheader_t *foundsig, *nssig, *cnamesig;
4710 rdatasetheader_t *update, *updatesig;
4711 rdatasetheader_t *nsecheader, *nsecsig;
4712 rbtdb_rdatatype_t sigtype, negtype;
4713
4714 UNUSED(version);
4715
4716 search.rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
4717
4718 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(search.rbtdb));
4719 REQUIRE(version == NULL);
4720
4721 if (now == 0)
4722 isc_stdtime_get(&now);
4723
4724 search.rbtversion = NULL;
4725 search.serial = 1;
4726 search.options = options;
4727 search.copy_name = false;
4728 search.need_cleanup = false;
4729 search.wild = false;
4730 search.zonecut = NULL;
4731 dns_fixedname_init(&search.zonecut_name);
4732 dns_rbtnodechain_init(&search.chain, search.rbtdb->common.mctx);
4733 search.now = now;
4734 update = NULL;
4735 updatesig = NULL;
4736
4737 RWLOCK(&search.rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
4738
4739 /*
4740 * Search down from the root of the tree. If, while going down, we
4741 * encounter a callback node, cache_zonecut_callback() will search the
4742 * rdatasets at the zone cut for a DNAME rdataset.
4743 */
4744 result = dns_rbt_findnode(search.rbtdb->tree, name, foundname, &node,
4745 &search.chain, DNS_RBTFIND_EMPTYDATA,
4746 cache_zonecut_callback, &search);
4747
4748 if (result == DNS_R_PARTIALMATCH) {
4749 if ((search.options & DNS_DBFIND_COVERINGNSEC) != 0) {
4750 result = find_coveringnsec(&search, nodep, now,
4751 foundname, rdataset,
4752 sigrdataset);
4753 if (result == DNS_R_COVERINGNSEC)
4754 goto tree_exit;
4755 }
4756 if (search.zonecut != NULL) {
4757 result = setup_delegation(&search, nodep, foundname,
4758 rdataset, sigrdataset);
4759 goto tree_exit;
4760 } else {
4761 find_ns:
4762 result = find_deepest_zonecut(&search, node, nodep,
4763 foundname, rdataset,
4764 sigrdataset);
4765 goto tree_exit;
4766 }
4767 } else if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
4768 goto tree_exit;
4769
4770 /*
4771 * Certain DNSSEC types are not subject to CNAME matching
4772 * (RFC4035, section 2.5 and RFC3007).
4773 *
4774 * We don't check for RRSIG, because we don't store RRSIG records
4775 * directly.
4776 */
4777 if (type == dns_rdatatype_key || type == dns_rdatatype_nsec)
4778 cname_ok = false;
4779
4780 /*
4781 * We now go looking for rdata...
4782 */
4783
4784 lock = &(search.rbtdb->node_locks[node->locknum].lock);
4785 locktype = isc_rwlocktype_read;
4786 NODE_LOCK(lock, locktype);
4787
4788 found = NULL;
4789 foundsig = NULL;
4790 sigtype = RBTDB_RDATATYPE_VALUE(dns_rdatatype_rrsig, type);
4791 negtype = RBTDB_RDATATYPE_VALUE(0, type);
4792 nsheader = NULL;
4793 nsecheader = NULL;
4794 nssig = NULL;
4795 nsecsig = NULL;
4796 cnamesig = NULL;
4797 empty_node = true;
4798 header_prev = NULL;
4799 for (header = node->data; header != NULL; header = header_next) {
4800 header_next = header->next;
4801 if (check_stale_header(node, header,
4802 &locktype, lock, &search,
4803 &header_prev)) {
4804 /* Do nothing. */
4805 } else if (EXISTS(header) && !ANCIENT(header)) {
4806 /*
4807 * We now know that there is at least one active
4808 * non-stale rdataset at this node.
4809 */
4810 empty_node = false;
4811
4812 /*
4813 * If we found a type we were looking for, remember
4814 * it.
4815 */
4816 if (header->type == type ||
4817 (type == dns_rdatatype_any &&
4818 RBTDB_RDATATYPE_BASE(header->type) != 0) ||
4819 (cname_ok && header->type ==
4820 dns_rdatatype_cname)) {
4821 /*
4822 * We've found the answer.
4823 */
4824 found = header;
4825 if (header->type == dns_rdatatype_cname &&
4826 cname_ok &&
4827 cnamesig != NULL) {
4828 /*
4829 * If we've already got the
4830 * CNAME RRSIG, use it.
4831 */
4832 foundsig = cnamesig;
4833 }
4834 } else if (header->type == sigtype) {
4835 /*
4836 * We've found the RRSIG rdataset for our
4837 * target type. Remember it.
4838 */
4839 foundsig = header;
4840 } else if (header->type == RBTDB_RDATATYPE_NCACHEANY ||
4841 header->type == negtype) {
4842 /*
4843 * We've found a negative cache entry.
4844 */
4845 found = header;
4846 } else if (header->type == dns_rdatatype_ns) {
4847 /*
4848 * Remember a NS rdataset even if we're
4849 * not specifically looking for it, because
4850 * we might need it later.
4851 */
4852 nsheader = header;
4853 } else if (header->type == RBTDB_RDATATYPE_SIGNS) {
4854 /*
4855 * If we need the NS rdataset, we'll also
4856 * need its signature.
4857 */
4858 nssig = header;
4859 } else if (header->type == dns_rdatatype_nsec) {
4860 nsecheader = header;
4861 } else if (header->type == RBTDB_RDATATYPE_SIGNSEC) {
4862 nsecsig = header;
4863 } else if (cname_ok &&
4864 header->type == RBTDB_RDATATYPE_SIGCNAME) {
4865 /*
4866 * If we get a CNAME match, we'll also need
4867 * its signature.
4868 */
4869 cnamesig = header;
4870 }
4871 header_prev = header;
4872 } else
4873 header_prev = header;
4874 }
4875
4876 if (empty_node) {
4877 /*
4878 * We have an exact match for the name, but there are no
4879 * extant rdatasets. That means that this node doesn't
4880 * meaningfully exist, and that we really have a partial match.
4881 */
4882 NODE_UNLOCK(lock, locktype);
4883 goto find_ns;
4884 }
4885
4886 /*
4887 * If we didn't find what we were looking for...
4888 */
4889 if (found == NULL ||
4890 (DNS_TRUST_ADDITIONAL(found->trust) &&
4891 ((options & DNS_DBFIND_ADDITIONALOK) == 0)) ||
4892 (found->trust == dns_trust_glue &&
4893 ((options & DNS_DBFIND_GLUEOK) == 0)) ||
4894 (DNS_TRUST_PENDING(found->trust) &&
4895 ((options & DNS_DBFIND_PENDINGOK) == 0))) {
4896
4897 /*
4898 * Return covering NODATA NSEC record.
4899 */
4900 if ((search.options & DNS_DBFIND_COVERINGNSEC) != 0 &&
4901 nsecheader != NULL)
4902 {
4903 if (nodep != NULL) {
4904 new_reference(search.rbtdb, node);
4905 INSIST(!ISC_LINK_LINKED(node, deadlink));
4906 *nodep = node;
4907 }
4908 bind_rdataset(search.rbtdb, node, nsecheader,
4909 search.now, rdataset);
4910 if (need_headerupdate(nsecheader, search.now))
4911 update = nsecheader;
4912 if (nsecsig != NULL) {
4913 bind_rdataset(search.rbtdb, node, nsecsig,
4914 search.now, sigrdataset);
4915 if (need_headerupdate(nsecsig, search.now))
4916 updatesig = nsecsig;
4917 }
4918 result = DNS_R_COVERINGNSEC;
4919 goto node_exit;
4920 }
4921
4922 /*
4923 * If there is an NS rdataset at this node, then this is the
4924 * deepest zone cut.
4925 */
4926 if (nsheader != NULL) {
4927 if (nodep != NULL) {
4928 new_reference(search.rbtdb, node);
4929 INSIST(!ISC_LINK_LINKED(node, deadlink));
4930 *nodep = node;
4931 }
4932 bind_rdataset(search.rbtdb, node, nsheader, search.now,
4933 rdataset);
4934 if (need_headerupdate(nsheader, search.now))
4935 update = nsheader;
4936 if (nssig != NULL) {
4937 bind_rdataset(search.rbtdb, node, nssig,
4938 search.now, sigrdataset);
4939 if (need_headerupdate(nssig, search.now))
4940 updatesig = nssig;
4941 }
4942 result = DNS_R_DELEGATION;
4943 goto node_exit;
4944 }
4945
4946 /*
4947 * Go find the deepest zone cut.
4948 */
4949 NODE_UNLOCK(lock, locktype);
4950 goto find_ns;
4951 }
4952
4953 /*
4954 * We found what we were looking for, or we found a CNAME.
4955 */
4956
4957 if (nodep != NULL) {
4958 new_reference(search.rbtdb, node);
4959 INSIST(!ISC_LINK_LINKED(node, deadlink));
4960 *nodep = node;
4961 }
4962
4963 if (NEGATIVE(found)) {
4964 /*
4965 * We found a negative cache entry.
4966 */
4967 if (NXDOMAIN(found))
4968 result = DNS_R_NCACHENXDOMAIN;
4969 else
4970 result = DNS_R_NCACHENXRRSET;
4971 } else if (type != found->type &&
4972 type != dns_rdatatype_any &&
4973 found->type == dns_rdatatype_cname) {
4974 /*
4975 * We weren't doing an ANY query and we found a CNAME instead
4976 * of the type we were looking for, so we need to indicate
4977 * that result to the caller.
4978 */
4979 result = DNS_R_CNAME;
4980 } else {
4981 /*
4982 * An ordinary successful query!
4983 */
4984 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
4985 }
4986
4987 if (type != dns_rdatatype_any || result == DNS_R_NCACHENXDOMAIN ||
4988 result == DNS_R_NCACHENXRRSET) {
4989 bind_rdataset(search.rbtdb, node, found, search.now,
4990 rdataset);
4991 if (need_headerupdate(found, search.now))
4992 update = found;
4993 if (!NEGATIVE(found) && foundsig != NULL) {
4994 bind_rdataset(search.rbtdb, node, foundsig, search.now,
4995 sigrdataset);
4996 if (need_headerupdate(foundsig, search.now))
4997 updatesig = foundsig;
4998 }
4999 }
5000
5001 node_exit:
5002 if ((update != NULL || updatesig != NULL) &&
5003 locktype != isc_rwlocktype_write) {
5004 NODE_UNLOCK(lock, locktype);
5005 NODE_LOCK(lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
5006 locktype = isc_rwlocktype_write;
5007 POST(locktype);
5008 }
5009 if (update != NULL && need_headerupdate(update, search.now))
5010 update_header(search.rbtdb, update, search.now);
5011 if (updatesig != NULL && need_headerupdate(updatesig, search.now))
5012 update_header(search.rbtdb, updatesig, search.now);
5013
5014 NODE_UNLOCK(lock, locktype);
5015
5016 tree_exit:
5017 RWUNLOCK(&search.rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
5018
5019 /*
5020 * If we found a zonecut but aren't going to use it, we have to
5021 * let go of it.
5022 */
5023 if (search.need_cleanup) {
5024 node = search.zonecut;
5025 INSIST(node != NULL);
5026 lock = &(search.rbtdb->node_locks[node->locknum].lock);
5027
5028 NODE_LOCK(lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
5029 decrement_reference(search.rbtdb, node, 0,
5030 isc_rwlocktype_read, isc_rwlocktype_none,
5031 false);
5032 NODE_UNLOCK(lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
5033 }
5034
5035 dns_rbtnodechain_reset(&search.chain);
5036
5037 update_cachestats(search.rbtdb, result);
5038 return (result);
5039}
5040
5041static isc_result_t
5042cache_findzonecut(dns_db_t *db, const dns_name_t *name, unsigned int options,
5043 isc_stdtime_t now, dns_dbnode_t **nodep,
5044 dns_name_t *foundname, dns_name_t *dcname,
5045 dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, dns_rdataset_t *sigrdataset)
5046{
5047 dns_rbtnode_t *node = NULL;
5048 nodelock_t *lock;
5049 isc_result_t result;
5050 rbtdb_search_t search;
5051 rdatasetheader_t *header, *header_prev, *header_next;
5052 rdatasetheader_t *found, *foundsig;
5053 unsigned int rbtoptions = DNS_RBTFIND_EMPTYDATA;
5054 isc_rwlocktype_t locktype;
5055 bool dcnull = (dcname == NULL);
5056
5057 search.rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
5058
5059 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(search.rbtdb));
5060
5061 if (now == 0)
5062 isc_stdtime_get(&now);
5063
5064 search.rbtversion = NULL;
5065 search.serial = 1;
5066 search.options = options;
5067 search.copy_name = false;
5068 search.need_cleanup = false;
5069 search.wild = false;
5070 search.zonecut = NULL;
5071 dns_fixedname_init(&search.zonecut_name);
5072 dns_rbtnodechain_init(&search.chain, search.rbtdb->common.mctx);
5073 search.now = now;
5074
5075 if (dcnull) {
5076 dcname = foundname;
5077 }
5078
5079 if ((options & DNS_DBFIND_NOEXACT) != 0)
5080 rbtoptions |= DNS_RBTFIND_NOEXACT;
5081
5082 RWLOCK(&search.rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
5083
5084 /*
5085 * Search down from the root of the tree.
5086 */
5087 result = dns_rbt_findnode(search.rbtdb->tree, name, dcname, &node,
5088 &search.chain, rbtoptions, NULL, &search);
5089
5090 if (result == DNS_R_PARTIALMATCH) {
5091 result = find_deepest_zonecut(&search, node, nodep, foundname,
5092 rdataset, sigrdataset);
5093 goto tree_exit;
5094 } else if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
5095 goto tree_exit;
5096 } else if (!dcnull) {
5097 dns_name_copy(dcname, foundname, NULL);
5098 }
5099 /*
5100 * We now go looking for an NS rdataset at the node.
5101 */
5102
5103 lock = &(search.rbtdb->node_locks[node->locknum].lock);
5104 locktype = isc_rwlocktype_read;
5105 NODE_LOCK(lock, locktype);
5106
5107 found = NULL;
5108 foundsig = NULL;
5109 header_prev = NULL;
5110 for (header = node->data; header != NULL; header = header_next) {
5111 header_next = header->next;
5112 if (check_stale_header(node, header,
5113 &locktype, lock, &search,
5114 &header_prev)) {
5115 /* Do nothing. */
5116 } else if (EXISTS(header)) {
5117 /*
5118 * If we found a type we were looking for, remember
5119 * it.
5120 */
5121 if (header->type == dns_rdatatype_ns) {
5122 /*
5123 * Remember a NS rdataset even if we're
5124 * not specifically looking for it, because
5125 * we might need it later.
5126 */
5127 found = header;
5128 } else if (header->type == RBTDB_RDATATYPE_SIGNS) {
5129 /*
5130 * If we need the NS rdataset, we'll also
5131 * need its signature.
5132 */
5133 foundsig = header;
5134 }
5135 header_prev = header;
5136 } else
5137 header_prev = header;
5138 }
5139
5140 if (found == NULL) {
5141 /*
5142 * No NS records here.
5143 */
5144 NODE_UNLOCK(lock, locktype);
5145 result = find_deepest_zonecut(&search, node, nodep, foundname,
5146 rdataset, sigrdataset);
5147 goto tree_exit;
5148 }
5149
5150 if (nodep != NULL) {
5151 new_reference(search.rbtdb, node);
5152 INSIST(!ISC_LINK_LINKED(node, deadlink));
5153 *nodep = node;
5154 }
5155
5156 bind_rdataset(search.rbtdb, node, found, search.now, rdataset);
5157 if (foundsig != NULL)
5158 bind_rdataset(search.rbtdb, node, foundsig, search.now,
5159 sigrdataset);
5160
5161 if (need_headerupdate(found, search.now) ||
5162 (foundsig != NULL && need_headerupdate(foundsig, search.now))) {
5163 if (locktype != isc_rwlocktype_write) {
5164 NODE_UNLOCK(lock, locktype);
5165 NODE_LOCK(lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
5166 locktype = isc_rwlocktype_write;
5167 POST(locktype);
5168 }
5169 if (need_headerupdate(found, search.now))
5170 update_header(search.rbtdb, found, search.now);
5171 if (foundsig != NULL &&
5172 need_headerupdate(foundsig, search.now)) {
5173 update_header(search.rbtdb, foundsig, search.now);
5174 }
5175 }
5176
5177 NODE_UNLOCK(lock, locktype);
5178
5179 tree_exit:
5180 RWUNLOCK(&search.rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
5181
5182 INSIST(!search.need_cleanup);
5183
5184 dns_rbtnodechain_reset(&search.chain);
5185
5186 if (result == DNS_R_DELEGATION)
5187 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
5188
5189 return (result);
5190}
5191
5192static void
5193attachnode(dns_db_t *db, dns_dbnode_t *source, dns_dbnode_t **targetp) {
5194 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
5195 dns_rbtnode_t *node = (dns_rbtnode_t *)source;
5196
5197 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
5198 REQUIRE(targetp != NULL && *targetp == NULL);
5199
5200 isc_refcount_increment(&node->references);
5201
5202 *targetp = source;
5203}
5204
5205static void
5206detachnode(dns_db_t *db, dns_dbnode_t **targetp) {
5207 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
5208 dns_rbtnode_t *node;
5209 bool want_free = false;
5210 bool inactive = false;
5211 rbtdb_nodelock_t *nodelock;
5212
5213 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
5214 REQUIRE(targetp != NULL && *targetp != NULL);
5215
5216 node = (dns_rbtnode_t *)(*targetp);
5217 nodelock = &rbtdb->node_locks[node->locknum];
5218
5219 NODE_LOCK(&nodelock->lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
5220
5221 if (decrement_reference(rbtdb, node, 0, isc_rwlocktype_read,
5222 isc_rwlocktype_none, false)) {
5223 if (isc_refcount_current(&nodelock->references) == 0 &&
5224 nodelock->exiting) {
5225 inactive = true;
5226 }
5227 }
5228
5229 NODE_UNLOCK(&nodelock->lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
5230
5231 *targetp = NULL;
5232
5233 if (inactive) {
5234 RBTDB_LOCK(&rbtdb->lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
5235 rbtdb->active--;
5236 if (rbtdb->active == 0)
5237 want_free = true;
5238 RBTDB_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
5239 if (want_free) {
5240 char buf[DNS_NAME_FORMATSIZE];
5241 if (dns_name_dynamic(&rbtdb->common.origin))
5242 dns_name_format(&rbtdb->common.origin, buf,
5243 sizeof(buf));
5244 else
5245 strlcpy(buf, "<UNKNOWN>", sizeof(buf));
5246 isc_log_write(dns_lctx, DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DATABASE,
5247 DNS_LOGMODULE_CACHE, ISC_LOG_DEBUG(1),
5248 "calling free_rbtdb(%s)", buf);
5249 free_rbtdb(rbtdb, true, NULL);
5250 }
5251 }
5252}
5253
5254static isc_result_t
5255expirenode(dns_db_t *db, dns_dbnode_t *node, isc_stdtime_t now) {
5256 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
5257 dns_rbtnode_t *rbtnode = node;
5258 rdatasetheader_t *header;
5259 bool force_expire = false;
5260 /*
5261 * These are the category and module used by the cache cleaner.
5262 */
5263 bool log = false;
5264 isc_logcategory_t *category = DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DATABASE;
5265 isc_logmodule_t *module = DNS_LOGMODULE_CACHE;
5266 int level = ISC_LOG_DEBUG(2);
5267 char printname[DNS_NAME_FORMATSIZE];
5268
5269 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
5270
5271 /*
5272 * Caller must hold a tree lock.
5273 */
5274
5275 if (now == 0)
5276 isc_stdtime_get(&now);
5277
5278 if (isc_mem_isovermem(rbtdb->common.mctx)) {
5279 /*
5280 * Force expire with 25% probability.
5281 * XXXDCL Could stand to have a better policy, like LRU.
5282 */
5283 force_expire = (rbtnode->down == NULL &&
5284 (isc_random32() % 4) == 0);
5285
5286 /*
5287 * Note that 'log' can be true IFF overmem is also true.
5288 * overmem can currently only be true for cache
5289 * databases -- hence all of the "overmem cache" log strings.
5290 */
5291 log = isc_log_wouldlog(dns_lctx, level);
5292 if (log)
5293 isc_log_write(dns_lctx, category, module, level,
5294 "overmem cache: %s %s",
5295 force_expire ? "FORCE" : "check",
5296 dns_rbt_formatnodename(rbtnode,
5297 printname,
5298 sizeof(printname)));
5299 }
5300
5301 /*
5302 * We may not need write access, but this code path is not performance
5303 * sensitive, so it should be okay to always lock as a writer.
5304 */
5305 NODE_LOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[rbtnode->locknum].lock,
5306 isc_rwlocktype_write);
5307
5308 for (header = rbtnode->data; header != NULL; header = header->next)
5309 if (header->rdh_ttl <= now - RBTDB_VIRTUAL) {
5310 /*
5311 * We don't check if refcurrent(rbtnode) == 0 and try
5312 * to free like we do in cache_find(), because
5313 * refcurrent(rbtnode) must be non-zero. This is so
5314 * because 'node' is an argument to the function.
5315 */
5316 mark_header_ancient(rbtdb, header);
5317 if (log)
5318 isc_log_write(dns_lctx, category, module,
5319 level, "overmem cache: stale %s",
5320 printname);
5321 } else if (force_expire) {
5322 if (! RETAIN(header)) {
5323 set_ttl(rbtdb, header, 0);
5324 mark_header_ancient(rbtdb, header);
5325 } else if (log) {
5326 isc_log_write(dns_lctx, category, module,
5327 level, "overmem cache: "
5328 "reprieve by RETAIN() %s",
5329 printname);
5330 }
5331 } else if (isc_mem_isovermem(rbtdb->common.mctx) && log)
5332 isc_log_write(dns_lctx, category, module, level,
5333 "overmem cache: saved %s", printname);
5334
5335 NODE_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[rbtnode->locknum].lock,
5336 isc_rwlocktype_write);
5337
5338 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
5339}
5340
5341static void
5342overmem(dns_db_t *db, bool over) {
5343 /* This is an empty callback. See adb.c:water() */
5344
5345 UNUSED(db);
5346 UNUSED(over);
5347
5348 return;
5349}
5350
5351static void
5352printnode(dns_db_t *db, dns_dbnode_t *node, FILE *out) {
5353 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
5354 dns_rbtnode_t *rbtnode = node;
5355 bool first;
5356 uint32_t refs;
5357
5358 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
5359
5360 NODE_LOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[rbtnode->locknum].lock,
5361 isc_rwlocktype_read);
5362
5363 refs = isc_refcount_current(&rbtnode->references);
5364 fprintf(out, "node %p, %" PRIu32 " references, locknum = %u\n",
5365 rbtnode, refs,
5366 rbtnode->locknum);
5367 if (rbtnode->data != NULL) {
5368 rdatasetheader_t *current, *top_next;
5369
5370 for (current = rbtnode->data; current != NULL;
5371 current = top_next) {
5372 top_next = current->next;
5373 first = true;
5374 fprintf(out, "\ttype %u", current->type);
5375 do {
5376 if (!first)
5377 fprintf(out, "\t");
5378 first = false;
5379 fprintf(out,
5380 "\tserial = %lu, ttl = %u, "
5381 "trust = %u, attributes = %u, "
5382 "resign = %u\n",
5383 (unsigned long)current->serial,
5384 current->rdh_ttl,
5385 current->trust,
5386 current->attributes,
5387 (current->resign << 1) |
5388 current->resign_lsb);
5389 current = current->down;
5390 } while (current != NULL);
5391 }
5392 } else
5393 fprintf(out, "(empty)\n");
5394
5395 NODE_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[rbtnode->locknum].lock,
5396 isc_rwlocktype_read);
5397}
5398
5399static isc_result_t
5400createiterator(dns_db_t *db, unsigned int options, dns_dbiterator_t **iteratorp)
5401{
5402 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
5403 rbtdb_dbiterator_t *rbtdbiter;
5404
5405 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
5406
5407 rbtdbiter = isc_mem_get(rbtdb->common.mctx, sizeof(*rbtdbiter));
5408 if (rbtdbiter == NULL)
5409 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
5410
5411 rbtdbiter->common.methods = &dbiterator_methods;
5412 rbtdbiter->common.db = NULL;
5413 dns_db_attach(db, &rbtdbiter->common.db);
5414 rbtdbiter->common.relative_names =
5415 ((options & DNS_DB_RELATIVENAMES) != 0);
5416 rbtdbiter->common.magic = DNS_DBITERATOR_MAGIC;
5417 rbtdbiter->common.cleaning = false;
5418 rbtdbiter->paused = true;
5419 rbtdbiter->tree_locked = isc_rwlocktype_none;
5420 rbtdbiter->result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
5421 dns_fixedname_init(&rbtdbiter->name);
5422 dns_fixedname_init(&rbtdbiter->origin);
5423 rbtdbiter->node = NULL;
5424 rbtdbiter->delcnt = 0;
5425 rbtdbiter->nsec3only = ((options & DNS_DB_NSEC3ONLY) != 0);
5426 rbtdbiter->nonsec3 = ((options & DNS_DB_NONSEC3) != 0);
5427 memset(rbtdbiter->deletions, 0, sizeof(rbtdbiter->deletions));
5428 dns_rbtnodechain_init(&rbtdbiter->chain, db->mctx);
5429 dns_rbtnodechain_init(&rbtdbiter->nsec3chain, db->mctx);
5430 if (rbtdbiter->nsec3only)
5431 rbtdbiter->current = &rbtdbiter->nsec3chain;
5432 else
5433 rbtdbiter->current = &rbtdbiter->chain;
5434
5435 *iteratorp = (dns_dbiterator_t *)rbtdbiter;
5436
5437 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
5438}
5439
5440static isc_result_t
5441zone_findrdataset(dns_db_t *db, dns_dbnode_t *node, dns_dbversion_t *version,
5442 dns_rdatatype_t type, dns_rdatatype_t covers,
5443 isc_stdtime_t now, dns_rdataset_t *rdataset,
5444 dns_rdataset_t *sigrdataset)
5445{
5446 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
5447 dns_rbtnode_t *rbtnode = (dns_rbtnode_t *)node;
5448 rdatasetheader_t *header, *header_next, *found, *foundsig;
5449 rbtdb_serial_t serial;
5450 rbtdb_version_t *rbtversion = version;
5451 bool close_version = false;
5452 rbtdb_rdatatype_t matchtype, sigmatchtype;
5453
5454 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
5455 REQUIRE(type != dns_rdatatype_any);
5456 INSIST(rbtversion == NULL || rbtversion->rbtdb == rbtdb);
5457
5458 if (rbtversion == NULL) {
5459 currentversion(db, (dns_dbversion_t **) (void *)(&rbtversion));
5460 close_version = true;
5461 }
5462 serial = rbtversion->serial;
5463 now = 0;
5464
5465 NODE_LOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[rbtnode->locknum].lock,
5466 isc_rwlocktype_read);
5467
5468 found = NULL;
5469 foundsig = NULL;
5470 matchtype = RBTDB_RDATATYPE_VALUE(type, covers);
5471 if (covers == 0)
5472 sigmatchtype = RBTDB_RDATATYPE_VALUE(dns_rdatatype_rrsig, type);
5473 else
5474 sigmatchtype = 0;
5475
5476 for (header = rbtnode->data; header != NULL; header = header_next) {
5477 header_next = header->next;
5478 do {
5479 if (header->serial <= serial &&
5480 !IGNORE(header)) {
5481 /*
5482 * Is this a "this rdataset doesn't
5483 * exist" record?
5484 */
5485 if (NONEXISTENT(header))
5486 header = NULL;
5487 break;
5488 } else
5489 header = header->down;
5490 } while (header != NULL);
5491 if (header != NULL) {
5492 /*
5493 * We have an active, extant rdataset. If it's a
5494 * type we're looking for, remember it.
5495 */
5496 if (header->type == matchtype) {
5497 found = header;
5498 if (foundsig != NULL)
5499 break;
5500 } else if (header->type == sigmatchtype) {
5501 foundsig = header;
5502 if (found != NULL)
5503 break;
5504 }
5505 }
5506 }
5507 if (found != NULL) {
5508 bind_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtnode, found, now, rdataset);
5509 if (foundsig != NULL)
5510 bind_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtnode, foundsig, now,
5511 sigrdataset);
5512 }
5513
5514 NODE_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[rbtnode->locknum].lock,
5515 isc_rwlocktype_read);
5516
5517 if (close_version)
5518 closeversion(db, (dns_dbversion_t **) (void *)(&rbtversion),
5519 false);
5520
5521 if (found == NULL)
5522 return (ISC_R_NOTFOUND);
5523
5524 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
5525}
5526
5527static isc_result_t
5528cache_findrdataset(dns_db_t *db, dns_dbnode_t *node, dns_dbversion_t *version,
5529 dns_rdatatype_t type, dns_rdatatype_t covers,
5530 isc_stdtime_t now, dns_rdataset_t *rdataset,
5531 dns_rdataset_t *sigrdataset)
5532{
5533 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
5534 dns_rbtnode_t *rbtnode = (dns_rbtnode_t *)node;
5535 rdatasetheader_t *header, *header_next, *found, *foundsig;
5536 rbtdb_rdatatype_t matchtype, sigmatchtype, negtype;
5537 isc_result_t result;
5538 nodelock_t *lock;
5539 isc_rwlocktype_t locktype;
5540
5541 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
5542 REQUIRE(type != dns_rdatatype_any);
5543
5544 UNUSED(version);
5545
5546 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
5547
5548 if (now == 0)
5549 isc_stdtime_get(&now);
5550
5551 lock = &rbtdb->node_locks[rbtnode->locknum].lock;
5552 locktype = isc_rwlocktype_read;
5553 NODE_LOCK(lock, locktype);
5554
5555 found = NULL;
5556 foundsig = NULL;
5557 matchtype = RBTDB_RDATATYPE_VALUE(type, covers);
5558 negtype = RBTDB_RDATATYPE_VALUE(0, type);
5559 if (covers == 0)
5560 sigmatchtype = RBTDB_RDATATYPE_VALUE(dns_rdatatype_rrsig, type);
5561 else
5562 sigmatchtype = 0;
5563
5564 for (header = rbtnode->data; header != NULL; header = header_next) {
5565 header_next = header->next;
5566 if (!ACTIVE(header, now)) {
5567 if ((header->rdh_ttl < now - RBTDB_VIRTUAL) &&
5568 (locktype == isc_rwlocktype_write ||
5569 NODE_TRYUPGRADE(lock) == ISC_R_SUCCESS)) {
5570 /*
5571 * We update the node's status only when we
5572 * can get write access.
5573 */
5574 locktype = isc_rwlocktype_write;
5575
5576 /*
5577 * We don't check if refcurrent(rbtnode) == 0
5578 * and try to free like we do in cache_find(),
5579 * because refcurrent(rbtnode) must be
5580 * non-zero. This is so because 'node' is an
5581 * argument to the function.
5582 */
5583 mark_header_ancient(rbtdb, header);
5584 }
5585 } else if (EXISTS(header) && !ANCIENT(header)) {
5586 if (header->type == matchtype)
5587 found = header;
5588 else if (header->type == RBTDB_RDATATYPE_NCACHEANY ||
5589 header->type == negtype)
5590 found = header;
5591 else if (header->type == sigmatchtype)
5592 foundsig = header;
5593 }
5594 }
5595 if (found != NULL) {
5596 bind_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtnode, found, now, rdataset);
5597 if (!NEGATIVE(found) && foundsig != NULL)
5598 bind_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtnode, foundsig, now,
5599 sigrdataset);
5600 }
5601
5602 NODE_UNLOCK(lock, locktype);
5603
5604 if (found == NULL)
5605 return (ISC_R_NOTFOUND);
5606
5607 if (NEGATIVE(found)) {
5608 /*
5609 * We found a negative cache entry.
5610 */
5611 if (NXDOMAIN(found))
5612 result = DNS_R_NCACHENXDOMAIN;
5613 else
5614 result = DNS_R_NCACHENXRRSET;
5615 }
5616
5617 update_cachestats(rbtdb, result);
5618
5619 return (result);
5620}
5621
5622static isc_result_t
5623allrdatasets(dns_db_t *db, dns_dbnode_t *node, dns_dbversion_t *version,
5624 isc_stdtime_t now, dns_rdatasetiter_t **iteratorp)
5625{
5626 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
5627 dns_rbtnode_t *rbtnode = (dns_rbtnode_t *)node;
5628 rbtdb_version_t *rbtversion = version;
5629 rbtdb_rdatasetiter_t *iterator;
5630
5631 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
5632
5633 iterator = isc_mem_get(rbtdb->common.mctx, sizeof(*iterator));
5634 if (iterator == NULL)
5635 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
5636
5637 if ((db->attributes & DNS_DBATTR_CACHE) == 0) {
5638 now = 0;
5639 if (rbtversion == NULL)
5640 currentversion(db,
5641 (dns_dbversion_t **) (void *)(&rbtversion));
5642 else {
5643 INSIST(rbtversion->rbtdb == rbtdb);
5644
5645 (void)isc_refcount_increment(&rbtversion->references);
5646 }
5647 } else {
5648 if (now == 0)
5649 isc_stdtime_get(&now);
5650 rbtversion = NULL;
5651 }
5652
5653 iterator->common.magic = DNS_RDATASETITER_MAGIC;
5654 iterator->common.methods = &rdatasetiter_methods;
5655 iterator->common.db = db;
5656 iterator->common.node = node;
5657 iterator->common.version = (dns_dbversion_t *)rbtversion;
5658 iterator->common.now = now;
5659
5660 isc_refcount_increment(&rbtnode->references);
5661
5662 iterator->current = NULL;
5663
