5664 *iteratorp = (dns_rdatasetiter_t *)iterator;
5665
5666 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
5667}
5668
5669static bool
5670cname_and_other_data(dns_rbtnode_t *node, rbtdb_serial_t serial) {
5671 rdatasetheader_t *header, *header_next;
5672 bool cname, other_data;
5673 dns_rdatatype_t rdtype;
5674
5675 /*
5676 * The caller must hold the node lock.
5677 */
5678
5679 /*
5680 * Look for CNAME and "other data" rdatasets active in our version.
5681 */
5682 cname = false;
5683 other_data = false;
5684 for (header = node->data; header != NULL; header = header_next) {
5685 header_next = header->next;
5686 if (header->type == dns_rdatatype_cname) {
5687 /*
5688 * Look for an active extant CNAME.
5689 */
5690 do {
5691 if (header->serial <= serial &&
5692 !IGNORE(header)) {
5693 /*
5694 * Is this a "this rdataset doesn't
5695 * exist" record?
5696 */
5697 if (NONEXISTENT(header))
5698 header = NULL;
5699 break;
5700 } else
5701 header = header->down;
5702 } while (header != NULL);
5703 if (header != NULL)
5704 cname = true;
5705 } else {
5706 /*
5707 * Look for active extant "other data".
5708 *
5709 * "Other data" is any rdataset whose type is not
5710 * KEY, NSEC, SIG or RRSIG.
5711 */
5712 rdtype = RBTDB_RDATATYPE_BASE(header->type);
5713 if (rdtype != dns_rdatatype_key &&
5714 rdtype != dns_rdatatype_sig &&
5715 rdtype != dns_rdatatype_nsec &&
5716 rdtype != dns_rdatatype_rrsig) {
5717 /*
5718 * Is it active and extant?
5719 */
5720 do {
5721 if (header->serial <= serial &&
5722 !IGNORE(header)) {
5723 /*
5724 * Is this a "this rdataset
5725 * doesn't exist" record?
5726 */
5727 if (NONEXISTENT(header))
5728 header = NULL;
5729 break;
5730 } else
5731 header = header->down;
5732 } while (header != NULL);
5733 if (header != NULL)
5734 other_data = true;
5735 }
5736 }
5737 }
5738
5739 if (cname && other_data)
5740 return (true);
5741
5742 return (false);
5743}
5744
5745static isc_result_t
5746resign_insert(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, int idx, rdatasetheader_t *newheader) {
5747 isc_result_t result;
5748
5749 INSIST(!IS_CACHE(rbtdb));
5750 INSIST(newheader->heap_index == 0);
5751 INSIST(!ISC_LINK_LINKED(newheader, link));
5752
5753 result = isc_heap_insert(rbtdb->heaps[idx], newheader);
5754 return (result);
5755}
5756
5757static void
5758resign_delete(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, rbtdb_version_t *version,
5759 rdatasetheader_t *header)
5760{
5761 /*
5762 * Remove the old header from the heap
5763 */
5764 if (header != NULL && header->heap_index != 0) {
5765 isc_heap_delete(rbtdb->heaps[header->node->locknum],
5766 header->heap_index);
5767 header->heap_index = 0;
5768 if (version != NULL) {
5769 new_reference(rbtdb, header->node);
5770 ISC_LIST_APPEND(version->resigned_list, header, link);
5771 }
5772 }
5773}
5774
5775static void
5776update_recordsandbytes(bool add, rbtdb_version_t *rbtversion,
5777 rdatasetheader_t *header)
5778{
5779 unsigned char *hdr = (unsigned char *)header;
5780 size_t hdrsize = sizeof (*header);
5781
5782 if (add) {
5783 rbtversion->records += dns_rdataslab_count(hdr, hdrsize);
5784 rbtversion->bytes += dns_rdataslab_size(hdr, hdrsize);
5785 } else {
5786 rbtversion->records -= dns_rdataslab_count(hdr, hdrsize);
5787 rbtversion->bytes -= dns_rdataslab_size(hdr, hdrsize);
5788 }
5789}
5790
5791static isc_result_t
5792add32(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, dns_rbtnode_t *rbtnode, rbtdb_version_t *rbtversion,
5793 rdatasetheader_t *newheader, unsigned int options, bool loading,
5794 dns_rdataset_t *addedrdataset, isc_stdtime_t now)
5795{
5796 rbtdb_changed_t *changed = NULL;
5797 rdatasetheader_t *topheader, *topheader_prev, *header, *sigheader;
5798 unsigned char *merged;
5799 isc_result_t result;
5800 bool header_nx;
5801 bool newheader_nx;
5802 bool merge;
5803 dns_rdatatype_t rdtype, covers;
5804 rbtdb_rdatatype_t negtype, sigtype;
5805 dns_trust_t trust;
5806 int idx;
5807
5808 /*
5809 * Add an rdatasetheader_t to a node.
5810 */
5811
5812 /*
5813 * Caller must be holding the node lock.
5814 */
5815
5816 if ((options & DNS_DBADD_MERGE) != 0) {
5817 REQUIRE(rbtversion != NULL);
5818 merge = true;
5819 } else
5820 merge = false;
5821
5822 if ((options & DNS_DBADD_FORCE) != 0)
5823 trust = dns_trust_ultimate;
5824 else
5825 trust = newheader->trust;
5826
5827 if (rbtversion != NULL && !loading) {
5828 /*
5829 * We always add a changed record, even if no changes end up
5830 * being made to this node, because it's harmless and
5831 * simplifies the code.
5832 */
5833 changed = add_changed(rbtdb, rbtversion, rbtnode);
5834 if (changed == NULL) {
5835 free_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtdb->common.mctx, newheader);
5836 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
5837 }
5838 }
5839
5840 newheader_nx = NONEXISTENT(newheader) ? true : false;
5841 topheader_prev = NULL;
5842 sigheader = NULL;
5843 negtype = 0;
5844 if (rbtversion == NULL && !newheader_nx) {
5845 rdtype = RBTDB_RDATATYPE_BASE(newheader->type);
5846 covers = RBTDB_RDATATYPE_EXT(newheader->type);
5847 sigtype = RBTDB_RDATATYPE_VALUE(dns_rdatatype_rrsig, covers);
5848 if (NEGATIVE(newheader)) {
5849 /*
5850 * We're adding a negative cache entry.
5851 */
5852 if (covers == dns_rdatatype_any) {
5853 /*
5854 * If we're adding an negative cache entry
5855 * which covers all types (NXDOMAIN,
5856 * NODATA(QTYPE=ANY)),
5857 *
5858 * We make all other data stale so that the
5859 * only rdataset that can be found at this
5860 * node is the negative cache entry.
5861 */
5862 for (topheader = rbtnode->data;
5863 topheader != NULL;
5864 topheader = topheader->next)
5865 {
5866 set_ttl(rbtdb, topheader, 0);
5867 mark_header_ancient(rbtdb, topheader);
5868 }
5869 goto find_header;
5870 }
5871 /*
5872 * Otherwise look for any RRSIGs of the given
5873 * type so they can be marked stale later.
5874 */
5875 for (topheader = rbtnode->data;
5876 topheader != NULL;
5877 topheader = topheader->next)
5878 if (topheader->type == sigtype)
5879 sigheader = topheader;
5880 negtype = RBTDB_RDATATYPE_VALUE(covers, 0);
5881 } else {
5882 /*
5883 * We're adding something that isn't a
5884 * negative cache entry. Look for an extant
5885 * non-stale NXDOMAIN/NODATA(QTYPE=ANY) negative
5886 * cache entry. If we're adding an RRSIG, also
5887 * check for an extant non-stale NODATA ncache
5888 * entry which covers the same type as the RRSIG.
5889 */
5890 for (topheader = rbtnode->data;
5891 topheader != NULL;
5892 topheader = topheader->next) {
5893 if ((topheader->type ==
5894 RBTDB_RDATATYPE_NCACHEANY) ||
5895 (newheader->type == sigtype &&
5896 topheader->type ==
5897 RBTDB_RDATATYPE_VALUE(0, covers))) {
5898 break;
5899 }
5900 }
5901 if (topheader != NULL && EXISTS(topheader) &&
5902 ACTIVE(topheader, now)) {
5903 /*
5904 * Found one.
5905 */
5906 if (trust < topheader->trust) {
5907 /*
5908 * The NXDOMAIN/NODATA(QTYPE=ANY)
5909 * is more trusted.
5910 */
5911 free_rdataset(rbtdb,
5912 rbtdb->common.mctx,
5913 newheader);
5914 if (addedrdataset != NULL)
5915 bind_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtnode,
5916 topheader, now,
5917 addedrdataset);
5918 return (DNS_R_UNCHANGED);
5919 }
5920 /*
5921 * The new rdataset is better. Expire the
5922 * ncache entry.
5923 */
5924 set_ttl(rbtdb, topheader, 0);
5925 mark_header_ancient(rbtdb, topheader);
5926 topheader = NULL;
5927 goto find_header;
5928 }
5929 negtype = RBTDB_RDATATYPE_VALUE(0, rdtype);
5930 }
5931 }
5932
5933 for (topheader = rbtnode->data;
5934 topheader != NULL;
5935 topheader = topheader->next) {
5936 if (topheader->type == newheader->type ||
5937 topheader->type == negtype)
5938 break;
5939 topheader_prev = topheader;
5940 }
5941
5942 find_header:
5943 /*
5944 * If header isn't NULL, we've found the right type. There may be
5945 * IGNORE rdatasets between the top of the chain and the first real
5946 * data. We skip over them.
5947 */
5948 header = topheader;
5949 while (header != NULL && IGNORE(header))
5950 header = header->down;
5951 if (header != NULL) {
5952 header_nx = NONEXISTENT(header) ? true : false;
5953
5954 /*
5955 * Deleting an already non-existent rdataset has no effect.
5956 */
5957 if (header_nx && newheader_nx) {
5958 free_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtdb->common.mctx, newheader);
5959 return (DNS_R_UNCHANGED);
5960 }
5961
5962 /*
5963 * Trying to add an rdataset with lower trust to a cache
5964 * DB has no effect, provided that the cache data isn't
5965 * stale. If the cache data is stale, new lower trust
5966 * data will supersede it below. Unclear what the best
5967 * policy is here.
5968 */
5969 if (rbtversion == NULL && trust < header->trust &&
5970 (ACTIVE(header, now) || header_nx)) {
5971 free_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtdb->common.mctx, newheader);
5972 if (addedrdataset != NULL)
5973 bind_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtnode, header, now,
5974 addedrdataset);
5975 return (DNS_R_UNCHANGED);
5976 }
5977
5978 /*
5979 * Don't merge if a nonexistent rdataset is involved.
5980 */
5981 if (merge && (header_nx || newheader_nx))
5982 merge = false;
5983
5984 /*
5985 * If 'merge' is true, we'll try to create a new rdataset
5986 * that is the union of 'newheader' and 'header'.
5987 */
5988 if (merge) {
5989 unsigned int flags = 0;
5990 INSIST(rbtversion->serial >= header->serial);
5991 merged = NULL;
5992 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
5993
5994 if ((options & DNS_DBADD_EXACT) != 0)
5995 flags |= DNS_RDATASLAB_EXACT;
5996 /*
5997 * TTL use here is irrelevant to the cache;
5998 * merge is only done with zonedbs.
5999 */
6000 if ((options & DNS_DBADD_EXACTTTL) != 0 &&
6001 newheader->rdh_ttl != header->rdh_ttl)
6002 result = DNS_R_NOTEXACT;
6003 else if (newheader->rdh_ttl != header->rdh_ttl)
6004 flags |= DNS_RDATASLAB_FORCE;
6005 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
6006 result = dns_rdataslab_merge(
6007 (unsigned char *)header,
6008 (unsigned char *)newheader,
6009 (unsigned int)(sizeof(*newheader)),
6010 rbtdb->common.mctx,
6011 rbtdb->common.rdclass,
6012 (dns_rdatatype_t)header->type,
6013 flags, &merged);
6014 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
6015 /*
6016 * If 'header' has the same serial number as
6017 * we do, we could clean it up now if we knew
6018 * that our caller had no references to it.
6019 * We don't know this, however, so we leave it
6020 * alone. It will get cleaned up when
6021 * clean_zone_node() runs.
6022 */
6023 free_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtdb->common.mctx,
6024 newheader);
6025 newheader = (rdatasetheader_t *)merged;
6026 init_rdataset(rbtdb, newheader);
6027 update_newheader(newheader, header);
6028 if (loading && RESIGN(newheader) &&
6029 RESIGN(header) &&
6030 resign_sooner(header, newheader))
6031 {
6032 newheader->resign = header->resign;
6033 newheader->resign_lsb =
6034 header->resign_lsb;
6035 }
6036 } else {
6037 free_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtdb->common.mctx,
6038 newheader);
6039 return (result);
6040 }
6041 }
6042 /*
6043 * Don't replace existing NS, A and AAAA RRsets in the
6044 * cache if they are already exist. This prevents named
6045 * being locked to old servers. Don't lower trust of
6046 * existing record if the update is forced. Nothing
6047 * special to be done w.r.t stale data; it gets replaced
6048 * normally further down.
6049 */
6050 if (IS_CACHE(rbtdb) && ACTIVE(header, now) &&
6051 header->type == dns_rdatatype_ns &&
6052 !header_nx && !newheader_nx &&
6053 header->trust >= newheader->trust &&
6054 dns_rdataslab_equalx((unsigned char *)header,
6055 (unsigned char *)newheader,
6056 (unsigned int)(sizeof(*newheader)),
6057 rbtdb->common.rdclass,
6058 (dns_rdatatype_t)header->type)) {
6059 /*
6060 * Honour the new ttl if it is less than the
6061 * older one.
6062 */
6063 if (header->rdh_ttl > newheader->rdh_ttl)
6064 set_ttl(rbtdb, header, newheader->rdh_ttl);
6065 if (header->noqname == NULL &&
6066 newheader->noqname != NULL) {
6067 header->noqname = newheader->noqname;
6068 newheader->noqname = NULL;
6069 }
6070 if (header->closest == NULL &&
6071 newheader->closest != NULL) {
6072 header->closest = newheader->closest;
6073 newheader->closest = NULL;
6074 }
6075 free_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtdb->common.mctx, newheader);
6076 if (addedrdataset != NULL)
6077 bind_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtnode, header, now,
6078 addedrdataset);
6079 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
6080 }
6081 /*
6082 * If we have will be replacing a NS RRset force its TTL
6083 * to be no more than the current NS RRset's TTL. This
6084 * ensures the delegations that are withdrawn are honoured.
6085 */
6086 if (IS_CACHE(rbtdb) && ACTIVE(header, now) &&
6087 header->type == dns_rdatatype_ns &&
6088 !header_nx && !newheader_nx &&
6089 header->trust <= newheader->trust) {
6090 if (newheader->rdh_ttl > header->rdh_ttl) {
6091 newheader->rdh_ttl = header->rdh_ttl;
6092 }
6093 }
6094 if (IS_CACHE(rbtdb) && ACTIVE(header, now) &&
6095 (options & DNS_DBADD_PREFETCH) == 0 &&
6096 (header->type == dns_rdatatype_a ||
6097 header->type == dns_rdatatype_aaaa ||
6098 header->type == dns_rdatatype_ds ||
6099 header->type == RBTDB_RDATATYPE_SIGDDS) &&
6100 !header_nx && !newheader_nx &&
6101 header->trust >= newheader->trust &&
6102 dns_rdataslab_equal((unsigned char *)header,
6103 (unsigned char *)newheader,
6104 (unsigned int)(sizeof(*newheader)))) {
6105 /*
6106 * Honour the new ttl if it is less than the
6107 * older one.
6108 */
6109 if (header->rdh_ttl > newheader->rdh_ttl)
6110 set_ttl(rbtdb, header, newheader->rdh_ttl);
6111 if (header->noqname == NULL &&
6112 newheader->noqname != NULL) {
6113 header->noqname = newheader->noqname;
6114 newheader->noqname = NULL;
6115 }
6116 if (header->closest == NULL &&
6117 newheader->closest != NULL) {
6118 header->closest = newheader->closest;
6119 newheader->closest = NULL;
6120 }
6121 free_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtdb->common.mctx, newheader);
6122 if (addedrdataset != NULL)
6123 bind_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtnode, header, now,
6124 addedrdataset);
6125 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
6126 }
6127 INSIST(rbtversion == NULL ||
6128 rbtversion->serial >= topheader->serial);
6129 if (loading) {
6130 newheader->down = NULL;
6131 idx = newheader->node->locknum;
6132 if (IS_CACHE(rbtdb)) {
6133 if (ZEROTTL(newheader))
6134 ISC_LIST_APPEND(rbtdb->rdatasets[idx],
6135 newheader, link);
6136 else
6137 ISC_LIST_PREPEND(rbtdb->rdatasets[idx],
6138 newheader, link);
6139 INSIST(rbtdb->heaps != NULL);
6140 result = isc_heap_insert(rbtdb->heaps[idx],
6141 newheader);
6142 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
6143 free_rdataset(rbtdb,
6144 rbtdb->common.mctx,
6145 newheader);
6146 return (result);
6147 }
6148 } else if (RESIGN(newheader)) {
6149 result = resign_insert(rbtdb, idx, newheader);
6150 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
6151 free_rdataset(rbtdb,
6152 rbtdb->common.mctx,
6153 newheader);
6154 return (result);
6155 }
6156 /*
6157 * Don't call resign_delete as we don't need
6158 * to reverse the delete. The free_rdataset
6159 * call below will clean up the heap entry.
6160 */
6161 }
6162
6163 /*
6164 * There are no other references to 'header' when
6165 * loading, so we MAY clean up 'header' now.
6166 * Since we don't generate changed records when
6167 * loading, we MUST clean up 'header' now.
6168 */
6169 if (topheader_prev != NULL)
6170 topheader_prev->next = newheader;
6171 else
6172 rbtnode->data = newheader;
6173 newheader->next = topheader->next;
6174 if (rbtversion != NULL && !header_nx) {
6175 RWLOCK(&rbtversion->rwlock,
6176 isc_rwlocktype_write);
6177 update_recordsandbytes(false, rbtversion,
6178 header);
6179 RWUNLOCK(&rbtversion->rwlock,
6180 isc_rwlocktype_write);
6181 }
6182 free_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtdb->common.mctx, header);
6183 } else {
6184 idx = newheader->node->locknum;
6185 if (IS_CACHE(rbtdb)) {
6186 INSIST(rbtdb->heaps != NULL);
6187 result = isc_heap_insert(rbtdb->heaps[idx],
6188 newheader);
6189 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
6190 free_rdataset(rbtdb,
6191 rbtdb->common.mctx,
6192 newheader);
6193 return (result);
6194 }
6195 if (ZEROTTL(newheader))
6196 ISC_LIST_APPEND(rbtdb->rdatasets[idx],
6197 newheader, link);
6198 else
6199 ISC_LIST_PREPEND(rbtdb->rdatasets[idx],
6200 newheader, link);
6201 } else if (RESIGN(newheader)) {
6202 result = resign_insert(rbtdb, idx, newheader);
6203 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
6204 free_rdataset(rbtdb,
6205 rbtdb->common.mctx,
6206 newheader);
6207 return (result);
6208 }
6209 resign_delete(rbtdb, rbtversion, header);
6210 }
6211 if (topheader_prev != NULL)
6212 topheader_prev->next = newheader;
6213 else
6214 rbtnode->data = newheader;
6215 newheader->next = topheader->next;
6216 newheader->down = topheader;
6217 topheader->next = newheader;
6218 rbtnode->dirty = 1;
6219 if (changed != NULL)
6220 changed->dirty = true;
6221 if (rbtversion == NULL) {
6222 set_ttl(rbtdb, header, 0);
6223 mark_header_ancient(rbtdb, header);
6224 if (sigheader != NULL) {
6225 set_ttl(rbtdb, sigheader, 0);
6226 mark_header_ancient(rbtdb, sigheader);
6227 }
6228 }
6229 if (rbtversion != NULL && !header_nx) {
6230 RWLOCK(&rbtversion->rwlock,
6231 isc_rwlocktype_write);
6232 update_recordsandbytes(false, rbtversion,
6233 header);
6234 RWUNLOCK(&rbtversion->rwlock,
6235 isc_rwlocktype_write);
6236 }
6237 }
6238 } else {
6239 /*
6240 * No non-IGNORED rdatasets of the given type exist at
6241 * this node.
6242 */
6243
6244 /*
6245 * If we're trying to delete the type, don't bother.
6246 */
6247 if (newheader_nx) {
6248 free_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtdb->common.mctx, newheader);
6249 return (DNS_R_UNCHANGED);
6250 }
6251
6252 idx = newheader->node->locknum;
6253 if (IS_CACHE(rbtdb)) {
6254 result = isc_heap_insert(rbtdb->heaps[idx], newheader);
6255 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
6256 free_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtdb->common.mctx,
6257 newheader);
6258 return (result);
6259 }
6260 if (ZEROTTL(newheader))
6261 ISC_LIST_APPEND(rbtdb->rdatasets[idx],
6262 newheader, link);
6263 else
6264 ISC_LIST_PREPEND(rbtdb->rdatasets[idx],
6265 newheader, link);
6266 } else if (RESIGN(newheader)) {
6267 result = resign_insert(rbtdb, idx, newheader);
6268 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
6269 free_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtdb->common.mctx,
6270 newheader);
6271 return (result);
6272 }
6273 resign_delete(rbtdb, rbtversion, header);
6274 }
6275
6276 if (topheader != NULL) {
6277 /*
6278 * We have an list of rdatasets of the given type,
6279 * but they're all marked IGNORE. We simply insert
6280 * the new rdataset at the head of the list.
6281 *
6282 * Ignored rdatasets cannot occur during loading, so
6283 * we INSIST on it.
6284 */
6285 INSIST(!loading);
6286 INSIST(rbtversion == NULL ||
6287 rbtversion->serial >= topheader->serial);
6288 if (topheader_prev != NULL)
6289 topheader_prev->next = newheader;
6290 else
6291 rbtnode->data = newheader;
6292 newheader->next = topheader->next;
6293 newheader->down = topheader;
6294 topheader->next = newheader;
6295 rbtnode->dirty = 1;
6296 if (changed != NULL)
6297 changed->dirty = true;
6298 } else {
6299 /*
6300 * No rdatasets of the given type exist at the node.
6301 */
6302 newheader->next = rbtnode->data;
6303 newheader->down = NULL;
6304 rbtnode->data = newheader;
6305 }
6306 }
6307
6308 if (rbtversion != NULL && !newheader_nx) {
6309 RWLOCK(&rbtversion->rwlock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
6310 update_recordsandbytes(true, rbtversion, newheader);
6311 RWUNLOCK(&rbtversion->rwlock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
6312 }
6313
6314 /*
6315 * Check if the node now contains CNAME and other data.
6316 */
6317 if (rbtversion != NULL &&
6318 cname_and_other_data(rbtnode, rbtversion->serial))
6319 return (DNS_R_CNAMEANDOTHER);
6320
6321 if (addedrdataset != NULL)
6322 bind_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtnode, newheader, now, addedrdataset);
6323
6324 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
6325}
6326
6327static inline bool
6328delegating_type(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, dns_rbtnode_t *node,
6329 rbtdb_rdatatype_t type)
6330{
6331 if (IS_CACHE(rbtdb)) {
6332 if (type == dns_rdatatype_dname)
6333 return (true);
6334 else
6335 return (false);
6336 } else if (type == dns_rdatatype_dname ||
6337 (type == dns_rdatatype_ns &&
6338 (node != rbtdb->origin_node || IS_STUB(rbtdb))))
6339 return (true);
6340 return (false);
6341}
6342
6343static inline isc_result_t
6344addnoqname(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, rdatasetheader_t *newheader,
6345 dns_rdataset_t *rdataset)
6346{
6347 struct noqname *noqname;
6348 isc_mem_t *mctx = rbtdb->common.mctx;
6349 dns_name_t name;
6350 dns_rdataset_t neg, negsig;
6351 isc_result_t result;
6352 isc_region_t r;
6353
6354 dns_name_init(&name, NULL);
6355 dns_rdataset_init(&neg);
6356 dns_rdataset_init(&negsig);
6357
6358 result = dns_rdataset_getnoqname(rdataset, &name, &neg, &negsig);
6359 RUNTIME_CHECK(result == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
6360
6361 noqname = isc_mem_get(mctx, sizeof(*noqname));
6362 if (noqname == NULL) {
6363 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
6364 goto cleanup;
6365 }
6366 dns_name_init(&noqname->name, NULL);
6367 noqname->neg = NULL;
6368 noqname->negsig = NULL;
6369 noqname->type = neg.type;
6370 result = dns_name_dup(&name, mctx, &noqname->name);
6371 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
6372 goto cleanup;
6373 result = dns_rdataslab_fromrdataset(&neg, mctx, &r, 0);
6374 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
6375 goto cleanup;
6376 noqname->neg = r.base;
6377 result = dns_rdataslab_fromrdataset(&negsig, mctx, &r, 0);
6378 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
6379 goto cleanup;
6380 noqname->negsig = r.base;
6381 dns_rdataset_disassociate(&neg);
6382 dns_rdataset_disassociate(&negsig);
6383 newheader->noqname = noqname;
6384 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
6385
6386cleanup:
6387 dns_rdataset_disassociate(&neg);
6388 dns_rdataset_disassociate(&negsig);
6389 if (noqname != NULL)
6390 free_noqname(mctx, &noqname);
6391 return(result);
6392}
6393
6394static inline isc_result_t
6395addclosest(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, rdatasetheader_t *newheader,
6396 dns_rdataset_t *rdataset)
6397{
6398 struct noqname *closest;
6399 isc_mem_t *mctx = rbtdb->common.mctx;
6400 dns_name_t name;
6401 dns_rdataset_t neg, negsig;
6402 isc_result_t result;
6403 isc_region_t r;
6404
6405 dns_name_init(&name, NULL);
6406 dns_rdataset_init(&neg);
6407 dns_rdataset_init(&negsig);
6408
6409 result = dns_rdataset_getclosest(rdataset, &name, &neg, &negsig);
6410 RUNTIME_CHECK(result == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
6411
6412 closest = isc_mem_get(mctx, sizeof(*closest));
6413 if (closest == NULL) {
6414 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
6415 goto cleanup;
6416 }
6417 dns_name_init(&closest->name, NULL);
6418 closest->neg = NULL;
6419 closest->negsig = NULL;
6420 closest->type = neg.type;
6421 result = dns_name_dup(&name, mctx, &closest->name);
6422 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
6423 goto cleanup;
6424 result = dns_rdataslab_fromrdataset(&neg, mctx, &r, 0);
6425 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
6426 goto cleanup;
6427 closest->neg = r.base;
6428 result = dns_rdataslab_fromrdataset(&negsig, mctx, &r, 0);
6429 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
6430 goto cleanup;
6431 closest->negsig = r.base;
6432 dns_rdataset_disassociate(&neg);
6433 dns_rdataset_disassociate(&negsig);
6434 newheader->closest = closest;
6435 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
6436
6437 cleanup:
6438 dns_rdataset_disassociate(&neg);
6439 dns_rdataset_disassociate(&negsig);
6440 if (closest != NULL)
6441 free_noqname(mctx, &closest);
6442 return(result);
6443}
6444
6445static dns_dbmethods_t zone_methods;
6446
6447static isc_result_t
6448addrdataset(dns_db_t *db, dns_dbnode_t *node, dns_dbversion_t *version,
6449 isc_stdtime_t now, dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, unsigned int options,
6450 dns_rdataset_t *addedrdataset)
6451{
6452 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
6453 dns_rbtnode_t *rbtnode = (dns_rbtnode_t *)node;
6454 rbtdb_version_t *rbtversion = version;
6455 isc_region_t region;
6456 rdatasetheader_t *newheader;
6457 rdatasetheader_t *header;
6458 isc_result_t result;
6459 bool delegating;
6460 bool newnsec;
6461 bool tree_locked = false;
6462 bool cache_is_overmem = false;
6463 dns_fixedname_t fixed;
6464 dns_name_t *name;
6465
6466 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
6467 INSIST(rbtversion == NULL || rbtversion->rbtdb == rbtdb);
6468
6469 if (rbtdb->common.methods == &zone_methods)
6470 REQUIRE(((rbtnode->nsec == DNS_RBT_NSEC_NSEC3 &&
6471 (rdataset->type == dns_rdatatype_nsec3 ||
6472 rdataset->covers == dns_rdatatype_nsec3)) ||
6473 (rbtnode->nsec != DNS_RBT_NSEC_NSEC3 &&
6474 rdataset->type != dns_rdatatype_nsec3 &&
6475 rdataset->covers != dns_rdatatype_nsec3)));
6476
6477 if (rbtversion == NULL) {
6478 if (now == 0)
6479 isc_stdtime_get(&now);
6480 } else
6481 now = 0;
6482
6483 result = dns_rdataslab_fromrdataset(rdataset, rbtdb->common.mctx,
6484 &region, sizeof(rdatasetheader_t));
6485 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
6486 return (result);
6487
6488 name = dns_fixedname_initname(&fixed);
6489 RWLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
6490 dns_rbt_fullnamefromnode(node, name);
6491 RWUNLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
6492 dns_rdataset_getownercase(rdataset, name);
6493
6494 newheader = (rdatasetheader_t *)region.base;
6495 init_rdataset(rbtdb, newheader);
6496 setownercase(newheader, name);
6497 set_ttl(rbtdb, newheader, rdataset->ttl + now);
6498 newheader->type = RBTDB_RDATATYPE_VALUE(rdataset->type,
6499 rdataset->covers);
6500 newheader->attributes = 0;
6501 if (rdataset->ttl == 0U)
6502 newheader->attributes |= RDATASET_ATTR_ZEROTTL;
6503 newheader->noqname = NULL;
6504 newheader->closest = NULL;
6505 newheader->count = init_count++;
6506 newheader->trust = rdataset->trust;
6507 newheader->last_used = now;
6508 newheader->node = rbtnode;
6509 if (rbtversion != NULL) {
6510 newheader->serial = rbtversion->serial;
6511 now = 0;
6512
6513 if ((rdataset->attributes & DNS_RDATASETATTR_RESIGN) != 0) {
6514 newheader->attributes |= RDATASET_ATTR_RESIGN;
6515 newheader->resign = (isc_stdtime_t)
6516 (dns_time64_from32(rdataset->resign) >> 1);
6517 newheader->resign_lsb = rdataset->resign & 0x1;
6518 } else {
6519 newheader->resign = 0;
6520 newheader->resign_lsb = 0;
6521 }
6522 } else {
6523 newheader->serial = 1;
6524 newheader->resign = 0;
6525 newheader->resign_lsb = 0;
6526 if ((rdataset->attributes & DNS_RDATASETATTR_PREFETCH) != 0)
6527 newheader->attributes |= RDATASET_ATTR_PREFETCH;
6528 if ((rdataset->attributes & DNS_RDATASETATTR_NEGATIVE) != 0)
6529 newheader->attributes |= RDATASET_ATTR_NEGATIVE;
6530 if ((rdataset->attributes & DNS_RDATASETATTR_NXDOMAIN) != 0)
6531 newheader->attributes |= RDATASET_ATTR_NXDOMAIN;
6532 if ((rdataset->attributes & DNS_RDATASETATTR_OPTOUT) != 0)
6533 newheader->attributes |= RDATASET_ATTR_OPTOUT;
6534 if ((rdataset->attributes & DNS_RDATASETATTR_NOQNAME) != 0) {
6535 result = addnoqname(rbtdb, newheader, rdataset);
6536 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
6537 free_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtdb->common.mctx,
6538 newheader);
6539 return (result);
6540 }
6541 }
6542 if ((rdataset->attributes & DNS_RDATASETATTR_CLOSEST) != 0) {
6543 result = addclosest(rbtdb, newheader, rdataset);
6544 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
6545 free_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtdb->common.mctx,
6546 newheader);
6547 return (result);
6548 }
6549 }
6550 }
6551
6552 /*
6553 * If we're adding a delegation type (e.g. NS or DNAME for a zone,
6554 * just DNAME for the cache), then we need to set the callback bit
6555 * on the node.
6556 */
6557 if (delegating_type(rbtdb, rbtnode, rdataset->type))
6558 delegating = true;
6559 else
6560 delegating = false;
6561
6562 /*
6563 * Add to the auxiliary NSEC tree if we're adding an NSEC record.
6564 */
6565 if (rbtnode->nsec != DNS_RBT_NSEC_HAS_NSEC &&
6566 rdataset->type == dns_rdatatype_nsec)
6567 newnsec = true;
6568 else
6569 newnsec = false;
6570
6571 /*
6572 * If we're adding a delegation type, adding to the auxiliary NSEC tree,
6573 * or the DB is a cache in an overmem state, hold an exclusive lock on
6574 * the tree. In the latter case the lock does not necessarily have to
6575 * be acquired but it will help purge stale entries more effectively.
6576 */
6577 if (IS_CACHE(rbtdb) && isc_mem_isovermem(rbtdb->common.mctx))
6578 cache_is_overmem = true;
6579 if (delegating || newnsec || cache_is_overmem) {
6580 tree_locked = true;
6581 RWLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
6582 }
6583
6584 if (cache_is_overmem)
6585 overmem_purge(rbtdb, rbtnode->locknum, now, tree_locked);
6586
6587 NODE_LOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[rbtnode->locknum].lock,
6588 isc_rwlocktype_write);
6589
6590 if (rbtdb->rrsetstats != NULL) {
6591 newheader->attributes |= RDATASET_ATTR_STATCOUNT;
6592 update_rrsetstats(rbtdb, newheader, true);
6593 }
6594
6595 if (IS_CACHE(rbtdb)) {
6596 if (tree_locked)
6597 cleanup_dead_nodes(rbtdb, rbtnode->locknum);
6598
6599 header = isc_heap_element(rbtdb->heaps[rbtnode->locknum], 1);
6600 if (header && header->rdh_ttl < now - RBTDB_VIRTUAL)
6601 expire_header(rbtdb, header, tree_locked,
6602 expire_ttl);
6603
6604 /*
6605 * If we've been holding a write lock on the tree just for
6606 * cleaning, we can release it now. However, we still need the
6607 * node lock.
6608 */
6609 if (tree_locked && !delegating && !newnsec) {
6610 RWUNLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
6611 tree_locked = false;
6612 }
6613 }
6614
6615 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
6616 if (newnsec) {
6617 dns_rbtnode_t *nsecnode;
6618
6619 dns_rbt_fullnamefromnode(rbtnode, name);
6620 nsecnode = NULL;
6621 result = dns_rbt_addnode(rbtdb->nsec, name, &nsecnode);
6622 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
6623 nsecnode->nsec = DNS_RBT_NSEC_NSEC;
6624 rbtnode->nsec = DNS_RBT_NSEC_HAS_NSEC;
6625 } else if (result == ISC_R_EXISTS) {
6626 rbtnode->nsec = DNS_RBT_NSEC_HAS_NSEC;
6627 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
6628 }
6629 }
6630
6631 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
6632 result = add32(rbtdb, rbtnode, rbtversion, newheader, options,
6633 false, addedrdataset, now);
6634 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS && delegating)
6635 rbtnode->find_callback = 1;
6636
6637 NODE_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[rbtnode->locknum].lock,
6638 isc_rwlocktype_write);
6639
6640 if (tree_locked)
6641 RWUNLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
6642
6643 /*
6644 * Update the zone's secure status. If version is non-NULL
6645 * this is deferred until closeversion() is called.
6646 */
6647 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS && version == NULL && !IS_CACHE(rbtdb))
6648 iszonesecure(db, version, rbtdb->origin_node);
6649
6650 return (result);
6651}
6652
6653static isc_result_t
6654subtractrdataset(dns_db_t *db, dns_dbnode_t *node, dns_dbversion_t *version,
6655 dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, unsigned int options,
6656 dns_rdataset_t *newrdataset)
6657{
6658 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
6659 dns_rbtnode_t *rbtnode = (dns_rbtnode_t *)node;
6660 rbtdb_version_t *rbtversion = version;
6661 rdatasetheader_t *topheader, *topheader_prev, *header, *newheader;
6662 unsigned char *subresult;
6663 isc_region_t region;
6664 isc_result_t result;
6665 rbtdb_changed_t *changed;
6666
6667 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
6668 REQUIRE(rbtversion != NULL && rbtversion->rbtdb == rbtdb);
6669
6670 if (rbtdb->common.methods == &zone_methods)
6671 REQUIRE(((rbtnode->nsec == DNS_RBT_NSEC_NSEC3 &&
6672 (rdataset->type == dns_rdatatype_nsec3 ||
6673 rdataset->covers == dns_rdatatype_nsec3)) ||
6674 (rbtnode->nsec != DNS_RBT_NSEC_NSEC3 &&
6675 rdataset->type != dns_rdatatype_nsec3 &&
6676 rdataset->covers != dns_rdatatype_nsec3)));
6677
6678 result = dns_rdataslab_fromrdataset(rdataset, rbtdb->common.mctx,
6679 &region, sizeof(rdatasetheader_t));
6680 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
6681 return (result);
6682 newheader = (rdatasetheader_t *)region.base;
6683 init_rdataset(rbtdb, newheader);
6684 set_ttl(rbtdb, newheader, rdataset->ttl);
6685 newheader->type = RBTDB_RDATATYPE_VALUE(rdataset->type,
6686 rdataset->covers);
6687 newheader->attributes = 0;
6688 newheader->serial = rbtversion->serial;
6689 newheader->trust = 0;
6690 newheader->noqname = NULL;
6691 newheader->closest = NULL;
6692 newheader->count = init_count++;
6693 newheader->last_used = 0;
6694 newheader->node = rbtnode;
6695 if ((rdataset->attributes & DNS_RDATASETATTR_RESIGN) != 0) {
6696 newheader->attributes |= RDATASET_ATTR_RESIGN;
6697 newheader->resign = (isc_stdtime_t)
6698 (dns_time64_from32(rdataset->resign) >> 1);
6699 newheader->resign_lsb = rdataset->resign & 0x1;
6700 } else {
6701 newheader->resign = 0;
6702 newheader->resign_lsb = 0;
6703 }
6704
6705 NODE_LOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[rbtnode->locknum].lock,
6706 isc_rwlocktype_write);
6707
6708 changed = add_changed(rbtdb, rbtversion, rbtnode);
6709 if (changed == NULL) {
6710 free_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtdb->common.mctx, newheader);
6711 NODE_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[rbtnode->locknum].lock,
6712 isc_rwlocktype_write);
6713 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
6714 }
6715
6716 topheader_prev = NULL;
6717 for (topheader = rbtnode->data;
6718 topheader != NULL;
6719 topheader = topheader->next) {
6720 if (topheader->type == newheader->type)
6721 break;
6722 topheader_prev = topheader;
6723 }
6724 /*
6725 * If header isn't NULL, we've found the right type. There may be
6726 * IGNORE rdatasets between the top of the chain and the first real
6727 * data. We skip over them.
6728 */
6729 header = topheader;
6730 while (header != NULL && IGNORE(header))
6731 header = header->down;
6732 if (header != NULL && EXISTS(header)) {
6733 unsigned int flags = 0;
6734 subresult = NULL;
6735 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
6736 if ((options & DNS_DBSUB_EXACT) != 0) {
6737 flags |= DNS_RDATASLAB_EXACT;
6738 if (newheader->rdh_ttl != header->rdh_ttl)
6739 result = DNS_R_NOTEXACT;
6740 }
6741 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
6742 result = dns_rdataslab_subtract(
6743 (unsigned char *)header,
6744 (unsigned char *)newheader,
6745 (unsigned int)(sizeof(*newheader)),
6746 rbtdb->common.mctx,
6747 rbtdb->common.rdclass,
6748 (dns_rdatatype_t)header->type,
6749 flags, &subresult);
6750 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
6751 free_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtdb->common.mctx, newheader);
6752 newheader = (rdatasetheader_t *)subresult;
6753 init_rdataset(rbtdb, newheader);
6754 update_newheader(newheader, header);
6755 if (RESIGN(header)) {
6756 newheader->attributes |= RDATASET_ATTR_RESIGN;
6757 newheader->resign = header->resign;
6758 newheader->resign_lsb = header->resign_lsb;
6759 result = resign_insert(rbtdb, rbtnode->locknum,
6760 newheader);
6761 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
6762 free_rdataset(rbtdb,
6763 rbtdb->common.mctx,
6764 newheader);
6765 goto unlock;
6766 }
6767 }
6768 /*
6769 * We have to set the serial since the rdataslab
6770 * subtraction routine copies the reserved portion of
6771 * header, not newheader.
6772 */
6773 newheader->serial = rbtversion->serial;
6774 /*
6775 * XXXJT: dns_rdataslab_subtract() copied the pointers
6776 * to additional info. We need to clear these fields
6777 * to avoid having duplicated references.
6778 */
6779 update_recordsandbytes(true, rbtversion, newheader);
6780 } else if (result == DNS_R_NXRRSET) {
6781 /*
6782 * This subtraction would remove all of the rdata;
6783 * add a nonexistent header instead.
6784 */
6785 free_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtdb->common.mctx, newheader);
6786 newheader = new_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtdb->common.mctx);
6787 if (newheader == NULL) {
6788 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
6789 goto unlock;
6790 }
6791 init_rdataset(rbtdb, newheader);
6792 set_ttl(rbtdb, newheader, 0);
6793 newheader->type = topheader->type;
6794 newheader->attributes = RDATASET_ATTR_NONEXISTENT;
6795 newheader->trust = 0;
6796 newheader->serial = rbtversion->serial;
6797 newheader->noqname = NULL;
6798 newheader->closest = NULL;
6799 newheader->count = 0;
6800 newheader->node = rbtnode;
6801 newheader->resign = 0;
6802 newheader->resign_lsb = 0;
6803 newheader->last_used = 0;
6804 } else {
6805 free_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtdb->common.mctx, newheader);
6806 goto unlock;
6807 }
6808
6809 /*
6810 * If we're here, we want to link newheader in front of
6811 * topheader.
6812 */
6813 INSIST(rbtversion->serial >= topheader->serial);
6814 update_recordsandbytes(false, rbtversion, header);
6815 if (topheader_prev != NULL)
6816 topheader_prev->next = newheader;
6817 else
6818 rbtnode->data = newheader;
6819 newheader->next = topheader->next;
6820 newheader->down = topheader;
6821 topheader->next = newheader;
6822 rbtnode->dirty = 1;
6823 changed->dirty = true;
6824 resign_delete(rbtdb, rbtversion, header);
6825 } else {
6826 /*
6827 * The rdataset doesn't exist, so we don't need to do anything
6828 * to satisfy the deletion request.
6829 */
6830 free_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtdb->common.mctx, newheader);
6831 if ((options & DNS_DBSUB_EXACT) != 0)
6832 result = DNS_R_NOTEXACT;
6833 else
6834 result = DNS_R_UNCHANGED;
6835 }
6836
6837 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS && newrdataset != NULL)
6838 bind_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtnode, newheader, 0, newrdataset);
6839
6840 if (result == DNS_R_NXRRSET && newrdataset != NULL &&
6841 (options & DNS_DBSUB_WANTOLD) != 0)
6842 bind_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtnode, header, 0, newrdataset);
6843
6844 unlock:
6845 NODE_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[rbtnode->locknum].lock,
6846 isc_rwlocktype_write);
6847
6848 /*
6849 * Update the zone's secure status. If version is non-NULL
6850 * this is deferred until closeversion() is called.
6851 */
6852 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS && version == NULL && !IS_CACHE(rbtdb))
6853 iszonesecure(db, rbtdb->current_version, rbtdb->origin_node);
6854
6855 return (result);
6856}
6857
6858static isc_result_t
6859deleterdataset(dns_db_t *db, dns_dbnode_t *node, dns_dbversion_t *version,
6860 dns_rdatatype_t type, dns_rdatatype_t covers)
6861{
6862 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
6863 dns_rbtnode_t *rbtnode = (dns_rbtnode_t *)node;
6864 rbtdb_version_t *rbtversion = version;
6865 isc_result_t result;
6866 rdatasetheader_t *newheader;
6867
6868 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
6869 INSIST(rbtversion == NULL || rbtversion->rbtdb == rbtdb);
6870
6871 if (type == dns_rdatatype_any)
6872 return (ISC_R_NOTIMPLEMENTED);
6873 if (type == dns_rdatatype_rrsig && covers == 0)
6874 return (ISC_R_NOTIMPLEMENTED);
6875
6876 newheader = new_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtdb->common.mctx);
6877 if (newheader == NULL)
6878 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
6879 init_rdataset(rbtdb, newheader);
6880 set_ttl(rbtdb, newheader, 0);
6881 newheader->type = RBTDB_RDATATYPE_VALUE(type, covers);
6882 newheader->attributes = RDATASET_ATTR_NONEXISTENT;
6883 newheader->trust = 0;
6884 newheader->noqname = NULL;
6885 newheader->closest = NULL;
6886 if (rbtversion != NULL)
6887 newheader->serial = rbtversion->serial;
6888 else
6889 newheader->serial = 0;
6890 newheader->count = 0;
6891 newheader->last_used = 0;
6892 newheader->node = rbtnode;
6893
6894 NODE_LOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[rbtnode->locknum].lock,
6895 isc_rwlocktype_write);
6896
6897 result = add32(rbtdb, rbtnode, rbtversion, newheader, DNS_DBADD_FORCE,
6898 false, NULL, 0);
6899
6900 NODE_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[rbtnode->locknum].lock,
6901 isc_rwlocktype_write);
6902
6903 /*
6904 * Update the zone's secure status. If version is non-NULL
6905 * this is deferred until closeversion() is called.
6906 */
6907 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS && version == NULL && !IS_CACHE(rbtdb))
6908 iszonesecure(db, rbtdb->current_version, rbtdb->origin_node);
6909
6910 return (result);
6911}
6912
6913/*
6914 * load a non-NSEC3 node in the main tree and optionally to the auxiliary NSEC
6915 */
6916static isc_result_t
6917loadnode(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, const dns_name_t *name, dns_rbtnode_t **nodep,
6918 bool hasnsec)
6919{
6920 isc_result_t noderesult, nsecresult, tmpresult;
6921 dns_rbtnode_t *nsecnode = NULL, *node = NULL;
6922
6923 noderesult = dns_rbt_addnode(rbtdb->tree, name, &node);
6924 if (!hasnsec)
6925 goto done;
6926 if (noderesult == ISC_R_EXISTS) {
6927 /*
6928 * Add a node to the auxiliary NSEC tree for an old node
6929 * just now getting an NSEC record.
6930 */
6931 if (node->nsec == DNS_RBT_NSEC_HAS_NSEC)
6932 goto done;
6933 } else if (noderesult != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
6934 goto done;
6935
6936 /*
6937 * Build the auxiliary tree for NSECs as we go.
6938 * This tree speeds searches for closest NSECs that would otherwise
6939 * need to examine many irrelevant nodes in large TLDs.
6940 *
6941 * Add nodes to the auxiliary tree after corresponding nodes have
6942 * been added to the main tree.
6943 */
6944 nsecresult = dns_rbt_addnode(rbtdb->nsec, name, &nsecnode);
6945 if (nsecresult == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
6946 nsecnode->nsec = DNS_RBT_NSEC_NSEC;
6947 node->nsec = DNS_RBT_NSEC_HAS_NSEC;
6948 goto done;
6949 }
6950
6951 if (nsecresult == ISC_R_EXISTS) {
6952#if 1 /* 0 */
6953 isc_log_write(dns_lctx,
6954 DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DATABASE,
6955 DNS_LOGMODULE_CACHE,
6956 ISC_LOG_WARNING,
6957 "addnode: NSEC node already exists");
6958#endif
6959 node->nsec = DNS_RBT_NSEC_HAS_NSEC;
6960 goto done;
6961 }
6962
6963 if (noderesult == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
6964
6965 /*
6966 * Remove the node we just added above.
6967 */
6968 tmpresult = dns_rbt_deletenode(rbtdb->tree, node, false);
6969 if (tmpresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
6970 isc_log_write(dns_lctx,
6971 DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DATABASE,
6972 DNS_LOGMODULE_CACHE,
6973 ISC_LOG_WARNING,
6974 "loading_addrdataset: "
6975 "dns_rbt_deletenode: %s after "
6976 "dns_rbt_addnode(NSEC): %s",
6977 isc_result_totext(tmpresult),
6978 isc_result_totext(noderesult));
6979 }
6980 }
6981
6982 /*
6983 * Set the error condition to be returned.
6984 */
6985 noderesult = nsecresult;
6986
6987 done:
6988 if (noderesult == ISC_R_SUCCESS || noderesult == ISC_R_EXISTS)
6989 *nodep = node;
6990
6991 return (noderesult);
6992}
6993
6994static isc_result_t
6995loading_addrdataset(void *arg, const dns_name_t *name,
6996 dns_rdataset_t *rdataset)
6997{
6998 rbtdb_load_t *loadctx = arg;
6999 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = loadctx->rbtdb;
7000 dns_rbtnode_t *node;
7001 isc_result_t result;
7002 isc_region_t region;
7003 rdatasetheader_t *newheader;
7004
7005 REQUIRE(rdataset->rdclass == rbtdb->common.rdclass);
7006
7007 /*
7008 * This routine does no node locking. See comments in
7009 * 'load' below for more information on loading and
7010 * locking.
7011 */
7012
7013 /*
7014 * SOA records are only allowed at top of zone.
7015 */
7016 if (rdataset->type == dns_rdatatype_soa &&
7017 !IS_CACHE(rbtdb) && !dns_name_equal(name, &rbtdb->common.origin))
7018 return (DNS_R_NOTZONETOP);
7019
7020 if (rdataset->type != dns_rdatatype_nsec3 &&
7021 rdataset->covers != dns_rdatatype_nsec3)
7022 add_empty_wildcards(rbtdb, name);
7023
7024 if (dns_name_iswildcard(name)) {
7025 /*
7026 * NS record owners cannot legally be wild cards.
7027 */
7028 if (rdataset->type == dns_rdatatype_ns)
7029 return (DNS_R_INVALIDNS);
7030 /*
7031 * NSEC3 record owners cannot legally be wild cards.
7032 */
7033 if (rdataset->type == dns_rdatatype_nsec3)
7034 return (DNS_R_INVALIDNSEC3);
7035 result = add_wildcard_magic(rbtdb, name);
7036 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
7037 return (result);
7038 }
7039
7040 node = NULL;
7041 if (rdataset->type == dns_rdatatype_nsec3 ||
7042 rdataset->covers == dns_rdatatype_nsec3) {
7043 result = dns_rbt_addnode(rbtdb->nsec3, name, &node);
7044 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
7045 node->nsec = DNS_RBT_NSEC_NSEC3;
7046 } else if (rdataset->type == dns_rdatatype_nsec) {
7047 result = loadnode(rbtdb, name, &node, true);
7048 } else {
7049 result = loadnode(rbtdb, name, &node, false);
7050 }
7051 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS && result != ISC_R_EXISTS)
7052 return (result);
7053 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
7054 dns_name_t foundname;
7055 dns_name_init(&foundname, NULL);
7056 dns_rbt_namefromnode(node, &foundname);
7057 node->locknum = node->hashval % rbtdb->node_lock_count;
7058 }
7059
7060 result = dns_rdataslab_fromrdataset(rdataset, rbtdb->common.mctx,
7061 &region,
7062 sizeof(rdatasetheader_t));
7063 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
7064 return (result);
7065 newheader = (rdatasetheader_t *)region.base;
7066 init_rdataset(rbtdb, newheader);
7067 set_ttl(rbtdb, newheader,
7068 rdataset->ttl + loadctx->now); /* XXX overflow check */
7069 newheader->type = RBTDB_RDATATYPE_VALUE(rdataset->type,
7070 rdataset->covers);
7071 newheader->attributes = 0;
7072 newheader->trust = rdataset->trust;
7073 newheader->serial = 1;
7074 newheader->noqname = NULL;
7075 newheader->closest = NULL;
7076 newheader->count = init_count++;
7077 newheader->last_used = 0;
7078 newheader->node = node;
7079 setownercase(newheader, name);
7080
7081 if ((rdataset->attributes & DNS_RDATASETATTR_RESIGN) != 0) {
7082 newheader->attributes |= RDATASET_ATTR_RESIGN;
7083 newheader->resign = (isc_stdtime_t)
7084 (dns_time64_from32(rdataset->resign) >> 1);
7085 newheader->resign_lsb = rdataset->resign & 0x1;
7086 } else {
7087 newheader->resign = 0;
7088 newheader->resign_lsb = 0;
7089 }
7090
7091 result = add32(rbtdb, node, rbtdb->current_version, newheader,
7092 DNS_DBADD_MERGE, true, NULL, 0);
7093 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS &&
7094 delegating_type(rbtdb, node, rdataset->type))
7095 node->find_callback = 1;
7096 else if (result == DNS_R_UNCHANGED)
7097 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
7098
7099 return (result);
7100}
7101
7102static isc_result_t
7103rbt_datafixer(dns_rbtnode_t *rbtnode, void *base, size_t filesize,
7104 void *arg, uint64_t *crc)
7105{
7106 isc_result_t result;
7107 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *) arg;
7108 rdatasetheader_t *header;
7109 unsigned char *limit = ((unsigned char *) base) + filesize;
7110 unsigned char *p;
7111 size_t size;
7112 unsigned int count;
7113
7114 REQUIRE(rbtnode != NULL);
7115
7116 for (header = rbtnode->data; header != NULL; header = header->next) {
7117 p = (unsigned char *) header;
7118
7119 size = dns_rdataslab_size(p, sizeof(*header));
7120 count = dns_rdataslab_count(p, sizeof(*header));;
7121 rbtdb->current_version->records += count;
7122 rbtdb->current_version->bytes += size;
7123 isc_crc64_update(crc, p, size);
7124#ifdef DEBUG
7125 hexdump("hashing header", p, sizeof(rdatasetheader_t));
7126 hexdump("hashing slab", p + sizeof(rdatasetheader_t),
7127 size - sizeof(rdatasetheader_t));
7128#endif
7129 header->serial = 1;
7130 header->is_mmapped = 1;
7131 header->node = rbtnode;
7132 header->node_is_relative = 0;
7133
7134 if (rbtdb != NULL && RESIGN(header) &&
7135 (header->resign != 0 || header->resign_lsb != 0))
7136 {
7137 int idx = header->node->locknum;
7138 result = isc_heap_insert(rbtdb->heaps[idx], header);
7139 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
7140 return (result);
7141 }
7142
7143 if (header->next != NULL) {
7144 size_t cooked = dns_rbt_serialize_align(size);
7145 if ((uintptr_t)header->next !=
7146 (p - (unsigned char *)base) + cooked)
7147 return (ISC_R_INVALIDFILE);
7148 header->next = (rdatasetheader_t *)(p + cooked);
7149 header->next_is_relative = 0;
7150 if ((header->next < (rdatasetheader_t *) base) ||
7151 (header->next > (rdatasetheader_t *) limit))
7152 return (ISC_R_INVALIDFILE);
7153 }
7154 }
7155
7156 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
7157}
7158
7159/*
7160 * Load the RBT database from the image in 'f'
7161 */
7162static isc_result_t
7163deserialize32(void *arg, FILE *f, off_t offset) {
7164 isc_result_t result;
7165 rbtdb_load_t *loadctx = arg;
7166 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = loadctx->rbtdb;
7167 rbtdb_file_header_t *header;
7168 int fd;
7169 off_t filesize = 0;
7170 char *base;
7171 dns_rbt_t *tree = NULL, *nsec = NULL, *nsec3 = NULL;
7172 int protect, flags;
7173 dns_rbtnode_t *origin_node = NULL;
7174
7175 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
7176
7177 /*
7178 * TODO CKB: since this is read-write (had to be to add nodes later)
7179 * we will need to lock the file or the nodes in it before modifying
7180 * the nodes in the file.
7181 */
7182
7183 /* Map in the whole file in one go */
7184 fd = fileno(f);
7185 isc_file_getsizefd(fd, &filesize);
7186 protect = PROT_READ|PROT_WRITE;
7187 flags = MAP_PRIVATE;
7188#ifdef MAP_FILE
7189 flags |= MAP_FILE;
7190#endif
7191
7192 base = isc_file_mmap(NULL, filesize, protect, flags, fd, 0);
7193 if (base == NULL || base == MAP_FAILED) {
7194 return (ISC_R_FAILURE);
7195 }
7196
7197 header = (rbtdb_file_header_t *)(base + offset);
7198 if (!match_header_version(header)) {
7199 result = ISC_R_INVALIDFILE;
7200 goto cleanup;
7201 }
7202
7203 if (header->tree != 0) {
7204 result = dns_rbt_deserialize_tree(base, filesize,
7205 (off_t) header->tree,
7206 rbtdb->common.mctx,
7207 delete_callback, rbtdb,
7208 rbt_datafixer, rbtdb,
7209 NULL, &tree);
7210 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
7211 goto cleanup;
7212
7213 result = dns_rbt_findnode(tree, &rbtdb->common.origin, NULL,
7214 &origin_node, NULL,
7215 DNS_RBTFIND_EMPTYDATA, NULL, NULL);
7216 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
7217 goto cleanup;
7218 }
7219
7220 if (header->nsec != 0) {
7221 result = dns_rbt_deserialize_tree(base, filesize,
7222 (off_t) header->nsec,
7223 rbtdb->common.mctx,
7224 delete_callback, rbtdb,
7225 rbt_datafixer, rbtdb,
7226 NULL, &nsec);
7227 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
7228 goto cleanup;
7229 }
7230
7231 if (header->nsec3 != 0) {
7232 result = dns_rbt_deserialize_tree(base, filesize,
7233 (off_t) header->nsec3,
7234 rbtdb->common.mctx,
7235 delete_callback, rbtdb,
7236 rbt_datafixer, rbtdb,
7237 NULL, &nsec3);
7238 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
7239 goto cleanup;
7240 }
7241
7242 /*
7243 * We have a successfully loaded all the rbt trees now update
7244 * rbtdb to use them.
7245 */
7246
7247 rbtdb->mmap_location = base;
7248 rbtdb->mmap_size = (size_t) filesize;
7249
7250 if (tree != NULL) {
7251 dns_rbt_destroy(&rbtdb->tree);
7252 rbtdb->tree = tree;
7253 rbtdb->origin_node = origin_node;
7254 }
7255
7256 if (nsec != NULL) {
7257 dns_rbt_destroy(&rbtdb->nsec);
7258 rbtdb->nsec = nsec;
7259 }
7260
7261 if (nsec3 != NULL) {
7262 dns_rbt_destroy(&rbtdb->nsec3);
7263 rbtdb->nsec3 = nsec3;
7264 }
7265
7266 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
7267
7268 cleanup:
7269 if (tree != NULL)
7270 dns_rbt_destroy(&tree);
7271 if (nsec != NULL)
7272 dns_rbt_destroy(&nsec);
7273 if (nsec3 != NULL)
7274 dns_rbt_destroy(&nsec3);
7275 isc_file_munmap(base, (size_t) filesize);
7276 return (result);
7277}
7278
7279static isc_result_t
7280beginload(dns_db_t *db, dns_rdatacallbacks_t *callbacks) {
7281 rbtdb_load_t *loadctx;
7282 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb;
7283 rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
7284
7285 REQUIRE(DNS_CALLBACK_VALID(callbacks));
7286 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
7287
7288 loadctx = isc_mem_get(rbtdb->common.mctx, sizeof(*loadctx));
7289 if (loadctx == NULL)
7290 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
7291
7292 loadctx->rbtdb = rbtdb;
7293 if (IS_CACHE(rbtdb))
7294 isc_stdtime_get(&loadctx->now);
7295 else
7296 loadctx->now = 0;
7297
7298 RBTDB_LOCK(&rbtdb->lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
7299
7300 REQUIRE((rbtdb->attributes & (RBTDB_ATTR_LOADED|RBTDB_ATTR_LOADING))
7301 == 0);
7302 rbtdb->attributes |= RBTDB_ATTR_LOADING;
7303
7304 RBTDB_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
7305
7306 callbacks->add = loading_addrdataset;
7307 callbacks->add_private = loadctx;
7308 callbacks->deserialize = deserialize32;
7309 callbacks->deserialize_private = loadctx;
7310
7311 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
7312}
7313
7314static isc_result_t
7315endload(dns_db_t *db, dns_rdatacallbacks_t *callbacks) {
7316 rbtdb_load_t *loadctx;
7317 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
7318
7319 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
7320 REQUIRE(DNS_CALLBACK_VALID(callbacks));
7321 loadctx = callbacks->add_private;
7322 REQUIRE(loadctx != NULL);
7323 REQUIRE(loadctx->rbtdb == rbtdb);
7324
7325 RBTDB_LOCK(&rbtdb->lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
7326
7327 REQUIRE((rbtdb->attributes & RBTDB_ATTR_LOADING) != 0);
7328 REQUIRE((rbtdb->attributes & RBTDB_ATTR_LOADED) == 0);
7329
7330 rbtdb->attributes &= ~RBTDB_ATTR_LOADING;
7331 rbtdb->attributes |= RBTDB_ATTR_LOADED;
7332
7333 RBTDB_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
7334
7335 /*
7336 * If there's a KEY rdataset at the zone origin containing a
7337 * zone key, we consider the zone secure.
7338 */
7339 if (! IS_CACHE(rbtdb) && rbtdb->origin_node != NULL)
7340 iszonesecure(db, rbtdb->current_version, rbtdb->origin_node);
7341
7342 callbacks->add = NULL;
7343 callbacks->add_private = NULL;
7344 callbacks->deserialize = NULL;
7345 callbacks->deserialize_private = NULL;
7346
7347 isc_mem_put(rbtdb->common.mctx, loadctx, sizeof(*loadctx));
7348
7349 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
7350}
7351
7352/*
7353 * helper function to handle writing out the rdataset data pointed to
7354 * by the void *data pointer in the dns_rbtnode
7355 */
7356static isc_result_t
7357rbt_datawriter(FILE *rbtfile, unsigned char *data, void *arg,
7358 uint64_t *crc)
7359{
7360 rbtdb_version_t *version = (rbtdb_version_t *) arg;
7361 rbtdb_serial_t serial;
7362 rdatasetheader_t newheader;
7363 rdatasetheader_t *header = (rdatasetheader_t *) data, *next;
7364 off_t where;
7365 size_t cooked, size;
7366 unsigned char *p;
7367 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
7368 char pad[sizeof(char *)];
7369 uintptr_t off;
7370
7371 REQUIRE(rbtfile != NULL);
7372 REQUIRE(data != NULL);
7373 REQUIRE(version != NULL);
7374
7375 serial = version->serial;
7376
7377 for (; header != NULL; header = next) {
7378 next = header->next;
7379 do {
7380 if (header->serial <= serial && !IGNORE(header)) {
7381 if (NONEXISTENT(header))
7382 header = NULL;
7383 break;
7384 } else
7385 header = header->down;
7386 } while (header != NULL);
7387
7388 if (header == NULL)
7389 continue;
7390
7391 CHECK(isc_stdio_tell(rbtfile, &where));
7392 size = dns_rdataslab_size((unsigned char *) header,
7393 sizeof(rdatasetheader_t));
7394
7395 p = (unsigned char *) header;
7396 memmove(&newheader, p, sizeof(rdatasetheader_t));
7397 newheader.down = NULL;
7398 newheader.next = NULL;
7399 off = where;
7400 if ((off_t)off != where)
7401 return (ISC_R_RANGE);
7402 newheader.node = (dns_rbtnode_t *) off;
7403 newheader.node_is_relative = 1;
7404 newheader.serial = 1;
7405
7406 /*
7407 * Round size up to the next pointer sized offset so it
7408 * will be properly aligned when read back in.
7409 */
7410 cooked = dns_rbt_serialize_align(size);
7411 if (next != NULL) {
7412 newheader.next = (rdatasetheader_t *) (off + cooked);
7413 newheader.next_is_relative = 1;
7414 }
7415
7416#ifdef DEBUG
7417 hexdump("writing header", (unsigned char *) &newheader,
7418 sizeof(rdatasetheader_t));
7419 hexdump("writing slab", p + sizeof(rdatasetheader_t),
7420 size - sizeof(rdatasetheader_t));
7421#endif
7422 isc_crc64_update(crc, (unsigned char *) &newheader,
7423 sizeof(rdatasetheader_t));
7424 CHECK(isc_stdio_write(&newheader, sizeof(rdatasetheader_t), 1,
7425 rbtfile, NULL));
7426
7427 isc_crc64_update(crc, p + sizeof(rdatasetheader_t),
7428 size - sizeof(rdatasetheader_t));
7429 CHECK(isc_stdio_write(p + sizeof(rdatasetheader_t),
7430 size - sizeof(rdatasetheader_t), 1,
7431 rbtfile, NULL));
7432 /*
7433 * Pad to force alignment.
7434 */
7435 if (size != (size_t) cooked) {
7436 memset(pad, 0, sizeof(pad));
7437 CHECK(isc_stdio_write(pad, cooked - size, 1,
7438 rbtfile, NULL));
7439 }
7440 }
7441
7442 failure:
7443 return (result);
7444}
7445
7446/*
7447 * Write out a zeroed header as a placeholder. Doing this ensures
7448 * that the file will not read while it is partially written, should
7449 * writing fail or be interrupted.
7450 */
7451static isc_result_t
7452rbtdb_zero_header(FILE *rbtfile) {
7453 char buffer[RBTDB_HEADER_LENGTH];
7454 isc_result_t result;
7455
7456 memset(buffer, 0, RBTDB_HEADER_LENGTH);
7457 result = isc_stdio_write(buffer, 1, RBTDB_HEADER_LENGTH, rbtfile, NULL);
7458 fflush(rbtfile);
7459
7460 return (result);
7461}
7462
7463static isc_once_t once = ISC_ONCE_INIT;
7464
7465static void
7466init_file_version(void) {
7467 int n;
7468
7469 memset(FILE_VERSION, 0, sizeof(FILE_VERSION));
7470 n = snprintf(FILE_VERSION, sizeof(FILE_VERSION),
7471 "RBTDB Image %s %s", dns_major, dns_mapapi);
7472 INSIST(n > 0 && (unsigned int)n < sizeof(FILE_VERSION));
7473}
7474
7475/*
7476 * Write the file header out, recording the locations of the three
7477 * RBT's used in the rbtdb: tree, nsec, and nsec3, and including NodeDump
7478 * version information and any information stored in the rbtdb object
7479 * itself that should be stored here.
7480 */
7481static isc_result_t
7482rbtdb_write_header(FILE *rbtfile, off_t tree_location, off_t nsec_location,
7483 off_t nsec3_location)
7484{
7485 rbtdb_file_header_t header;
7486 isc_result_t result;
7487
7488 RUNTIME_CHECK(isc_once_do(&once, init_file_version) == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
7489
7490 memset(&header, 0, sizeof(rbtdb_file_header_t));
7491 memmove(header.version1, FILE_VERSION, sizeof(header.version1));
7492 memmove(header.version2, FILE_VERSION, sizeof(header.version2));
7493 header.ptrsize = (uint32_t) sizeof(void *);
7494 header.bigendian = (1 == htonl(1)) ? 1 : 0;
7495 header.tree = (uint64_t) tree_location;
7496 header.nsec = (uint64_t) nsec_location;
7497 header.nsec3 = (uint64_t) nsec3_location;
7498 result = isc_stdio_write(&header, 1, sizeof(rbtdb_file_header_t),
7499 rbtfile, NULL);
7500 fflush(rbtfile);
7501
7502 return (result);
7503}
7504
7505static bool
7506match_header_version(rbtdb_file_header_t *header) {
7507 RUNTIME_CHECK(isc_once_do(&once, init_file_version) == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
7508
7509 if (memcmp(header->version1, FILE_VERSION,
7510 sizeof(header->version1)) != 0 ||
7511 memcmp(header->version2, FILE_VERSION,
7512 sizeof(header->version1)) != 0)
7513 {
7514 return (false);
7515 }
7516
7517 return (true);
7518}
7519
7520static isc_result_t
7521serialize(dns_db_t *db, dns_dbversion_t *ver, FILE *rbtfile) {
7522 rbtdb_version_t *version = (rbtdb_version_t *) ver;
7523 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb;
7524 isc_result_t result;
7525 off_t tree_location, nsec_location, nsec3_location, header_location;
7526
7527 rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
7528
7529 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
7530 REQUIRE(rbtfile != NULL);
7531
7532 /* Ensure we're writing to a plain file */
7533 CHECK(isc_file_isplainfilefd(fileno(rbtfile)));
7534
7535 /*
7536 * first, write out a zeroed header to store rbtdb information
7537 *
7538 * then for each of the three trees, store the current position
7539 * in the file and call dns_rbt_serialize_tree
7540 *
7541 * finally, write out the rbtdb header, storing the locations of the
7542 * rbtheaders
7543 *
7544 * NOTE: need to do something better with the return codes, &= will
7545 * not work.
7546 */
7547 CHECK(isc_stdio_tell(rbtfile, &header_location));
7548 CHECK(rbtdb_zero_header(rbtfile));
7549 CHECK(dns_rbt_serialize_tree(rbtfile, rbtdb->tree, rbt_datawriter,
7550 version, &tree_location));
7551 CHECK(dns_rbt_serialize_tree(rbtfile, rbtdb->nsec, rbt_datawriter,
7552 version, &nsec_location));
7553 CHECK(dns_rbt_serialize_tree(rbtfile, rbtdb->nsec3, rbt_datawriter,
7554 version, &nsec3_location));
7555
7556 CHECK(isc_stdio_seek(rbtfile, header_location, SEEK_SET));
7557 CHECK(rbtdb_write_header(rbtfile, tree_location, nsec_location,
7558 nsec3_location));
7559 failure:
7560 return (result);
7561}
7562
7563static isc_result_t
7564dump(dns_db_t *db, dns_dbversion_t *version, const char *filename,
7565 dns_masterformat_t masterformat)
7566{
7567 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb;
7568 rbtdb_version_t *rbtversion = version;
7569
7570 rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
7571
7572 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
7573 INSIST(rbtversion == NULL || rbtversion->rbtdb == rbtdb);
7574
7575 return (dns_master_dump(rbtdb->common.mctx, db, version,
7576 &dns_master_style_default,
7577 filename, masterformat, NULL));
7578}
7579
7580static void
7581delete_callback(void *data, void *arg) {
7582 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = arg;
7583 rdatasetheader_t *current, *next;
7584 unsigned int locknum;
7585
7586 current = data;
7587 locknum = current->node->locknum;
7588 NODE_LOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[locknum].lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
7589 while (current != NULL) {
7590 next = current->next;
7591 free_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtdb->common.mctx, current);
7592 current = next;
7593 }
7594 NODE_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[locknum].lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
7595}
7596
7597static bool
7598issecure(dns_db_t *db) {
7599 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb;
7600 bool secure;
7601
7602 rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
7603
7604 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
7605
7606 RWLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
7607 secure = (rbtdb->current_version->secure == dns_db_secure);
7608 RWUNLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
7609
7610 return (secure);
7611}
7612
7613static bool
7614isdnssec(dns_db_t *db) {
7615 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb;
7616 bool dnssec;
7617
7618 rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
7619
7620 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
7621
7622 RWLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
7623 dnssec = (rbtdb->current_version->secure != dns_db_insecure);
7624 RWUNLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
7625
7626 return (dnssec);
7627}

7629static unsigned int
7630nodecount(dns_db_t *db) {
7631 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb;
7632 unsigned int count;
7633
7634 rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
7635
7636 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
7637
7638 RWLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
7639 count = dns_rbt_nodecount(rbtdb->tree);
7640 RWUNLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
7641
7642 return (count);
7643}

7645static size_t
7646hashsize(dns_db_t *db) {
7647 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb;
7648 size_t size;
7649
7650 rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
7651
7652 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
7653
7654 RWLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
7655 size = dns_rbt_hashsize(rbtdb->tree);
7656 RWUNLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
7657
7658 return (size);
7659}

7661static void
7662settask(dns_db_t *db, isc_task_t *task) {
7663 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb;
7664
7665 rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
7666
7667 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
7668
7669 RBTDB_LOCK(&rbtdb->lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
7670 if (rbtdb->task != NULL)
7671 isc_task_detach(&rbtdb->task);
7672 if (task != NULL)
7673 isc_task_attach(task, &rbtdb->task);
7674 RBTDB_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
7675}

7677static bool
7678ispersistent(dns_db_t *db) {
7679 UNUSED(db);
7680 return (false);
7681}
7682
7683static isc_result_t
7684getoriginnode(dns_db_t *db, dns_dbnode_t **nodep) {
7685 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
7686 dns_rbtnode_t *onode;
7687 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
7688
7689 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
7690 REQUIRE(nodep != NULL && *nodep == NULL);
7691
7692 /* Note that the access to origin_node doesn't require a DB lock */
7693 onode = (dns_rbtnode_t *)rbtdb->origin_node;
7694 if (onode != NULL) {
7695 new_reference(rbtdb, onode);
7696
7697 *nodep = rbtdb->origin_node;
7698 } else {
7699 INSIST(IS_CACHE(rbtdb));
7700 result = ISC_R_NOTFOUND;
7701 }
7702
7703 return (result);
7704}
7705
7706static isc_result_t
7707getnsec3parameters(dns_db_t *db, dns_dbversion_t *version, dns_hash_t *hash,
7708 uint8_t *flags, uint16_t *iterations,
7709 unsigned char *salt, size_t *salt_length)
7710{
7711 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb;
7712 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_NOTFOUND;
7713 rbtdb_version_t *rbtversion = version;
7714
7715 rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
7716
7717 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
7718 INSIST(rbtversion == NULL || rbtversion->rbtdb == rbtdb);
7719
7720 RWLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
7721
7722 if (rbtversion == NULL)
7723 rbtversion = rbtdb->current_version;
7724
7725 if (rbtversion->havensec3) {
7726 if (hash != NULL)
7727 *hash = rbtversion->hash;
7728 if (salt != NULL && salt_length != NULL) {
7729 REQUIRE(*salt_length >= rbtversion->salt_length);
7730 memmove(salt, rbtversion->salt,
7731 rbtversion->salt_length);
7732 }
7733 if (salt_length != NULL)
7734 *salt_length = rbtversion->salt_length;
7735 if (iterations != NULL)
7736 *iterations = rbtversion->iterations;
7737 if (flags != NULL)
7738 *flags = rbtversion->flags;
7739 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
7740 }
7741 RWUNLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
7742
7743 return (result);
7744}
7745
7746static isc_result_t
7747getsize(dns_db_t *db, dns_dbversion_t *version, uint64_t *records,
7748 uint64_t *bytes)
7749{
7750 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb;
7751 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
7752 rbtdb_version_t *rbtversion = version;
7753
7754 rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
7755
7756 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
7757 INSIST(rbtversion == NULL || rbtversion->rbtdb == rbtdb);
7758
7759 if (rbtversion == NULL)
7760 rbtversion = rbtdb->current_version;
7761
7762 RWLOCK(&rbtversion->rwlock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
7763 if (records != NULL)
7764 *records = rbtversion->records;
7765
7766 if (bytes != NULL)
7767 *bytes = rbtversion->bytes;
7768 RWUNLOCK(&rbtversion->rwlock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
7769
7770 return (result);
7771}
7772
7773static isc_result_t
7774setsigningtime(dns_db_t *db, dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, isc_stdtime_t resign) {
7775 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
7776 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
7777 rdatasetheader_t *header, oldheader;
7778
7779 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
7780 REQUIRE(!IS_CACHE(rbtdb));
7781 REQUIRE(rdataset != NULL);
7782
7783 header = rdataset->private3;
7784 header--;
7785
7786 NODE_LOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[header->node->locknum].lock,
7787 isc_rwlocktype_write);
7788
7789 oldheader = *header;
7790 /*
7791 * Only break the heap invariant (by adjusting resign and resign_lsb)
7792 * if we are going to be restoring it by calling isc_heap_increased
7793 * or isc_heap_decreased.
7794 */
7795 if (resign != 0) {
7796 header->resign =
7797 (isc_stdtime_t)(dns_time64_from32(resign) >> 1);
7798 header->resign_lsb = resign & 0x1;
7799 }
7800 if (header->heap_index != 0) {
7801 INSIST(RESIGN(header));
7802 if (resign == 0) {
7803 isc_heap_delete(rbtdb->heaps[header->node->locknum],
7804 header->heap_index);
7805 header->heap_index = 0;
7806 } else if (resign_sooner(header, &oldheader)) {
7807 isc_heap_increased(rbtdb->heaps[header->node->locknum],
7808 header->heap_index);
7809 } else if (resign_sooner(&oldheader, header)) {
7810 isc_heap_decreased(rbtdb->heaps[header->node->locknum],
7811 header->heap_index);
7812 }
7813 } else if (resign != 0) {
7814 header->attributes |= RDATASET_ATTR_RESIGN;
7815 result = resign_insert(rbtdb, header->node->locknum, header);
7816 }
7817 NODE_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[header->node->locknum].lock,
7818 isc_rwlocktype_write);
7819 return (result);
7820}
7821
7822static isc_result_t
7823getsigningtime(dns_db_t *db, dns_rdataset_t *rdataset,
7824 dns_name_t *foundname)
7825{
7826 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
7827 rdatasetheader_t *header = NULL, *this;
7828 unsigned int i;
7829 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_NOTFOUND;
7830 unsigned int locknum;
7831
7832 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
7833
7834 RWLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
7835
7836 for (i = 0; i < rbtdb->node_lock_count; i++) {
7837 NODE_LOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[i].lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
7838 this = isc_heap_element(rbtdb->heaps[i], 1);
7839 if (this == NULL) {
7840 NODE_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[i].lock,
7841 isc_rwlocktype_read);
7842 continue;
7843 }
7844 if (header == NULL)
7845 header = this;
7846 else if (resign_sooner(this, header)) {
7847 locknum = header->node->locknum;
7848 NODE_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[locknum].lock,
7849 isc_rwlocktype_read);
7850 header = this;
7851 } else
7852 NODE_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[i].lock,
7853 isc_rwlocktype_read);
7854 }
7855
7856 if (header == NULL)
7857 goto unlock;
7858
7859 bind_rdataset(rbtdb, header->node, header, 0, rdataset);
7860
7861 if (foundname != NULL)
7862 dns_rbt_fullnamefromnode(header->node, foundname);
7863
7864 NODE_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[header->node->locknum].lock,
7865 isc_rwlocktype_read);
7866
7867 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
7868
7869 unlock:
7870 RWUNLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
7871
7872 return (result);
7873}
7874
7875static void
7876resigned(dns_db_t *db, dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, dns_dbversion_t *version)
7877{
7878 rbtdb_version_t *rbtversion = (rbtdb_version_t *)version;
7879 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
7880 dns_rbtnode_t *node;
7881 rdatasetheader_t *header;
7882
7883 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
7884 REQUIRE(rdataset != NULL);
7885 REQUIRE(rdataset->methods == &rdataset_methods);
7886 REQUIRE(rbtdb->future_version == rbtversion);
7887 REQUIRE(rbtversion != NULL);
7888 REQUIRE(rbtversion->writer);
7889 REQUIRE(rbtversion->rbtdb == rbtdb);
7890
7891 node = rdataset->private2;
7892 INSIST(node != NULL);
7893 header = rdataset->private3;
7894 INSIST(header != NULL);
7895 header--;
7896
7897 if (header->heap_index == 0)
7898 return;
7899
7900 RWLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
7901 NODE_LOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[node->locknum].lock,
7902 isc_rwlocktype_write);
7903 /*
7904 * Delete from heap and save to re-signed list so that it can
7905 * be restored if we backout of this change.
7906 */
7907 resign_delete(rbtdb, rbtversion, header);
7908 NODE_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[node->locknum].lock,
7909 isc_rwlocktype_write);
7910 RWUNLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
7911}
7912

7915 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
7916
7917 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
7918 REQUIRE(IS_CACHE(rbtdb)); /* current restriction */
7919 REQUIRE(stats != NULL);
7920
7921 isc_stats_attach(stats, &rbtdb->cachestats);
7922 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
7923}

7947static isc_result_t
7948nodefullname(dns_db_t *db, dns_dbnode_t *node, dns_name_t *name) {
7949 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)db;
7950 dns_rbtnode_t *rbtnode = (dns_rbtnode_t *)node;
7951 isc_result_t result;
7952
7953 REQUIRE(VALID_RBTDB(rbtdb));
7954 REQUIRE(node != NULL);
7955 REQUIRE(name != NULL);
7956
7957 RWLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
7958 result = dns_rbt_fullnamefromnode(rbtnode, name);
7959 RWUNLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
7960
7961 return (result);
7962}

7973 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);

7983 *ttl = rbtdb->serve_stale_ttl;
7984 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
