8089
8090isc_result_t
8091dns_rbtdb_create(isc_mem_t *mctx, const dns_name_t *origin, dns_dbtype_t type,
8092 dns_rdataclass_t rdclass, unsigned int argc, char *argv[],
8093 void *driverarg, dns_db_t **dbp)
8094{
8095 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb;
8096 isc_result_t result;
8097 int i;
8098 dns_name_t name;
8099 bool (*sooner)(void *, void *);
8100 isc_mem_t *hmctx = mctx;
8101
8102 /* Keep the compiler happy. */
8103 UNUSED(driverarg);
8104
8105 rbtdb = isc_mem_get(mctx, sizeof(*rbtdb));
8106 if (rbtdb == NULL)
8107 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
8108
8109 /*
8110 * If argv[0] exists, it points to a memory context to use for heap
8111 */
8112 if (argc != 0)
8113 hmctx = (isc_mem_t *) argv[0];
8114
8115 memset(rbtdb, '\0', sizeof(*rbtdb));
8116 dns_name_init(&rbtdb->common.origin, NULL);
8117 rbtdb->common.attributes = 0;
8118 if (type == dns_dbtype_cache) {
8119 rbtdb->common.methods = &cache_methods;
8120 rbtdb->common.attributes |= DNS_DBATTR_CACHE;
8121 } else if (type == dns_dbtype_stub) {
8122 rbtdb->common.methods = &zone_methods;
8123 rbtdb->common.attributes |= DNS_DBATTR_STUB;
8124 } else
8125 rbtdb->common.methods = &zone_methods;
8126 rbtdb->common.rdclass = rdclass;
8127 rbtdb->common.mctx = NULL;
8128
8129 ISC_LIST_INIT(rbtdb->common.update_listeners);
8130
8131 result = RBTDB_INITLOCK(&rbtdb->lock);
8132 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
8133 goto cleanup_rbtdb;
8134
8135 result = isc_rwlock_init(&rbtdb->tree_lock, 0, 0);
8136 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
8137 goto cleanup_lock;
8138
8139 /*
8140 * Initialize node_lock_count in a generic way to support future
8141 * extension which allows the user to specify this value on creation.
8142 * Note that when specified for a cache DB it must be larger than 1
8143 * as commented with the definition of DEFAULT_CACHE_NODE_LOCK_COUNT.
8144 */
8145 if (rbtdb->node_lock_count == 0) {
8146 if (IS_CACHE(rbtdb))
8147 rbtdb->node_lock_count = DEFAULT_CACHE_NODE_LOCK_COUNT;
8148 else
8149 rbtdb->node_lock_count = DEFAULT_NODE_LOCK_COUNT;
8150 } else if (rbtdb->node_lock_count < 2 && IS_CACHE(rbtdb)) {
8151 result = ISC_R_RANGE;
8152 goto cleanup_tree_lock;
8153 }
8154 INSIST(rbtdb->node_lock_count < (1 << DNS_RBT_LOCKLENGTH));
8155 rbtdb->node_locks = isc_mem_get(mctx, rbtdb->node_lock_count *
8156 sizeof(rbtdb_nodelock_t));
8157 if (rbtdb->node_locks == NULL) {
8158 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
8159 goto cleanup_tree_lock;
8160 }
8161
8162 rbtdb->cachestats = NULL;
8163 rbtdb->gluecachestats = NULL;
8164
8165 rbtdb->rrsetstats = NULL;
8166 if (IS_CACHE(rbtdb)) {
8167 result = dns_rdatasetstats_create(mctx, &rbtdb->rrsetstats);
8168 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
8169 goto cleanup_node_locks;
8170 rbtdb->rdatasets = isc_mem_get(mctx, rbtdb->node_lock_count *
8171 sizeof(rdatasetheaderlist_t));
8172 if (rbtdb->rdatasets == NULL) {
8173 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
8174 goto cleanup_rrsetstats;
8175 }
8176 for (i = 0; i < (int)rbtdb->node_lock_count; i++)
8177 ISC_LIST_INIT(rbtdb->rdatasets[i]);
8178 } else
8179 rbtdb->rdatasets = NULL;
8180
8181 /*
8182 * Create the heaps.
8183 */
8184 rbtdb->heaps = isc_mem_get(hmctx, rbtdb->node_lock_count *
8185 sizeof(isc_heap_t *));
8186 if (rbtdb->heaps == NULL) {
8187 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
8188 goto cleanup_rdatasets;
8189 }
8190 for (i = 0; i < (int)rbtdb->node_lock_count; i++)
8191 rbtdb->heaps[i] = NULL;
8192 sooner = IS_CACHE(rbtdb) ? ttl_sooner : resign_sooner;
8193 for (i = 0; i < (int)rbtdb->node_lock_count; i++) {
8194 result = isc_heap_create(hmctx, sooner, set_index, 0,
8195 &rbtdb->heaps[i]);
8196 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
8197 goto cleanup_heaps;
8198 }
8199
8200 /*
8201 * Create deadnode lists.
8202 */
8203 rbtdb->deadnodes = isc_mem_get(mctx, rbtdb->node_lock_count *
8204 sizeof(rbtnodelist_t));
8205 if (rbtdb->deadnodes == NULL) {
8206 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
8207 goto cleanup_heaps;
8208 }
8209 for (i = 0; i < (int)rbtdb->node_lock_count; i++)
8210 ISC_LIST_INIT(rbtdb->deadnodes[i]);
8211
8212 rbtdb->active = rbtdb->node_lock_count;
8213
8214 for (i = 0; i < (int)(rbtdb->node_lock_count); i++) {
8215 result = NODE_INITLOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[i].lock);
8216 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
8217 isc_refcount_init(&rbtdb->node_locks[i].references, 0);
8218 }
8219 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
8220 while (i-- > 0) {
8221 NODE_DESTROYLOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[i].lock);
8222 isc_refcount_destroy(&rbtdb->node_locks[i].references);
8223 }
8224 goto cleanup_deadnodes;
8225 }
8226 rbtdb->node_locks[i].exiting = false;
8227 }
8228
8229 /*
8230 * Attach to the mctx. The database will persist so long as there
8231 * are references to it, and attaching to the mctx ensures that our
8232 * mctx won't disappear out from under us.
8233 */
8234 isc_mem_attach(mctx, &rbtdb->common.mctx);
8235 isc_mem_attach(hmctx, &rbtdb->hmctx);
8236
8237 /*
8238 * Make a copy of the origin name.
8239 */
8240 result = dns_name_dupwithoffsets(origin, mctx, &rbtdb->common.origin);
8241 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
8242 free_rbtdb(rbtdb, false, NULL);
8243 return (result);
8244 }
8245
8246 /*
8247 * Make the Red-Black Trees.
8248 */
8249 result = dns_rbt_create(mctx, delete_callback, rbtdb, &rbtdb->tree);
8250 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
8251 free_rbtdb(rbtdb, false, NULL);
8252 return (result);
8253 }
8254
8255 result = dns_rbt_create(mctx, delete_callback, rbtdb, &rbtdb->nsec);
8256 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
8257 free_rbtdb(rbtdb, false, NULL);
8258 return (result);
8259 }
8260
8261 result = dns_rbt_create(mctx, delete_callback, rbtdb, &rbtdb->nsec3);
8262 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
8263 free_rbtdb(rbtdb, false, NULL);
8264 return (result);
8265 }
8266
8267 /*
8268 * In order to set the node callback bit correctly in zone databases,
8269 * we need to know if the node has the origin name of the zone.
8270 * In loading_addrdataset() we could simply compare the new name
8271 * to the origin name, but this is expensive. Also, we don't know the
8272 * node name in addrdataset(), so we need another way of knowing the
8273 * zone's top.
8274 *
8275 * We now explicitly create a node for the zone's origin, and then
8276 * we simply remember the node's address. This is safe, because
8277 * the top-of-zone node can never be deleted, nor can its address
8278 * change.
8279 */
8280 if (!IS_CACHE(rbtdb)) {
8281 rbtdb->origin_node = NULL;
8282 result = dns_rbt_addnode(rbtdb->tree, &rbtdb->common.origin,
8283 &rbtdb->origin_node);
8284 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
8285 INSIST(result != ISC_R_EXISTS);
8286 free_rbtdb(rbtdb, false, NULL);
8287 return (result);
8288 }
8289 INSIST(rbtdb->origin_node != NULL);
8290 rbtdb->origin_node->nsec = DNS_RBT_NSEC_NORMAL;
8291 /*
8292 * We need to give the origin node the right locknum.
8293 */
8294 dns_name_init(&name, NULL);
8295 dns_rbt_namefromnode(rbtdb->origin_node, &name);
8296 rbtdb->origin_node->locknum =
8297 rbtdb->origin_node->hashval %
8298 rbtdb->node_lock_count;
8299 /*
8300 * Add an apex node to the NSEC3 tree so that NSEC3 searches
8301 * return partial matches when there is only a single NSEC3
8302 * record in the tree.
8303 */
8304 rbtdb->nsec3_origin_node = NULL;
8305 result = dns_rbt_addnode(rbtdb->nsec3, &rbtdb->common.origin,
8306 &rbtdb->nsec3_origin_node);
8307 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
8308 INSIST(result != ISC_R_EXISTS);
8309 free_rbtdb(rbtdb, false, NULL);
8310 return (result);
8311 }
8312 rbtdb->nsec3_origin_node->nsec = DNS_RBT_NSEC_NSEC3;
8313 /*
8314 * We need to give the nsec3 origin node the right locknum.
8315 */
8316 dns_name_init(&name, NULL);
8317 dns_rbt_namefromnode(rbtdb->nsec3_origin_node, &name);
8318 rbtdb->nsec3_origin_node->locknum =
8319 rbtdb->nsec3_origin_node->hashval %
8320 rbtdb->node_lock_count;
8321 }
8322
8323 /*
8324 * Misc. Initialization.
8325 */
8326 isc_refcount_init(&rbtdb->references, 1);
8327 rbtdb->attributes = 0;
8328 rbtdb->task = NULL;
8329 rbtdb->serve_stale_ttl = 0;
8330
8331 /*
8332 * Version Initialization.
8333 */
8334 rbtdb->current_serial = 1;
8335 rbtdb->least_serial = 1;
8336 rbtdb->next_serial = 2;
8337 rbtdb->current_version = allocate_version(mctx, 1, 1, false);
8338 if (rbtdb->current_version == NULL) {
8339 INSIST(isc_refcount_decrement(&rbtdb->references) > 0);
8340 free_rbtdb(rbtdb, false, NULL);
8341 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
8342 }
8343 rbtdb->current_version->rbtdb = rbtdb;
8344 rbtdb->current_version->secure = dns_db_insecure;
8345 rbtdb->current_version->havensec3 = false;
8346 rbtdb->current_version->flags = 0;
8347 rbtdb->current_version->iterations = 0;
8348 rbtdb->current_version->hash = 0;
8349 rbtdb->current_version->salt_length = 0;
8350 memset(rbtdb->current_version->salt, 0,
8351 sizeof(rbtdb->current_version->salt));
8352 result = isc_rwlock_init(&rbtdb->current_version->rwlock, 0, 0);
8353 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
8354 free_gluetable(rbtdb->current_version);
8355 isc_rwlock_destroy(&rbtdb->current_version->glue_rwlock);
8356 isc_refcount_destroy(&rbtdb->current_version->references);
8357 isc_mem_put(mctx, rbtdb->current_version,
8358 sizeof(*rbtdb->current_version));
8359 rbtdb->current_version = NULL;
8360 INSIST(isc_refcount_decrement(&rbtdb->references) > 0);
8361 free_rbtdb(rbtdb, false, NULL);
8362 return (result);
8363 }
8364
8365 rbtdb->current_version->records = 0;
8366 rbtdb->current_version->bytes = 0;
8367 rbtdb->future_version = NULL;
8368 ISC_LIST_INIT(rbtdb->open_versions);
8369 /*
8370 * Keep the current version in the open list so that list operation
8371 * won't happen in normal lookup operations.
8372 */
8373 PREPEND(rbtdb->open_versions, rbtdb->current_version, link);
8374
8375 rbtdb->common.magic = DNS_DB_MAGIC;
8376 rbtdb->common.impmagic = RBTDB_MAGIC;
8377
8378 *dbp = (dns_db_t *)rbtdb;
8379
8380 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
8381
8382 cleanup_deadnodes:
8383 isc_mem_put(mctx, rbtdb->deadnodes,
8384 rbtdb->node_lock_count * sizeof(rbtnodelist_t));
8385
8386 cleanup_heaps:
8387 if (rbtdb->heaps != NULL) {
8388 for (i = 0 ; i < (int)rbtdb->node_lock_count ; i++)
8389 if (rbtdb->heaps[i] != NULL)
8390 isc_heap_destroy(&rbtdb->heaps[i]);
8391 isc_mem_put(hmctx, rbtdb->heaps,
8392 rbtdb->node_lock_count * sizeof(isc_heap_t *));
8393 }
8394
8395 cleanup_rdatasets:
8396 if (rbtdb->rdatasets != NULL)
8397 isc_mem_put(mctx, rbtdb->rdatasets, rbtdb->node_lock_count *
8398 sizeof(rdatasetheaderlist_t));
8399 cleanup_rrsetstats:
8400 if (rbtdb->rrsetstats != NULL)
8401 dns_stats_detach(&rbtdb->rrsetstats);
8402
8403 cleanup_node_locks:
8404 isc_mem_put(mctx, rbtdb->node_locks,
8405 rbtdb->node_lock_count * sizeof(rbtdb_nodelock_t));
8406
8407 cleanup_tree_lock:
8408 isc_rwlock_destroy(&rbtdb->tree_lock);
8409
8410 cleanup_lock:
8411 RBTDB_DESTROYLOCK(&rbtdb->lock);
8412
8413 cleanup_rbtdb:
8414 isc_mem_put(mctx, rbtdb, sizeof(*rbtdb));
8415 return (result);
8416}
8417
8418
8419/*
8420 * Slabbed Rdataset Methods
8421 */
8422
8423static void
8424rdataset_disassociate(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset) {
8425 dns_db_t *db = rdataset->private1;
8426 dns_dbnode_t *node = rdataset->private2;
8427
8428 detachnode(db, &node);
8429}
8430
8431static isc_result_t
8432rdataset_first(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset) {
8433 unsigned char *raw = rdataset->private3; /* RDATASLAB */
8434 unsigned int count;
8435
8436 count = raw[0] * 256 + raw[1];
8437 if (count == 0) {
8438 rdataset->private5 = NULL;
8439 return (ISC_R_NOMORE);
8440 }
8441
8442#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
8443 if ((rdataset->attributes & DNS_RDATASETATTR_LOADORDER) == 0)
8444 raw += 2 + (4 * count);
8445 else
8446#endif
8447 raw += 2;
8448
8449 /*
8450 * The privateuint4 field is the number of rdata beyond the
8451 * cursor position, so we decrement the total count by one
8452 * before storing it.
8453 *
8454 * If DNS_RDATASETATTR_LOADORDER is not set 'raw' points to the
8455 * first record. If DNS_RDATASETATTR_LOADORDER is set 'raw' points
8456 * to the first entry in the offset table.
8457 */
8458 count--;
8459 rdataset->privateuint4 = count;
8460 rdataset->private5 = raw;
8461
8462 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
8463}
8464
8465static isc_result_t
8466rdataset_next(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset) {
8467 unsigned int count;
8468 unsigned int length;
8469 unsigned char *raw; /* RDATASLAB */
8470
8471 count = rdataset->privateuint4;
8472 if (count == 0)
8473 return (ISC_R_NOMORE);
8474 count--;
8475 rdataset->privateuint4 = count;
8476
8477 /*
8478 * Skip forward one record (length + 4) or one offset (4).
8479 */
8480 raw = rdataset->private5;
8481#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
8482 if ((rdataset->attributes & DNS_RDATASETATTR_LOADORDER) == 0) {
8483#endif
8484 length = raw[0] * 256 + raw[1];
8485 raw += length;
8486#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
8487 }
8488 rdataset->private5 = raw + 4; /* length(2) + order(2) */
8489#else
8490 rdataset->private5 = raw + 2; /* length(2) */
8491#endif
8492
8493 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
8494}
8495
8496static void
8497rdataset_current(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, dns_rdata_t *rdata) {
8498 unsigned char *raw = rdataset->private5; /* RDATASLAB */
8499#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
8500 unsigned int offset;
8501#endif
8502 unsigned int length;
8503 isc_region_t r;
8504 unsigned int flags = 0;
8505
8506 REQUIRE(raw != NULL);
8507
8508 /*
8509 * Find the start of the record if not already in private5
8510 * then skip the length and order fields.
8511 */
8512#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
8513 if ((rdataset->attributes & DNS_RDATASETATTR_LOADORDER) != 0) {
8514 offset = (raw[0] << 24) + (raw[1] << 16) +
8515 (raw[2] << 8) + raw[3];
8516 raw = rdataset->private3;
8517 raw += offset;
8518 }
8519#endif
8520 length = raw[0] * 256 + raw[1];
8521#if DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
8522 raw += 4;
8523#else
8524 raw += 2;
8525#endif
8526 if (rdataset->type == dns_rdatatype_rrsig) {
8527 if (*raw & DNS_RDATASLAB_OFFLINE)
8528 flags |= DNS_RDATA_OFFLINE;
8529 length--;
8530 raw++;
8531 }
8532 r.length = length;
8533 r.base = raw;
8534 dns_rdata_fromregion(rdata, rdataset->rdclass, rdataset->type, &r);
8535 rdata->flags |= flags;
8536}
8537
8538static void
8539rdataset_clone(dns_rdataset_t *source, dns_rdataset_t *target) {
8540 dns_db_t *db = source->private1;
8541 dns_dbnode_t *node = source->private2;
8542 dns_dbnode_t *cloned_node = NULL;
8543
8544 attachnode(db, node, &cloned_node);
8545 INSIST(!ISC_LINK_LINKED(target, link));
8546 *target = *source;
8547 ISC_LINK_INIT(target, link);
8548
8549 /*
8550 * Reset iterator state.
8551 */
8552 target->privateuint4 = 0;
8553 target->private5 = NULL;
8554}
8555
8556static unsigned int
8557rdataset_count(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset) {
8558 unsigned char *raw = rdataset->private3; /* RDATASLAB */
8559 unsigned int count;
8560
8561 count = raw[0] * 256 + raw[1];
8562
8563 return (count);
8564}

8566static isc_result_t
8567rdataset_getnoqname(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, dns_name_t *name,
8568 dns_rdataset_t *nsec, dns_rdataset_t *nsecsig)
8569{
8570 dns_db_t *db = rdataset->private1;
8571 dns_dbnode_t *node = rdataset->private2;
8572 dns_dbnode_t *cloned_node;
8573 const struct noqname *noqname = rdataset->private6;
8574
8575 cloned_node = NULL;
8576 attachnode(db, node, &cloned_node);
8577 nsec->methods = &slab_methods;
8578 nsec->rdclass = db->rdclass;
8579 nsec->type = noqname->type;
8580 nsec->covers = 0;
8581 nsec->ttl = rdataset->ttl;
8582 nsec->trust = rdataset->trust;
8583 nsec->private1 = rdataset->private1;
8584 nsec->private2 = rdataset->private2;
8585 nsec->private3 = noqname->neg;
8586 nsec->privateuint4 = 0;
8587 nsec->private5 = NULL;
8588 nsec->private6 = NULL;
8589 nsec->private7 = NULL;
8590
8591 cloned_node = NULL;
8592 attachnode(db, node, &cloned_node);
8593 nsecsig->methods = &slab_methods;
8594 nsecsig->rdclass = db->rdclass;
8595 nsecsig->type = dns_rdatatype_rrsig;
8596 nsecsig->covers = noqname->type;
8597 nsecsig->ttl = rdataset->ttl;
8598 nsecsig->trust = rdataset->trust;
8599 nsecsig->private1 = rdataset->private1;
8600 nsecsig->private2 = rdataset->private2;
8601 nsecsig->private3 = noqname->negsig;
8602 nsecsig->privateuint4 = 0;
8603 nsecsig->private5 = NULL;
8604 nsec->private6 = NULL;
8605 nsec->private7 = NULL;
8606
8607 dns_name_clone(&noqname->name, name);
8608
8609 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
8610}

8658static void
8659rdataset_settrust(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, dns_trust_t trust) {

8661 dns_rbtnode_t *rbtnode = rdataset->private2;
8662 rdatasetheader_t *header = rdataset->private3;

8664 header--;

8666 isc_rwlocktype_write);
8667 header->trust = rdataset->trust = trust;
8668 NODE_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[rbtnode->locknum].lock,
8669 isc_rwlocktype_write);
8670}

8672static void

8686static void
8687rdataset_clearprefetch(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset) {

8696 NODE_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[rbtnode->locknum].lock,

8700/*
8701 * Rdataset Iterator Methods
8702 */
8703
8704static void
8705rdatasetiter_destroy(dns_rdatasetiter_t **iteratorp) {
8706 rbtdb_rdatasetiter_t *rbtiterator;
8707
8708 rbtiterator = (rbtdb_rdatasetiter_t *)(*iteratorp);
8709
8710 if (rbtiterator->common.version != NULL)
8711 closeversion(rbtiterator->common.db,
8712 &rbtiterator->common.version, false);
8713 detachnode(rbtiterator->common.db, &rbtiterator->common.node);
8714 isc_mem_put(rbtiterator->common.db->mctx, rbtiterator,
8715 sizeof(*rbtiterator));
8716
8717 *iteratorp = NULL;
8718}
8719
8720static isc_result_t
8721rdatasetiter_first(dns_rdatasetiter_t *iterator) {
8722 rbtdb_rdatasetiter_t *rbtiterator = (rbtdb_rdatasetiter_t *)iterator;
8723 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)(rbtiterator->common.db);
8724 dns_rbtnode_t *rbtnode = rbtiterator->common.node;
8725 rbtdb_version_t *rbtversion = rbtiterator->common.version;
8726 rdatasetheader_t *header, *top_next;
8727 rbtdb_serial_t serial;
8728 isc_stdtime_t now;
8729
8730 if (IS_CACHE(rbtdb)) {
8731 serial = 1;
8732 now = rbtiterator->common.now;
8733 } else {
8734 serial = rbtversion->serial;
8735 now = 0;
8736 }
8737
8738 NODE_LOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[rbtnode->locknum].lock,
8739 isc_rwlocktype_read);
8740
8741 for (header = rbtnode->data; header != NULL; header = top_next) {
8742 top_next = header->next;
8743 do {
8744 if (header->serial <= serial && !IGNORE(header)) {
8745 /*
8746 * Is this a "this rdataset doesn't exist"
8747 * record? Or is it too old in the cache?
8748 *
8749 * Note: unlike everywhere else, we
8750 * check for now > header->rdh_ttl instead
8751 * of now >= header->rdh_ttl. This allows
8752 * ANY and RRSIG queries for 0 TTL
8753 * rdatasets to work.
8754 */
8755 if (NONEXISTENT(header) ||
8756 (now != 0 && now > header->rdh_ttl
8757 + rbtdb->serve_stale_ttl))
8758 header = NULL;
8759 break;
8760 } else
8761 header = header->down;
8762 } while (header != NULL);
8763 if (header != NULL)
8764 break;
8765 }
8766
8767 NODE_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[rbtnode->locknum].lock,
8768 isc_rwlocktype_read);
8769
8770 rbtiterator->current = header;
8771
8772 if (header == NULL)
8773 return (ISC_R_NOMORE);
8774
8775 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
8776}
8777
8778static isc_result_t
8779rdatasetiter_next(dns_rdatasetiter_t *iterator) {
8780 rbtdb_rdatasetiter_t *rbtiterator = (rbtdb_rdatasetiter_t *)iterator;
8781 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)(rbtiterator->common.db);
8782 dns_rbtnode_t *rbtnode = rbtiterator->common.node;
8783 rbtdb_version_t *rbtversion = rbtiterator->common.version;
8784 rdatasetheader_t *header, *top_next;
8785 rbtdb_serial_t serial;
8786 isc_stdtime_t now;
8787 rbtdb_rdatatype_t type, negtype;
8788 dns_rdatatype_t rdtype, covers;
8789
8790 header = rbtiterator->current;
8791 if (header == NULL)
8792 return (ISC_R_NOMORE);
8793
8794 if (IS_CACHE(rbtdb)) {
8795 serial = 1;
8796 now = rbtiterator->common.now;
8797 } else {
8798 serial = rbtversion->serial;
8799 now = 0;
8800 }
8801
8802 NODE_LOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[rbtnode->locknum].lock,
8803 isc_rwlocktype_read);
8804
8805 type = header->type;
8806 rdtype = RBTDB_RDATATYPE_BASE(header->type);
8807 if (NEGATIVE(header)) {
8808 covers = RBTDB_RDATATYPE_EXT(header->type);
8809 negtype = RBTDB_RDATATYPE_VALUE(covers, 0);
8810 } else
8811 negtype = RBTDB_RDATATYPE_VALUE(0, rdtype);
8812 for (header = header->next; header != NULL; header = top_next) {
8813 top_next = header->next;
8814 /*
8815 * If not walking back up the down list.
8816 */
8817 if (header->type != type && header->type != negtype) {
8818 do {
8819 if (header->serial <= serial &&
8820 !IGNORE(header)) {
8821 /*
8822 * Is this a "this rdataset doesn't
8823 * exist" record?
8824 *
8825 * Note: unlike everywhere else, we
8826 * check for now > header->ttl instead
8827 * of now >= header->ttl. This allows
8828 * ANY and RRSIG queries for 0 TTL
8829 * rdatasets to work.
8830 */
8831 if (NONEXISTENT(header) ||
8832 (now != 0 && now > header->rdh_ttl))
8833 header = NULL;
8834 break;
8835 } else
8836 header = header->down;
8837 } while (header != NULL);
8838 if (header != NULL)
8839 break;
8840 }
8841 }
8842
8843 NODE_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[rbtnode->locknum].lock,
8844 isc_rwlocktype_read);
8845
8846 rbtiterator->current = header;
8847
8848 if (header == NULL)
8849 return (ISC_R_NOMORE);
8850
8851 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
8852}
8853
8854static void
8855rdatasetiter_current(dns_rdatasetiter_t *iterator, dns_rdataset_t *rdataset) {
8856 rbtdb_rdatasetiter_t *rbtiterator = (rbtdb_rdatasetiter_t *)iterator;
8857 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)(rbtiterator->common.db);
8858 dns_rbtnode_t *rbtnode = rbtiterator->common.node;
8859 rdatasetheader_t *header;
8860
8861 header = rbtiterator->current;
8862 REQUIRE(header != NULL);
8863
8864 NODE_LOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[rbtnode->locknum].lock,
8865 isc_rwlocktype_read);
8866
8867 bind_rdataset(rbtdb, rbtnode, header, rbtiterator->common.now,
8868 rdataset);
8869
8870 NODE_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[rbtnode->locknum].lock,
8871 isc_rwlocktype_read);
8872}
8873
8874
8875/*
8876 * Database Iterator Methods
8877 */
8878
8879static inline void
8880reference_iter_node(rbtdb_dbiterator_t *rbtdbiter) {
8881 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)rbtdbiter->common.db;
8882 dns_rbtnode_t *node = rbtdbiter->node;
8883
8884 if (node == NULL)
8885 return;
8886
8887 INSIST(rbtdbiter->tree_locked != isc_rwlocktype_none);
8888 reactivate_node(rbtdb, node, rbtdbiter->tree_locked);
8889}
8890
8891static inline void
8892dereference_iter_node(rbtdb_dbiterator_t *rbtdbiter) {
8893 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)rbtdbiter->common.db;
8894 dns_rbtnode_t *node = rbtdbiter->node;
8895 nodelock_t *lock;
8896
8897 if (node == NULL)
8898 return;
8899
8900 lock = &rbtdb->node_locks[node->locknum].lock;
8901 NODE_LOCK(lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
8902 decrement_reference(rbtdb, node, 0, isc_rwlocktype_read,
8903 rbtdbiter->tree_locked, false);
8904 NODE_UNLOCK(lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
8905
8906 rbtdbiter->node = NULL;
8907}
8908
8909static void
8910flush_deletions(rbtdb_dbiterator_t *rbtdbiter) {
8911 dns_rbtnode_t *node;
8912 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)rbtdbiter->common.db;
8913 bool was_read_locked = false;
8914 nodelock_t *lock;
8915 int i;
8916
8917 if (rbtdbiter->delcnt != 0) {
8918 /*
8919 * Note that "%d node of %d in tree" can report things like
8920 * "flush_deletions: 59 nodes of 41 in tree". This means
8921 * That some nodes appear on the deletions list more than
8922 * once. Only the last occurence will actually be deleted.
8923 */
8924 isc_log_write(dns_lctx, DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DATABASE,
8925 DNS_LOGMODULE_CACHE, ISC_LOG_DEBUG(1),
8926 "flush_deletions: %d nodes of %d in tree",
8927 rbtdbiter->delcnt,
8928 dns_rbt_nodecount(rbtdb->tree));
8929
8930 if (rbtdbiter->tree_locked == isc_rwlocktype_read) {
8931 RWUNLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
8932 was_read_locked = true;
8933 }
8934 RWLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
8935 rbtdbiter->tree_locked = isc_rwlocktype_write;
8936
8937 for (i = 0; i < rbtdbiter->delcnt; i++) {
8938 node = rbtdbiter->deletions[i];
8939 lock = &rbtdb->node_locks[node->locknum].lock;
8940
8941 NODE_LOCK(lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
8942 decrement_reference(rbtdb, node, 0,
8943 isc_rwlocktype_read,
8944 rbtdbiter->tree_locked, false);
8945 NODE_UNLOCK(lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
8946 }
8947
8948 rbtdbiter->delcnt = 0;
8949
8950 RWUNLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
8951 if (was_read_locked) {
8952 RWLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
8953 rbtdbiter->tree_locked = isc_rwlocktype_read;
8954
8955 } else {
8956 rbtdbiter->tree_locked = isc_rwlocktype_none;
8957 }
8958 }
8959}
8960
8961static inline void
8962resume_iteration(rbtdb_dbiterator_t *rbtdbiter) {
8963 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)rbtdbiter->common.db;
8964
8965 REQUIRE(rbtdbiter->paused);
8966 REQUIRE(rbtdbiter->tree_locked == isc_rwlocktype_none);
8967
8968 RWLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
8969 rbtdbiter->tree_locked = isc_rwlocktype_read;
8970
8971 rbtdbiter->paused = false;
8972}
8973
8974static void
8975dbiterator_destroy(dns_dbiterator_t **iteratorp) {
8976 rbtdb_dbiterator_t *rbtdbiter = (rbtdb_dbiterator_t *)(*iteratorp);
8977 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)rbtdbiter->common.db;
8978 dns_db_t *db = NULL;
8979
8980 if (rbtdbiter->tree_locked == isc_rwlocktype_read) {
8981 RWUNLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
8982 rbtdbiter->tree_locked = isc_rwlocktype_none;
8983 } else
8984 INSIST(rbtdbiter->tree_locked == isc_rwlocktype_none);
8985
8986 dereference_iter_node(rbtdbiter);
8987
8988 flush_deletions(rbtdbiter);
8989
8990 dns_db_attach(rbtdbiter->common.db, &db);
8991 dns_db_detach(&rbtdbiter->common.db);
8992
8993 dns_rbtnodechain_reset(&rbtdbiter->chain);
8994 dns_rbtnodechain_reset(&rbtdbiter->nsec3chain);
8995 isc_mem_put(db->mctx, rbtdbiter, sizeof(*rbtdbiter));
8996 dns_db_detach(&db);
8997
8998 *iteratorp = NULL;
8999}
9000
9001static isc_result_t
9002dbiterator_first(dns_dbiterator_t *iterator) {
9003 isc_result_t result;
9004 rbtdb_dbiterator_t *rbtdbiter = (rbtdb_dbiterator_t *)iterator;
9005 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)iterator->db;
9006 dns_name_t *name, *origin;
9007
9008 if (rbtdbiter->result != ISC_R_SUCCESS &&
9009 rbtdbiter->result != ISC_R_NOTFOUND &&
9010 rbtdbiter->result != DNS_R_PARTIALMATCH &&
9011 rbtdbiter->result != ISC_R_NOMORE)
9012 return (rbtdbiter->result);
9013
9014 if (rbtdbiter->paused)
9015 resume_iteration(rbtdbiter);
9016
9017 dereference_iter_node(rbtdbiter);
9018
9019 name = dns_fixedname_name(&rbtdbiter->name);
9020 origin = dns_fixedname_name(&rbtdbiter->origin);
9021 dns_rbtnodechain_reset(&rbtdbiter->chain);
9022 dns_rbtnodechain_reset(&rbtdbiter->nsec3chain);
9023
9024 if (rbtdbiter->nsec3only) {
9025 rbtdbiter->current = &rbtdbiter->nsec3chain;
9026 result = dns_rbtnodechain_first(rbtdbiter->current,
9027 rbtdb->nsec3, name, origin);
9028 } else {
9029 rbtdbiter->current = &rbtdbiter->chain;
9030 result = dns_rbtnodechain_first(rbtdbiter->current,
9031 rbtdb->tree, name, origin);
9032 if (!rbtdbiter->nonsec3 && result == ISC_R_NOTFOUND) {
9033 rbtdbiter->current = &rbtdbiter->nsec3chain;
9034 result = dns_rbtnodechain_first(rbtdbiter->current,
9035 rbtdb->nsec3, name,
9036 origin);
9037 }
9038 }
9039 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS || result == DNS_R_NEWORIGIN) {
9040 result = dns_rbtnodechain_current(rbtdbiter->current, NULL,
9041 NULL, &rbtdbiter->node);
9042 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
9043 rbtdbiter->new_origin = true;
9044 reference_iter_node(rbtdbiter);
9045 }
9046 } else {
9047 INSIST(result == ISC_R_NOTFOUND);
9048 result = ISC_R_NOMORE; /* The tree is empty. */
9049 }
9050
9051 rbtdbiter->result = result;
9052
9053 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
9054 ENSURE(!rbtdbiter->paused);
9055
9056 return (result);
9057}
9058
9059static isc_result_t
9060dbiterator_last(dns_dbiterator_t *iterator) {
9061 isc_result_t result;
9062 rbtdb_dbiterator_t *rbtdbiter = (rbtdb_dbiterator_t *)iterator;
9063 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)iterator->db;
9064 dns_name_t *name, *origin;
9065
9066 if (rbtdbiter->result != ISC_R_SUCCESS &&
9067 rbtdbiter->result != ISC_R_NOTFOUND &&
9068 rbtdbiter->result != DNS_R_PARTIALMATCH &&
9069 rbtdbiter->result != ISC_R_NOMORE)
9070 return (rbtdbiter->result);
9071
9072 if (rbtdbiter->paused)
9073 resume_iteration(rbtdbiter);
9074
9075 dereference_iter_node(rbtdbiter);
9076
9077 name = dns_fixedname_name(&rbtdbiter->name);
9078 origin = dns_fixedname_name(&rbtdbiter->origin);
9079 dns_rbtnodechain_reset(&rbtdbiter->chain);
9080 dns_rbtnodechain_reset(&rbtdbiter->nsec3chain);
9081
9082 result = ISC_R_NOTFOUND;
9083 if (rbtdbiter->nsec3only && !rbtdbiter->nonsec3) {
9084 rbtdbiter->current = &rbtdbiter->nsec3chain;
9085 result = dns_rbtnodechain_last(rbtdbiter->current,
9086 rbtdb->nsec3, name, origin);
9087 }
9088 if (!rbtdbiter->nsec3only && result == ISC_R_NOTFOUND) {
9089 rbtdbiter->current = &rbtdbiter->chain;
9090 result = dns_rbtnodechain_last(rbtdbiter->current, rbtdb->tree,
9091 name, origin);
9092 }
9093 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS || result == DNS_R_NEWORIGIN) {
9094 result = dns_rbtnodechain_current(rbtdbiter->current, NULL,
9095 NULL, &rbtdbiter->node);
9096 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
9097 rbtdbiter->new_origin = true;
9098 reference_iter_node(rbtdbiter);
9099 }
9100 } else {
9101 INSIST(result == ISC_R_NOTFOUND);
9102 result = ISC_R_NOMORE; /* The tree is empty. */
9103 }
9104
9105 rbtdbiter->result = result;
9106
9107 return (result);
9108}
9109
9110static isc_result_t
9111dbiterator_seek(dns_dbiterator_t *iterator, const dns_name_t *name) {
9112 isc_result_t result, tresult;
9113 rbtdb_dbiterator_t *rbtdbiter = (rbtdb_dbiterator_t *)iterator;
9114 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)iterator->db;
9115 dns_name_t *iname, *origin;
9116
9117 if (rbtdbiter->result != ISC_R_SUCCESS &&
9118 rbtdbiter->result != ISC_R_NOTFOUND &&
9119 rbtdbiter->result != DNS_R_PARTIALMATCH &&
9120 rbtdbiter->result != ISC_R_NOMORE)
9121 return (rbtdbiter->result);
9122
9123 if (rbtdbiter->paused)
9124 resume_iteration(rbtdbiter);
9125
9126 dereference_iter_node(rbtdbiter);
9127
9128 iname = dns_fixedname_name(&rbtdbiter->name);
9129 origin = dns_fixedname_name(&rbtdbiter->origin);
9130 dns_rbtnodechain_reset(&rbtdbiter->chain);
9131 dns_rbtnodechain_reset(&rbtdbiter->nsec3chain);
9132
9133 if (rbtdbiter->nsec3only) {
9134 rbtdbiter->current = &rbtdbiter->nsec3chain;
9135 result = dns_rbt_findnode(rbtdb->nsec3, name, NULL,
9136 &rbtdbiter->node,
9137 rbtdbiter->current,
9138 DNS_RBTFIND_EMPTYDATA, NULL, NULL);
9139 } else if (rbtdbiter->nonsec3) {
9140 rbtdbiter->current = &rbtdbiter->chain;
9141 result = dns_rbt_findnode(rbtdb->tree, name, NULL,
9142 &rbtdbiter->node,
9143 rbtdbiter->current,
9144 DNS_RBTFIND_EMPTYDATA, NULL, NULL);
9145 } else {
9146 /*
9147 * Stay on main chain if not found on either chain.
9148 */
9149 rbtdbiter->current = &rbtdbiter->chain;
9150 result = dns_rbt_findnode(rbtdb->tree, name, NULL,
9151 &rbtdbiter->node,
9152 rbtdbiter->current,
9153 DNS_RBTFIND_EMPTYDATA, NULL, NULL);
9154 if (result == DNS_R_PARTIALMATCH) {
9155 dns_rbtnode_t *node = NULL;
9156 tresult = dns_rbt_findnode(rbtdb->nsec3, name, NULL,
9157 &node, &rbtdbiter->nsec3chain,
9158 DNS_RBTFIND_EMPTYDATA,
9159 NULL, NULL);
9160 if (tresult == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
9161 rbtdbiter->node = node;
9162 rbtdbiter->current = &rbtdbiter->nsec3chain;
9163 result = tresult;
9164 }
9165 }
9166 }
9167
9168 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS || result == DNS_R_PARTIALMATCH) {
9169 tresult = dns_rbtnodechain_current(rbtdbiter->current, iname,
9170 origin, NULL);
9171 if (tresult == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
9172 rbtdbiter->new_origin = true;
9173 reference_iter_node(rbtdbiter);
9174 } else {
9175 result = tresult;
9176 rbtdbiter->node = NULL;
9177 }
9178 } else
9179 rbtdbiter->node = NULL;
9180
9181 rbtdbiter->result = (result == DNS_R_PARTIALMATCH) ?
9182 ISC_R_SUCCESS : result;
9183
9184 return (result);
9185}
9186
9187static isc_result_t
9188dbiterator_prev(dns_dbiterator_t *iterator) {
9189 isc_result_t result;
9190 rbtdb_dbiterator_t *rbtdbiter = (rbtdb_dbiterator_t *)iterator;
9191 dns_name_t *name, *origin;
9192 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)iterator->db;
9193
9194 REQUIRE(rbtdbiter->node != NULL);
9195
9196 if (rbtdbiter->result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
9197 return (rbtdbiter->result);
9198
9199 if (rbtdbiter->paused)
9200 resume_iteration(rbtdbiter);
9201
9202 name = dns_fixedname_name(&rbtdbiter->name);
9203 origin = dns_fixedname_name(&rbtdbiter->origin);
9204 result = dns_rbtnodechain_prev(rbtdbiter->current, name, origin);
9205 if (result == ISC_R_NOMORE && !rbtdbiter->nsec3only &&
9206 !rbtdbiter->nonsec3 &&
9207 &rbtdbiter->nsec3chain == rbtdbiter->current) {
9208 rbtdbiter->current = &rbtdbiter->chain;
9209 dns_rbtnodechain_reset(rbtdbiter->current);
9210 result = dns_rbtnodechain_last(rbtdbiter->current, rbtdb->tree,
9211 name, origin);
9212 if (result == ISC_R_NOTFOUND)
9213 result = ISC_R_NOMORE;
9214 }
9215
9216 dereference_iter_node(rbtdbiter);
9217
9218 if (result == DNS_R_NEWORIGIN || result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
9219 rbtdbiter->new_origin = (result == DNS_R_NEWORIGIN);
9220 result = dns_rbtnodechain_current(rbtdbiter->current, NULL,
9221 NULL, &rbtdbiter->node);
9222 }
9223
9224 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
9225 reference_iter_node(rbtdbiter);
9226
9227 rbtdbiter->result = result;
9228
9229 return (result);
9230}
9231
9232static isc_result_t
9233dbiterator_next(dns_dbiterator_t *iterator) {
9234 isc_result_t result;
9235 rbtdb_dbiterator_t *rbtdbiter = (rbtdb_dbiterator_t *)iterator;
9236 dns_name_t *name, *origin;
9237 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)iterator->db;
9238
9239 REQUIRE(rbtdbiter->node != NULL);
9240
9241 if (rbtdbiter->result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
9242 return (rbtdbiter->result);
9243
9244 if (rbtdbiter->paused)
9245 resume_iteration(rbtdbiter);
9246
9247 name = dns_fixedname_name(&rbtdbiter->name);
9248 origin = dns_fixedname_name(&rbtdbiter->origin);
9249 result = dns_rbtnodechain_next(rbtdbiter->current, name, origin);
9250 if (result == ISC_R_NOMORE && !rbtdbiter->nsec3only &&
9251 !rbtdbiter->nonsec3 && &rbtdbiter->chain == rbtdbiter->current) {
9252 rbtdbiter->current = &rbtdbiter->nsec3chain;
9253 dns_rbtnodechain_reset(rbtdbiter->current);
9254 result = dns_rbtnodechain_first(rbtdbiter->current,
9255 rbtdb->nsec3, name, origin);
9256 if (result == ISC_R_NOTFOUND)
9257 result = ISC_R_NOMORE;
9258 }
9259
9260 dereference_iter_node(rbtdbiter);
9261
9262 if (result == DNS_R_NEWORIGIN || result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
9263 rbtdbiter->new_origin = (result == DNS_R_NEWORIGIN);
9264 result = dns_rbtnodechain_current(rbtdbiter->current, NULL,
9265 NULL, &rbtdbiter->node);
9266 }
9267 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
9268 reference_iter_node(rbtdbiter);
9269
9270 rbtdbiter->result = result;
9271
9272 return (result);
9273}
9274
9275static isc_result_t
9276dbiterator_current(dns_dbiterator_t *iterator, dns_dbnode_t **nodep,
9277 dns_name_t *name)
9278{
9279 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)iterator->db;
9280 rbtdb_dbiterator_t *rbtdbiter = (rbtdb_dbiterator_t *)iterator;
9281 dns_rbtnode_t *node = rbtdbiter->node;
9282 isc_result_t result;
9283 dns_name_t *nodename = dns_fixedname_name(&rbtdbiter->name);
9284 dns_name_t *origin = dns_fixedname_name(&rbtdbiter->origin);
9285
9286 REQUIRE(rbtdbiter->result == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
9287 REQUIRE(rbtdbiter->node != NULL);
9288
9289 if (rbtdbiter->paused)
9290 resume_iteration(rbtdbiter);
9291
9292 if (name != NULL) {
9293 if (rbtdbiter->common.relative_names)
9294 origin = NULL;
9295 result = dns_name_concatenate(nodename, origin, name, NULL);
9296 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
9297 return (result);
9298 if (rbtdbiter->common.relative_names && rbtdbiter->new_origin)
9299 result = DNS_R_NEWORIGIN;
9300 } else
9301 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
9302
9303 new_reference(rbtdb, node);
9304
9305 *nodep = rbtdbiter->node;
9306
9307 if (iterator->cleaning && result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
9308 isc_result_t expire_result;
9309
9310 /*
9311 * If the deletion array is full, flush it before trying
9312 * to expire the current node. The current node can't
9313 * fully deleted while the iteration cursor is still on it.
9314 */
9315 if (rbtdbiter->delcnt == DELETION_BATCH_MAX)
9316 flush_deletions(rbtdbiter);
9317
9318 expire_result = expirenode(iterator->db, *nodep, 0);
9319
9320 /*
9321 * expirenode() currently always returns success.
9322 */
9323 if (expire_result == ISC_R_SUCCESS && node->down == NULL) {
9324 rbtdbiter->deletions[rbtdbiter->delcnt++] = node;
9325 isc_refcount_increment(&node->references);
9326 }
9327 }
9328
9329 return (result);
9330}
9331
9332static isc_result_t
9333dbiterator_pause(dns_dbiterator_t *iterator) {
9334 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = (dns_rbtdb_t *)iterator->db;
9335 rbtdb_dbiterator_t *rbtdbiter = (rbtdb_dbiterator_t *)iterator;
9336
9337 if (rbtdbiter->result != ISC_R_SUCCESS &&
9338 rbtdbiter->result != ISC_R_NOTFOUND &&
9339 rbtdbiter->result != DNS_R_PARTIALMATCH &&
9340 rbtdbiter->result != ISC_R_NOMORE)
9341 return (rbtdbiter->result);
9342
9343 if (rbtdbiter->paused)
9344 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
9345
9346 rbtdbiter->paused = true;
9347
9348 if (rbtdbiter->tree_locked != isc_rwlocktype_none) {
9349 INSIST(rbtdbiter->tree_locked == isc_rwlocktype_read);
9350 RWUNLOCK(&rbtdb->tree_lock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
9351 rbtdbiter->tree_locked = isc_rwlocktype_none;
9352 }
9353
9354 flush_deletions(rbtdbiter);
9355
9356 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
9357}
9358
9359static isc_result_t
9360dbiterator_origin(dns_dbiterator_t *iterator, dns_name_t *name) {
9361 rbtdb_dbiterator_t *rbtdbiter = (rbtdb_dbiterator_t *)iterator;
9362 dns_name_t *origin = dns_fixedname_name(&rbtdbiter->origin);
9363
9364 if (rbtdbiter->result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
9365 return (rbtdbiter->result);
9366
9367 return (dns_name_copy(origin, name, NULL));
9368}
9369
9370static void
9371setownercase(rdatasetheader_t *header, const dns_name_t *name) {
9372 unsigned int i;
9373 bool fully_lower;
9374
9375 /*
9376 * We do not need to worry about label lengths as they are all
9377 * less than or equal to 63.
9378 */
9379 memset(header->upper, 0, sizeof(header->upper));
9380 fully_lower = true;
9381 for (i = 0; i < name->length; i++)
9382 if (name->ndata[i] >= 0x41 && name->ndata[i] <= 0x5a) {
9383 header->upper[i/8] |= 1 << (i%8);
9384 fully_lower = false;
9385 }
9386 header->attributes |= RDATASET_ATTR_CASESET;
9387 if (ISC_LIKELY(fully_lower))
9388 header->attributes |= RDATASET_ATTR_CASEFULLYLOWER;
9389}
9390
9391static void
9392rdataset_setownercase(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, const dns_name_t *name) {
9393 unsigned char *raw = rdataset->private3; /* RDATASLAB */
9394 rdatasetheader_t *header;
9395
9396 header = (struct rdatasetheader *)(raw - sizeof(*header));
9397 setownercase(header, name);
9398}

9469
9470static void
9471rdataset_getownercase(const dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, dns_name_t *name) {
9472 const unsigned char *raw = rdataset->private3; /* RDATASLAB */
9473 const rdatasetheader_t *header;
9474 unsigned int i, j;
9475 unsigned char bits;
9476 unsigned char c, flip;
9477
9478 header = (const struct rdatasetheader *)(raw - sizeof(*header));
9479
9480 if (!CASESET(header))
9481 return;
9482
9483#if 0
9484 /*
9485 * This was the original code, and is implemented differently in
9486 * the #else block that follows.
9487 */
9488 for (i = 0; i < name->length; i++) {
9489 /*
9490 * Set the case bit if it does not match the recorded bit.
9491 */
9492 if (name->ndata[i] >= 0x61 && name->ndata[i] <= 0x7a &&
9493 (header->upper[i/8] & (1 << (i%8))) != 0)
9494 name->ndata[i] &= ~0x20; /* clear the lower case bit */
9495 else if (name->ndata[i] >= 0x41 && name->ndata[i] <= 0x5a &&
9496 (header->upper[i/8] & (1 << (i%8))) == 0)
9497 name->ndata[i] |= 0x20; /* set the lower case bit */
9498 }
9499#else
9500
9501 if (ISC_LIKELY(CASEFULLYLOWER(header))) {
9502 unsigned char *bp, *be;
9503 bp = name->ndata;
9504 be = bp + name->length;
9505
9506 while (bp <= be - 4) {
9507 c = bp[0];
9508 bp[0] = maptolower[c];
9509 c = bp[1];
9510 bp[1] = maptolower[c];
9511 c = bp[2];
9512 bp[2] = maptolower[c];
9513 c = bp[3];
9514 bp[3] = maptolower[c];
9515 bp += 4;
9516 }
9517 while (bp < be) {
9518 c = *bp;
9519 *bp++ = maptolower[c];
9520 }
9521 return;
9522 }
9523
9524 i = 0;
9525 for (j = 0; j < (name->length >> 3); j++) {
9526 unsigned int k;
9527
9528 bits = ~(header->upper[j]);
9529
9530 for (k = 0; k < 8; k++) {
9531 c = name->ndata[i];
9532 flip = (bits & 1) << 5;
9533 flip ^= c;
9534 flip &= charmask[c];
9535 name->ndata[i] ^= flip;
9536
9537 i++;
9538 bits >>= 1;
9539 }
9540 }
9541
9542 if (ISC_UNLIKELY(i == name->length))
9543 return;
9544
9545 bits = ~(header->upper[j]);
9546
9547 for (; i < name->length; i++) {
9548 c = name->ndata[i];
9549 flip = (bits & 1) << 5;
9550 flip ^= c;
9551 flip &= charmask[c];
9552 name->ndata[i] ^= flip;
9553
9554 bits >>= 1;
9555 }
9556#endif
9557}
9558
9559struct rbtdb_glue {
9560 struct rbtdb_glue *next;
9561 dns_fixedname_t fixedname;
9562 dns_rdataset_t rdataset_a;
9563 dns_rdataset_t sigrdataset_a;
9564 dns_rdataset_t rdataset_aaaa;
9565 dns_rdataset_t sigrdataset_aaaa;
9566};
9567
9568typedef struct {
9569 rbtdb_glue_t *glue_list;
9570 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb;
9571 rbtdb_version_t *rbtversion;
9572} rbtdb_glue_additionaldata_ctx_t;
9573
9574static void
9575free_gluelist(rbtdb_glue_t *glue_list, dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb) {
9576 rbtdb_glue_t *cur, *cur_next;
9577
9578 if (glue_list == (void *) -1)
9579 return;
9580
9581 cur = glue_list;
9582 while (cur != NULL) {
9583 cur_next = cur->next;
9584
9585 if (dns_rdataset_isassociated(&cur->rdataset_a))
9586 dns_rdataset_disassociate(&cur->rdataset_a);
9587 if (dns_rdataset_isassociated(&cur->sigrdataset_a))
9588 dns_rdataset_disassociate(&cur->sigrdataset_a);
9589
9590 if (dns_rdataset_isassociated(&cur->rdataset_aaaa))
9591 dns_rdataset_disassociate(&cur->rdataset_aaaa);
9592 if (dns_rdataset_isassociated(&cur->sigrdataset_aaaa))
9593 dns_rdataset_disassociate(&cur->sigrdataset_aaaa);
9594
9595 dns_rdataset_invalidate(&cur->rdataset_a);
9596 dns_rdataset_invalidate(&cur->sigrdataset_a);
9597 dns_rdataset_invalidate(&cur->rdataset_aaaa);
9598 dns_rdataset_invalidate(&cur->sigrdataset_aaaa);
9599
9600 isc_mem_put(rbtdb->common.mctx, cur, sizeof(*cur));
9601 cur = cur_next;
9602 }
9603}
9604
9605static void
9606free_gluetable(rbtdb_version_t *version) {
9607 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb;
9608 size_t i;
9609
9610 RWLOCK(&version->glue_rwlock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
9611
9612 rbtdb = version->rbtdb;
9613
9614 for (i = 0; i < version->glue_table_size; i++) {
9615 rbtdb_glue_table_node_t *cur, *cur_next;
9616
9617 cur = version->glue_table[i];
9618 while (cur != NULL) {
9619 cur_next = cur->next;
9620 /* isc_refcount_decrement(&cur->node->references); */
9621 cur->node = NULL;
9622 free_gluelist(cur->glue_list, rbtdb);
9623 cur->glue_list = NULL;
9624 isc_mem_put(rbtdb->common.mctx, cur, sizeof(*cur));
9625 cur = cur_next;
9626 }
9627 version->glue_table[i] = NULL;
9628 }
9629
9630 isc_mem_put(rbtdb->common.mctx, version->glue_table,
9631 (sizeof(*version->glue_table) *
9632 version->glue_table_size));
9633
9634 RWUNLOCK(&version->glue_rwlock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
9635}
9636
9637static bool
9638rehash_gluetable(rbtdb_version_t *version) {
9639 size_t oldsize, i;
9640 rbtdb_glue_table_node_t **oldtable;
9641 rbtdb_glue_table_node_t *gluenode;
9642 rbtdb_glue_table_node_t *nextgluenode;
9643 uint32_t hash;
9644
9645 if (ISC_LIKELY(version->glue_table_nodecount <
9646 (version->glue_table_size * 3U)))
9647 return (false);
9648
9649 oldsize = version->glue_table_size;
9650 oldtable = version->glue_table;
9651 do {
9652 INSIST((version->glue_table_size * 2 + 1) >
9653 version->glue_table_size);
9654 version->glue_table_size = version->glue_table_size * 2 + 1;
9655 } while (version->glue_table_nodecount >=
9656 (version->glue_table_size * 3U));
9657
9658 version->glue_table = (rbtdb_glue_table_node_t **)
9659 isc_mem_get(version->rbtdb->common.mctx,
9660 (version->glue_table_size *
9661 sizeof(*version->glue_table)));
9662 if (ISC_UNLIKELY(version->glue_table == NULL)) {
9663 version->glue_table = oldtable;
9664 version->glue_table_size = oldsize;
9665 return (false);
9666 }
9667
9668 for (i = 0; i < version->glue_table_size; i++)
9669 version->glue_table[i] = NULL;
9670
9671 for (i = 0; i < oldsize; i++) {
9672 for (gluenode = oldtable[i];
9673 gluenode != NULL;
9674 gluenode = nextgluenode)
9675 {
9676 hash = isc_hash_function(&gluenode->node,
9677 sizeof(gluenode->node),
9678 true, NULL) %
9679 version->glue_table_size;
9680 nextgluenode = gluenode->next;
9681 gluenode->next = version->glue_table[hash];
9682 version->glue_table[hash] = gluenode;
9683 }
9684 }
9685
9686 isc_mem_put(version->rbtdb->common.mctx, oldtable,
9687 oldsize * sizeof(*version->glue_table));
9688
9689 isc_log_write(dns_lctx, DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DATABASE,
9690 DNS_LOGMODULE_ZONE, ISC_LOG_DEBUG(3),
9691 "rehash_gluetable(): "
9692 "resized glue table from %" PRIu64 " to "
9693 "%" PRIu64,
9694 (uint64_t) oldsize,
9695 (uint64_t) version->glue_table_size);
9696
9697 return (true);
9698}
9699
9700static isc_result_t
9701glue_nsdname_cb(void *arg, const dns_name_t *name, dns_rdatatype_t qtype) {
9702 rbtdb_glue_additionaldata_ctx_t *ctx;
9703 isc_result_t result;
9704 dns_fixedname_t fixedname_a;
9705 dns_name_t *name_a = NULL;
9706 dns_rdataset_t rdataset_a, sigrdataset_a;
9707 dns_rbtnode_t *node_a = NULL;
9708 dns_fixedname_t fixedname_aaaa;
9709 dns_name_t *name_aaaa = NULL;
9710 dns_rdataset_t rdataset_aaaa, sigrdataset_aaaa;
9711 dns_rbtnode_t *node_aaaa = NULL;
9712 rbtdb_glue_t *glue = NULL;
9713 dns_name_t *gluename = NULL;
9714
9715 /*
9716 * NS records want addresses in additional records.
9717 */
9718 INSIST(qtype == dns_rdatatype_a);
9719
9720 ctx = (rbtdb_glue_additionaldata_ctx_t *) arg;
9721
9722 name_a = dns_fixedname_initname(&fixedname_a);
9723 dns_rdataset_init(&rdataset_a);
9724 dns_rdataset_init(&sigrdataset_a);
9725
9726 name_aaaa = dns_fixedname_initname(&fixedname_aaaa);
9727 dns_rdataset_init(&rdataset_aaaa);
9728 dns_rdataset_init(&sigrdataset_aaaa);
9729
9730 result = zone_find((dns_db_t *) ctx->rbtdb, name, ctx->rbtversion,
9731 dns_rdatatype_a, DNS_DBFIND_GLUEOK, 0,
9732 (dns_dbnode_t **) &node_a, name_a,
9733 &rdataset_a, &sigrdataset_a);
9734 if (result == DNS_R_GLUE) {
9735 glue = isc_mem_get(ctx->rbtdb->common.mctx, sizeof(*glue));
9736 if (glue == NULL) {
9737 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
9738 goto out;
9739 }
9740
9741 gluename = dns_fixedname_initname(&glue->fixedname);
9742 dns_name_copy(name_a, gluename, NULL);
9743
9744 dns_rdataset_init(&glue->rdataset_a);
9745 dns_rdataset_init(&glue->sigrdataset_a);
9746 dns_rdataset_init(&glue->rdataset_aaaa);
9747 dns_rdataset_init(&glue->sigrdataset_aaaa);
9748
9749 dns_rdataset_clone(&rdataset_a, &glue->rdataset_a);
9750 if (dns_rdataset_isassociated(&sigrdataset_a)) {
9751 dns_rdataset_clone(&sigrdataset_a,
9752 &glue->sigrdataset_a);
9753 }
9754 }
9755
9756 result = zone_find((dns_db_t *) ctx->rbtdb, name, ctx->rbtversion,
9757 dns_rdatatype_aaaa, DNS_DBFIND_GLUEOK, 0,
9758 (dns_dbnode_t **) &node_aaaa, name_aaaa,
9759 &rdataset_aaaa, &sigrdataset_aaaa);
9760 if (result == DNS_R_GLUE) {
9761 if (glue == NULL) {
9762 glue = isc_mem_get(ctx->rbtdb->common.mctx,
9763 sizeof(*glue));
9764 if (glue == NULL) {
9765 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
9766 goto out;
9767 }
9768
9769 gluename = dns_fixedname_initname(&glue->fixedname);
9770 dns_name_copy(name_aaaa, gluename, NULL);
9771
9772 dns_rdataset_init(&glue->rdataset_a);
9773 dns_rdataset_init(&glue->sigrdataset_a);
9774 dns_rdataset_init(&glue->rdataset_aaaa);
9775 dns_rdataset_init(&glue->sigrdataset_aaaa);
9776 } else {
9777 INSIST(node_a == node_aaaa);
9778 INSIST(dns_name_equal(name_a, name_aaaa));
9779 }
9780
9781 dns_rdataset_clone(&rdataset_aaaa, &glue->rdataset_aaaa);
9782 if (dns_rdataset_isassociated(&sigrdataset_aaaa)) {
9783 dns_rdataset_clone(&sigrdataset_aaaa,
9784 &glue->sigrdataset_aaaa);
9785 }
9786 }
9787
9788 if (glue != NULL) {
9789 glue->next = ctx->glue_list;
9790 ctx->glue_list = glue;
9791 }
9792
9793 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
9794
9795out:
9796 if (dns_rdataset_isassociated(&rdataset_a))
9797 rdataset_disassociate(&rdataset_a);
9798 if (dns_rdataset_isassociated(&sigrdataset_a))
9799 rdataset_disassociate(&sigrdataset_a);
9800
9801 if (dns_rdataset_isassociated(&rdataset_aaaa))
9802 rdataset_disassociate(&rdataset_aaaa);
9803 if (dns_rdataset_isassociated(&sigrdataset_aaaa))
9804 rdataset_disassociate(&sigrdataset_aaaa);
9805
9806 if (node_a != NULL)
9807 detachnode((dns_db_t *) ctx->rbtdb, (dns_dbnode_t *) &node_a);
9808 if (node_aaaa != NULL)
9809 detachnode((dns_db_t *) ctx->rbtdb,
9810 (dns_dbnode_t *) &node_aaaa);
9811
9812 return (result);
9813}
9814
9815static isc_result_t
9816rdataset_addglue(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, dns_dbversion_t *version,
9817 dns_message_t *msg)
9818{
9819 dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb = rdataset->private1;
9820 dns_rbtnode_t *node = rdataset->private2;
9821 rbtdb_version_t *rbtversion = version;
9822 uint32_t idx;
9823 rbtdb_glue_table_node_t *cur;
9824 bool found = false;
9825 bool restarted = false;
9826 rbtdb_glue_t *ge;
9827 rbtdb_glue_additionaldata_ctx_t ctx;
9828 isc_result_t result;
9829
9830 REQUIRE(rdataset->type == dns_rdatatype_ns);
9831 REQUIRE(rbtdb == rbtversion->rbtdb);
9832 REQUIRE(!IS_CACHE(rbtdb) && !IS_STUB(rbtdb));
9833
9834 /*
9835 * The glue table cache that forms a part of the DB version
9836 * structure is not explicitly bounded and there's no cache
9837 * cleaning. The zone data size itself is an implicit bound.
9838 *
9839 * The key into the glue hashtable is the node pointer. This is
9840 * because the glue hashtable is a property of the DB version,
9841 * and the glue is keyed for the ownername/NS tuple. We don't
9842 * bother with using an expensive dns_name_t comparison here as
9843 * the node pointer is a fixed value that won't change for a DB
9844 * version and can be compared directly.
9845 */
9846 idx = isc_hash_function(&node, sizeof(node), true, NULL) %
9847 rbtversion->glue_table_size;
9848
9849restart:
9850 /*
9851 * First, check if we have the additional entries already cached
9852 * in the glue table.
9853 */
9854 RWLOCK(&rbtversion->glue_rwlock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
9855
9856 for (cur = rbtversion->glue_table[idx]; cur != NULL; cur = cur->next)
9857 if (cur->node == node)
9858 break;
9859
9860 if (cur == NULL) {
9861 goto no_glue;
9862 }
9863 /*
9864 * We found a cached result. Add it to the message and
9865 * return.
9866 */
9867 found = true;
9868 ge = cur->glue_list;
9869
9870 /*
9871 * (void *) -1 is a special value that means no glue is
9872 * present in the zone.
9873 */
9874 if (ge == (void *) -1) {
9875 if (!restarted && (rbtdb->gluecachestats != NULL)) {
9876 isc_stats_increment
9877 (rbtdb->gluecachestats,
9878 dns_gluecachestatscounter_hits_absent);
9879 }
9880 goto no_glue;
9881 } else {
9882 if (!restarted && (rbtdb->gluecachestats != NULL)) {
9883 isc_stats_increment
9884 (rbtdb->gluecachestats,
9885 dns_gluecachestatscounter_hits_present);
9886 }
9887 }
9888
9889 for (; ge != NULL; ge = ge->next) {
9890 isc_buffer_t *buffer = NULL;
9891 dns_name_t *name = NULL;
9892 dns_rdataset_t *rdataset_a = NULL;
9893 dns_rdataset_t *sigrdataset_a = NULL;
9894 dns_rdataset_t *rdataset_aaaa = NULL;
9895 dns_rdataset_t *sigrdataset_aaaa = NULL;
9896 dns_name_t *gluename = dns_fixedname_name(&ge->fixedname);
9897
9898 result = isc_buffer_allocate(msg->mctx, &buffer, 512);
9899 if (ISC_UNLIKELY(result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)) {
9900 goto no_glue;
9901 }
9902
9903 result = dns_message_gettempname(msg, &name);
9904 if (ISC_UNLIKELY(result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)) {
9905 isc_buffer_free(&buffer);
9906 goto no_glue;
9907 }
9908
9909 dns_name_copy(gluename, name, buffer);
9910 dns_message_takebuffer(msg, &buffer);
9911
9912 if (dns_rdataset_isassociated(&ge->rdataset_a)) {
9913 result = dns_message_gettemprdataset(msg, &rdataset_a);
9914 if (ISC_UNLIKELY(result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)) {
9915 dns_message_puttempname(msg, &name);
9916 goto no_glue;
9917 }
9918 }
9919
9920 if (dns_rdataset_isassociated(&ge->sigrdataset_a)) {
9921 result = dns_message_gettemprdataset(msg,
9922 &sigrdataset_a);
9923 if (ISC_UNLIKELY(result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)) {
9924 if (rdataset_a != NULL) {
9925 dns_message_puttemprdataset(msg,
9926 &rdataset_a);
9927 }
9928 dns_message_puttempname(msg, &name);
9929 goto no_glue;
9930 }
9931 }
9932
9933 if (dns_rdataset_isassociated(&ge->rdataset_aaaa)) {
9934 result = dns_message_gettemprdataset(msg,
9935 &rdataset_aaaa);
9936 if (ISC_UNLIKELY(result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)) {
9937 dns_message_puttempname(msg, &name);
9938 if (rdataset_a != NULL) {
9939 dns_message_puttemprdataset(msg,
9940 &rdataset_a);
9941 }
9942 if (sigrdataset_a != NULL) {
9943 dns_message_puttemprdataset(msg,
9944 &sigrdataset_a);
9945 }
9946 goto no_glue;
9947 }
9948 }
9949
9950 if (dns_rdataset_isassociated(&ge->sigrdataset_aaaa)) {
9951 result = dns_message_gettemprdataset(msg,
9952 &sigrdataset_aaaa);
9953 if (ISC_UNLIKELY(result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)) {
9954 dns_message_puttempname(msg, &name);
9955 if (rdataset_a != NULL) {
9956 dns_message_puttemprdataset(msg,
9957 &rdataset_a);
9958 }
9959 if (sigrdataset_a != NULL)
9960 dns_message_puttemprdataset(msg,
9961 &sigrdataset_a);
9962 if (rdataset_aaaa != NULL)
9963 dns_message_puttemprdataset(msg,
9964 &rdataset_aaaa);
9965 goto no_glue;
9966 }
9967 }
9968
9969 if (ISC_LIKELY(rdataset_a != NULL)) {
9970 dns_rdataset_clone(&ge->rdataset_a, rdataset_a);
9971 ISC_LIST_APPEND(name->list, rdataset_a, link);
9972 }
9973
9974 if (sigrdataset_a != NULL) {
9975 dns_rdataset_clone(&ge->sigrdataset_a, sigrdataset_a);
9976 ISC_LIST_APPEND(name->list, sigrdataset_a, link);
9977 }
9978
9979 if (rdataset_aaaa != NULL) {
9980 dns_rdataset_clone(&ge->rdataset_aaaa,
9981 rdataset_aaaa);
9982 ISC_LIST_APPEND(name->list, rdataset_aaaa,
9983 link);
9984 }
9985 if (sigrdataset_aaaa != NULL) {
9986 dns_rdataset_clone(&ge->sigrdataset_aaaa,
9987 sigrdataset_aaaa);
9988 ISC_LIST_APPEND(name->list, sigrdataset_aaaa,
9989 link);
9990 }
9991
9992 dns_message_addname(msg, name, DNS_SECTION_ADDITIONAL);
9993 }
9994
9995no_glue:
9996 RWUNLOCK(&rbtversion->glue_rwlock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
9997
9998 if (found) {
9999 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
10000 }
10001
10002 if (restarted) {
10003 return (ISC_R_FAILURE);
10004 }
10005
10006 /*
10007 * No cached glue was found in the table. Cache it and restart
10008 * this function.
10009 *
10010 * Due to the gap between the read lock and the write lock, it's
10011 * possible that we may cache a duplicate glue table entry, but
10012 * we don't care.
10013 */
10014
10015 ctx.glue_list = NULL;
10016 ctx.rbtdb = rbtdb;
10017 ctx.rbtversion = rbtversion;
10018
10019 RWLOCK(&rbtversion->glue_rwlock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
10020
10021 if (ISC_UNLIKELY(rehash_gluetable(rbtversion))) {
10022 idx = isc_hash_function(&node, sizeof(node),
10023 true, NULL) %
10024 rbtversion->glue_table_size;
10025 }
10026
10027 (void)dns_rdataset_additionaldata(rdataset, glue_nsdname_cb, &ctx);
10028
10029 cur = isc_mem_get(rbtdb->common.mctx, sizeof(*cur));
10030 if (cur == NULL) {
10031 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
10032 goto out;
10033 }
10034
10035 /*
10036 * XXXMUKS: it looks like the dns_dbversion is not destroyed
10037 * when named is terminated by a keyboard break. This doesn't
10038 * cleanup the node reference and keeps the process dangling.
10039 */
10040 /* isc_refcount_increment0(&node->references); */
10041 cur->node = node;
10042
10043 if (ctx.glue_list == NULL) {
10044 /*
10045 * No glue was found. Cache it so.
10046 */
10047 cur->glue_list = (void *) -1;
10048 if (rbtdb->gluecachestats != NULL) {
10049 isc_stats_increment
10050 (rbtdb->gluecachestats,
10051 dns_gluecachestatscounter_inserts_absent);
10052 }
10053 } else {
10054 cur->glue_list = ctx.glue_list;
10055 if (rbtdb->gluecachestats != NULL) {
10056 isc_stats_increment
10057 (rbtdb->gluecachestats,
10058 dns_gluecachestatscounter_inserts_present);
10059 }
10060 }
10061
10062 cur->next = rbtversion->glue_table[idx];
10063 rbtversion->glue_table[idx] = cur;
10064 rbtversion->glue_table_nodecount++;
10065
10066 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
10067
10068 out:
10069 RWUNLOCK(&rbtversion->glue_rwlock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
10070
10071 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
10072 restarted = true;
10073 goto restart;
10074 }
10075
10076 return (result);
10077}
10078
10079/*%
10080 * Routines for LRU-based cache management.
10081 */
10082
10083/*%
10084 * See if a given cache entry that is being reused needs to be updated
10085 * in the LRU-list. From the LRU management point of view, this function is
10086 * expected to return true for almost all cases. When used with threads,
10087 * however, this may cause a non-negligible performance penalty because a
10088 * writer lock will have to be acquired before updating the list.
10089 * If DNS_RBTDB_LIMITLRUUPDATE is defined to be non 0 at compilation time, this
10090 * function returns true if the entry has not been updated for some period of
10091 * time. We differentiate the NS or glue address case and the others since
10092 * experiments have shown that the former tends to be accessed relatively
10093 * infrequently and the cost of cache miss is higher (e.g., a missing NS records
10094 * may cause external queries at a higher level zone, involving more
10095 * transactions).
10096 *
10097 * Caller must hold the node (read or write) lock.
10098 */
10099static inline bool
10100need_headerupdate(rdatasetheader_t *header, isc_stdtime_t now) {
10101 if ((header->attributes &
10102 (RDATASET_ATTR_NONEXISTENT |
10103 RDATASET_ATTR_ANCIENT |
10104 RDATASET_ATTR_ZEROTTL)) != 0)
10105 return (false);
10106
10107#if DNS_RBTDB_LIMITLRUUPDATE
10108 if (header->type == dns_rdatatype_ns ||
10109 (header->trust == dns_trust_glue &&
10110 (header->type == dns_rdatatype_a ||
10111 header->type == dns_rdatatype_aaaa))) {
10112 /*
10113 * Glue records are updated if at least 60 seconds have passed
10114 * since the previous update time.
10115 */
10116 return (header->last_used + 60 <= now);
10117 }
10118
10119 /* Other records are updated if 5 minutes have passed. */
10120 return (header->last_used + 300 <= now);
10121#else
10122 UNUSED(now);
10123
10124 return (true);
10125#endif
10126}
10127
10128/*%
10129 * Update the timestamp of a given cache entry and move it to the head
10130 * of the corresponding LRU list.
10131 *
10132 * Caller must hold the node (write) lock.
10133 *
10134 * Note that the we do NOT touch the heap here, as the TTL has not changed.
10135 */
10136static void
10137update_header(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, rdatasetheader_t *header,
10138 isc_stdtime_t now)
10139{
10140 INSIST(IS_CACHE(rbtdb));
10141
10142 /* To be checked: can we really assume this? XXXMLG */
10143 INSIST(ISC_LINK_LINKED(header, link));
10144
10145 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(rbtdb->rdatasets[header->node->locknum], header, link);
10146 header->last_used = now;
10147 ISC_LIST_PREPEND(rbtdb->rdatasets[header->node->locknum], header, link);
10148}
10149
10150/*%
10151 * Purge some expired and/or stale (i.e. unused for some period) cache entries
10152 * under an overmem condition. To recover from this condition quickly, up to
10153 * 2 entries will be purged. This process is triggered while adding a new
10154 * entry, and we specifically avoid purging entries in the same LRU bucket as
10155 * the one to which the new entry will belong. Otherwise, we might purge
10156 * entries of the same name of different RR types while adding RRsets from a
10157 * single response (consider the case where we're adding A and AAAA glue records
10158 * of the same NS name).
10159 */
10160static void
10161overmem_purge(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, unsigned int locknum_start,
10162 isc_stdtime_t now, bool tree_locked)
10163{
10164 rdatasetheader_t *header, *header_prev;
10165 unsigned int locknum;
10166 int purgecount = 2;
10167
10168 for (locknum = (locknum_start + 1) % rbtdb->node_lock_count;
10169 locknum != locknum_start && purgecount > 0;
10170 locknum = (locknum + 1) % rbtdb->node_lock_count) {
10171 NODE_LOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[locknum].lock,
10172 isc_rwlocktype_write);
10173
10174 header = isc_heap_element(rbtdb->heaps[locknum], 1);
10175 if (header && header->rdh_ttl < now - RBTDB_VIRTUAL) {
10176 expire_header(rbtdb, header, tree_locked,
10177 expire_ttl);
10178 purgecount--;
10179 }
10180
10181 for (header = ISC_LIST_TAIL(rbtdb->rdatasets[locknum]);
10182 header != NULL && purgecount > 0;
10183 header = header_prev) {
10184 header_prev = ISC_LIST_PREV(header, link);
10185 /*
10186 * Unlink the entry at this point to avoid checking it
10187 * again even if it's currently used someone else and
10188 * cannot be purged at this moment. This entry won't be
10189 * referenced any more (so unlinking is safe) since the
10190 * TTL was reset to 0.
10191 */
10192 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(rbtdb->rdatasets[locknum], header,
10193 link);
10194 expire_header(rbtdb, header, tree_locked,
10195 expire_lru);
10196 purgecount--;
10197 }
10198
10199 NODE_UNLOCK(&rbtdb->node_locks[locknum].lock,
10200 isc_rwlocktype_write);
10201 }
10202}
10203
10204static void
10205expire_header(dns_rbtdb_t *rbtdb, rdatasetheader_t *header,
10206 bool tree_locked, expire_t reason)
10207{
10208 set_ttl(rbtdb, header, 0);
10209 mark_header_ancient(rbtdb, header);
10210
10211 /*
10212 * Caller must hold the node (write) lock.
10213 */
10214
10215 if (isc_refcount_current(&header->node->references) == 0) {
10216 /*
10217 * If no one else is using the node, we can clean it up now.
10218 * We first need to gain a new reference to the node to meet a
10219 * requirement of decrement_reference().
10220 */
10221 new_reference(rbtdb, header->node);
10222 decrement_reference(rbtdb, header->node, 0,
10223 isc_rwlocktype_write,
10224 tree_locked ? isc_rwlocktype_write :
10225 isc_rwlocktype_none, false);
10226
10227 if (rbtdb->cachestats == NULL)
10228 return;
10229
10230 switch (reason) {
10231 case expire_ttl:
10232 isc_stats_increment(rbtdb->cachestats,
10233 dns_cachestatscounter_deletettl);
10234 break;
10235 case expire_lru:
10236 isc_stats_increment(rbtdb->cachestats,
10237 dns_cachestatscounter_deletelru);
10238 break;
10239 default:
10240 break;
10241 }
10242
10243 }
10244}
